Name: grey robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: large sign
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: NEWHAVEN.TXT

Name: rigid leather tunic
Desc1: This is a boiled leather cuirass. Only slightly flexible, it
Desc2: has soft leather at the joints and on the arms, and provides
Desc3: good protection.

Name: studded leather tunic
Desc1: This is a vest of thick leather studded with iron rivets. It
Desc2: is a little heavy, but will provide good protection in
Desc3: combat.

Name: chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This is a tunic of small interlinked iron rings, overtop of
Desc2: a thin leather jacket. It is heavy, and makes some noise
Desc3: when in use, but provides very good defense against attack.

Name: scalemail tunic
Desc1: This is a suit of boiled leather with coin-sized iron discs
Desc2: sewn onto it. It is a little heavier than chainmail, but
Desc3: also protects better.

Name: brigandine tunic
Desc1: This is a suit of boiled leather reinforced with iron bands.
Desc2: It is quite heavy, and makes noise when in use due to the
Desc3: clanking of the iron bands, but provides excellent defense
Desc4: in combat.

Name: half-plate corselet
Desc1: This is a corselet of thin steel, worn over a leather
Desc2: jacket. It is very heavy and cumbersome, but provides
Desc3: excellent protection against attacks.

Name: light plate corselet
Desc1: This is corselet of light steel plate, worn over heavy
Desc2: leather. It is very heavy and noisy, but the incredible
Desc3: edge it gives in combat may be worthwhile, if you are strong
Desc4: enough to bear its weight!

Name: full plate corselet
Desc1: This is a heavy platemail corselet, with a chainmail vest
Desc2: underneath. It is so heavy you can barely pick it up, and it
Desc3: clangs noisily when moved, but it is nearly unsurpassed in
Desc4: the protection it provides in combat.

Name: cloth pants
Desc1: This is a pair of simple cloth leggings, with a leather belt
Desc2: to cinch them up. They are light and unrestrictive, but do
Desc3: not provide much in the way of defense.

Name: leather pants
Desc1: This is a pair of soft leather pants. They are comfortable
Desc2: and flexible but are not too heavy, and provide decent
Desc3: defense.

Name: rigid leather pants
Desc1: This is a pair of soft leather pants with rigid leather
Desc2: plates sewn onto them for protection. They are only slightly
Desc3: bulky, and provide fairly good protection.

Name: chainmail leggings
Desc1: These leggings are made of a simple pair of cloth pants,
Desc2: with linked chain-mail overtop. They provide good protection
Desc3: in combat, but make some noise due to the noise they make.

Name: scalemail leggings
Desc1: This is a pair of leather pants with iron discs sewn onto
Desc2: them as protection. They are a little heavy, but give better
Desc3: protection than chainmail does.

Name: brigandine leggings
Desc1: This is a pair of leather pants with iron bands sewn around
Desc2: them. They provide great protection, but are heavy, and make
Desc3: considerable noise due to the clanking of the overlapping
Desc4: bands.

Name: light plate leggings
Desc1: This a pair of steel plate leggings, with heavy leather
Desc2: underneath and at the joints. They are quite heavy, and make
Desc3: tremendous noise, but are invaluable for their defensive
Desc4: potential.

Name: full plate leggings
Desc1: This is pair of heavy plate greaves, with chainmail
Desc2: underneath and at the joints. They are extremely heavy and
Desc3: noisy, but provide excellent protection.

Name: small sign
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: SILVRMRE.TXT

Name: skullcap
Desc1: This is an extremely thin skullcap of steel, designed to be
Desc2: worn over the crown of the head. It provides a little
Desc3: defense.

Name: soft leather cap
Desc1: This is a leather helm with ear and nose-guards. It is light
Desc2: and flexible, and provides decent protection.

Name: hard leather helm
Desc1: This is a rigid leather helm studded with iron rivets. It is
Desc2: much heavier than a regular leather helm, but the iron studs
Desc3: deflect blows.

Name: chain coif
Desc1: This is a snugly-fitting chainmail hood, covering head and
Desc2: neck. It is strong and durable, and fairly light.

Name: pot-helm
Desc1: This is an iron helm with noseguard and leather neck-guard.
Desc2: It is the helm of choice for most guardsmen and warriors, as
Desc3: it is not too heavy, but protects well.

Name: horned helmet
Desc1: This is a solid iron helm, neck-length and horned. Its
Desc2: massive horns curl upwards, like a bull's. It is heavy, but
Desc3: is strong and protects well.

Name: visored greathelm
Desc1: This is a massive steel helm, offering full protection from
Desc2: attacks. Vision is limited to sight through the narrow
Desc3: eyeslits.

Name: cotton gloves
Desc1: This is a pair of light cotton gloves, offering little
Desc2: protection save from the cold.

Name: suede gloves
Desc1: This is a pair of simple suede gloves. They are soft and
Desc2: warm, but are not very protective.

Name: leather gloves
Desc1: This is a pair of soft leather gloves. They are longer than
Desc2: most gloves, coming up to the mid-forearm, and give decent
Desc3: protection versus attack.

Name: hard leather gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of rigid leather gauntlets. They are long,
Desc2: coming nearly up to the elbow, and give good defense. They
Desc3: are the gauntlet of choice for most adventurers.

Name: chain gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair if elbow-length chain gauntlets, with cloth
Desc2: underneath for comfort. They have a leather palm for better
Desc3: weapon grip.

Name: scale gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of soft leather gloves with coin-sized
Desc2: iron discs sewn onto them. They are heavy, as far as gloves
Desc3: go, and have leather palms for better weapon grip.

Name: plate gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of steel plate gauntlets. They are heavy and
Desc2: durable, and provide great protection. They have an open
Desc3: leather palm for increased grip.

Name: cloth shoes
Desc1: This is a pair of light canvas shoes, with coiled rope
Desc2: soles. They are not suited for action of any kind.

Name: padded black boots
Desc1: This is a pair of padded black boots. They come up to mid-
Desc2: shin and are quilted as to reduce noise. This is the
Desc3: footwear of choice for stealth-minded adventurers.

Name: ironwood shield
Desc1: Crafted from an ironwood tree, this shield is thick and
Desc2: offers good deflection of attack. Hardened by magic, it is
Desc3: lighter then metal, and a warmth pulses from its surface,
Desc4: much like a heartbeat.

Name: hardened leather boots
Desc1: This is a pair of rigid leather boots. They come up to the
Desc2: middle of the shin, and are tough and well-made. They give
Desc3: good protection in combat.

Name: chainmail boots
Desc1: This is a pair of rigid leather boots, covered in steel
Desc2: chain links. The links have been muffled, but still make it
Desc3: more difficult for a person to sneak, despite this they
Desc4: offer good protection in combat.

Name: plate boots
Desc1: This is a pair of steel plate sollerets, lined with leather
Desc2: on the inside for comfort. Despite this precaution, however,
Desc3: they are not comfortable at all, although they provide great
Desc4: defense against attack.

Name: travelers cloak
Desc1: This is a light leather cloak, suitable for the road. It
Desc2: gives a little defense, and is good for protection against
Desc3: the elements.

Name: silk cape
Desc1: This is a long silken cape, embroidered with intertwining
Desc2: designs about the hem. A small silver clasp holds it closed.

Name: greatcloak
Desc1: This is a massive animal skin cloak. It is thick and is
Desc2: good protection, and provides great defense against the
Desc3: weather, but is heavy and would get in the way of any
Desc4: stealthy maneuvers.

Name: buckler shield
Desc1: This is a tiny shield, mostly used in tandem with a fencing
Desc2: weapon. It is light and can be moved quickly to deflect
Desc3: attack, but does not provide very good protection.

Name: target shield
Desc1: This is a small wooden shield, used by warriors to practice
Desc2: maneuvers. It is fairly light and protective.

Name: round shield
Desc1: This is a medium-sized round shield. It is a popular shield,
Desc2: as it is moderately heavy, and provides good defense.

Name: spiked shield
Desc1: This is a medium-sized shield with a large iron spike in the
Desc2: centre. It is very heavy, but gives good protection, as well
Desc3: as a little offense.

Name: curved heater
Desc1: This is a traditional knight's shield. It is not too heavy,
Desc2: but is designed to deflect blows well. Its face is blank so
Desc3: that a heraldric symbol or family crest may be placed on it.

Name: kite shield
Desc1: This is a long, thin shield, useful against arrows. It is
Desc2: heavy and somewhat cumbersome, but if you stand sideways it
Desc3: is possible to shield most of the body from attack.

Name: longsword
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: broadsword
Desc1: This is similar to the longsword, but is double-edged and
Desc2: is heavier. It hits hard, but is harder to wield than the
Desc3: longsword.

Name: shortsword
Desc1: This is a two-foot-long blade, useful for close-quarters
Desc2: fighting. It is the standard arm of alley-fighters, and the
Desc3: dwarven tunnel-fighters, who do not have the space available
Desc4: to swing a long sword.

Name: dagger
Desc1: This is a small, sharp knife, used primarily for stabbing.
Desc2: It is easy to handle and to conceal, but it does minor
Desc3: damage. It is completely useless against most heavy armours.

Name: knife
Desc1: This is a wicked-looking curved knife. It is heavier than
Desc2: a dagger, but is also harder to wield.

Name: stiletto
Desc1: This is an extremely thin, edgeless thrusting blade. It is
Desc2: very small and easy to conceal. Its extremely poor combat
Desc3: value makes it useless against all but the most lightly
Desc4: armoured opponents.

Name: battle axe
Desc1: This is a large double-bladed axe, used in one hand. It is
Desc2: a favourite of strong warriors, as it can inflict impressive
Desc3: wounds, and is not so massive as to be unwieldly.

Name: scimitar
Desc1: This is a curved sword, about three feet in length, and
Desc2: bladed upon one edge. It is thin, and fairly light, but can
Desc3: deliver considerable slashing wounds.

Name: short-spear
Desc1: This is a short thrusting spear, used in one hand and
Desc2: usually with a shield. It can do decent impaling damage, and
Desc3: is a favourite of woods dwellers who have to worry about
Desc4: hitting trees with a swing.

Name: sickle
Desc1: This is a sharp, curved crescent of iron. The Druids use
Desc2: this to cut mistletoe and such plants for their woodland
Desc3: worship. In a pinch, it can do decent damage, but it is
Desc4: unwieldly.

Name: hatchet
Desc1: This is a short-hafted light axe, not designed for throwing.
Desc2: It is bladed only on one side, and attacks with this weapon
Desc3: are fairly fast and damaging.

Name: falchion
Desc1: This is an end-heavy sword, with a slight forward curve. It
Desc2: is large and heavy, and does considerable damage in combat.
Desc3: It is a little unwieldly and slow.

Name: greatsword
Desc1: This is a long, heavy, four-foot-long sword. It is quite
Desc2: sharp and deadly, and is bladed on both sides. This two-
Desc3: handed sword can inflict massive damage in battle, but can
Desc4: only be used effectively by the very strong. It can punch
Desc5: through the best platemail with ease.

Name: flamberge
Desc1: This is a medium-sized, wavy-bladed greatsword. It is
Desc2: lighter and faster than a conventional greatsword, and
Desc3: inflicts less damage. It is still extremely effective in
Desc4: combat, however.

Name: bastard sword
Desc1: This is a light two-handed sword. It is about three-and-a-
Desc2: half feet long, midway in size between a broadsword and a
Desc3: greatsword. It is fairly fast and damaging, and is overall
Desc4: a good weapon.

Name: greataxe
Desc1: This is a heavy, long-hafted, double-bladed axe. It is very
Desc2: sharp, and its massive head can inflict horrible wounds on
Desc3: an opponent. It is very slow and unwieldly, but armour is
Desc4: almost useless against it as it punches right through.

Name: halberd
Desc1: This is six-foot pole with an axe head mounted at the top.
Desc2: It is extremely slow, and is quite clumsly to wield, but the
Desc3: damage its huge, arcing swings can inflict is quiet high.

Name: pike
Desc1: This is a six-foot-long spear. It is too long to be used
Desc2: very well, but provides good defense, and does considerable
Desc3: damage.

Name: long-spear
Desc1: This is a four foot long spear, used with both hands. It is
Desc2: fairly quick and is a good defensive weapon, but it does not
Desc3: do great damage.

Name: glaive
Desc1: This is a heavy blade mounted on the end of a six-foot pole.
Desc2: It is only bladed on one side, and is used with a harsh
Desc3: chopping motion. It is slow and clumsy, but does very good
Desc4: damage.

Name: mace
Desc1: This is a steel ball mounted on a two-foot wooden rod. It
Desc2: is a well-rounded weapon, providing adequate defense and
Desc3: attack. This is the weapon of choice for Priests and the
Desc4: like.

Name: morning-star
Desc1: This is a spiked steel ball, attached by chain to a two-foot
Desc2: wooden rod. It does good damage, as when it is swung the
Desc3: ball reaches great speeds, but is not too fast or wieldy.

Name: heavy-mace
Desc1: This is a heavy steel ball mounted on a wooden handle. It is
Desc2: fairly large and heavy, and does good damage. It is mainly
Desc3: used by the stronger of the Priesthood.

Name: club
Desc1: This is a knob-ended piece of wood. It is generally a poor
Desc2: weapon, doing decent damage but being comparatively slow.
Desc3: Its main advantage is that it is readily available.

Name: warhammer
Desc1: This is a martial version of the tool by the same name. It
Desc2: has a heavy, flattened head on one side, and a blunt spike
Desc3: on the other. The damage it can do is considerable, but due
Desc4: to its weight it is fairly slow.

Name: spiked club
Desc1: This is a rod with jagged nails stuck through it. It is not
Desc2: very quick or effective against armour, but can do good
Desc3: damage against unarmored foes as the nails rip through them.
Desc4: It is mainly used my impoverished thugs who cannot afford
Desc5: any better weapons.

Name: whip
Desc1: This is a four-foot-long braided leather whip. Overall, it
Desc2: is not a very good weapon, as it is used mainly to entangle
Desc3: and to cause pain.

Name: war mattock
Desc1: This is a large, heavy, square-headed mace with a flat end.
Desc2: It does good damage and is a fairly good weapon.

Name: quarterstaff
Desc1: This is a six-foot wooden staff, bound about the middle with
Desc2: strips of cloth. It is a simple weapon, and does not deal
Desc3: very much damage, but provides good defense as it is quite
Desc4: quick to use.

Name: iron-capped staff
Desc1: This is a staff with iron caps on the ends. It does more
Desc2: damage than a conventional staff, but is also slower due to
Desc3: the added weight.

Name: flail
Desc1: This is a large, two-handed morning star. It is heavy and
Desc2: extremely damaging, as well as being slow and poor on the
Desc3: defensive side. It is a good weapon for brawny warriors who
Desc4: prefer blunt weapons.

Name: battle-hammer
Desc1: This is a large, two-handed sledgehammer. It is very heavy
Desc2: and quite slow, but the damage it does in battle is
Desc3: considerable.

Name: iron staff
Desc1: This is a wooden staff with an iron core. It is quite heavy
Desc2: for its size, and is not as easily maneuvered as a regular
Desc3: staff, but it also does more damage.

Name: sandals
Desc1: This is a simple pair of leather thong sandals.

Name: wall
Desc1: This smooth wall is made of carefully-fitted bricks. As you
Desc2: examine it, one of the bricks seems to stick out of the wall
Desc3: as if it were a gross boil.

Name: crack
Desc1: There is a small crack in the wall here. Investigating it
Desc2: further, you find a small button!

Name: tapestry
Desc1: This is an elaborately-woven tapestry, made of red and gold
Desc2: thread. It depicts a battle between a griffon and a dragon,
Desc3: their bodies entwined one around the other. Moving it aside,
Desc4: you see a small crack in the wall.

Name: hole
Desc1: This jagged hole is about four feet in diameter, and looks
Desc2: as if it was made by some extremely powerful beast. Peering
Desc3: in, you can see the shadowy recesses of a cavernous tunnel!

Name: fountain
Desc1: This beautiful alabaster fountain gleams in the light. It is
Desc2: carved to ressemble the arched neck and head of a dragon,
Desc3: and it spews water into a large circular dish in the form of
Desc4: a clamshell.

Name: statue
Desc1: This is a white marble statue of a ten-foot-tall knight in
Desc2: full plate armour. He stands resting both hands on the
Desc3: pommel of his sword, and his shield rests up against the
Desc4: wall. Although his face cannot be seen through his visored
Desc5: helmet, he conveys a feeling of sorrow.

Name: sword
Desc1: The knight's massive bastard-sword is intricately engraved
Desc2: with ancient runic symbols. It is nearly six feet long, and
Desc3: even though this must be a stone duplicate of the real
Desc4: weapon, it appears to be razor-sharp.

Name: griffon shield
Desc1: This golden kite shield looks as if it has separated from
Desc2: some wall or fixture. It is rough around the edges but has
Desc3: an inner beauty and shine to it. An intricate carving of a
Desc4: rearing griffon is shown on the shield, showing it to be a
Desc5: symbol of Silvermere. Inscripted on the front of the shield

Name: griffon
Desc1: The carved griffon is detailed exquisitely. Each claw and
Desc2: feather is defined so exactly that it must have taken years
Desc3: to complete. The griffon's beak appears as sharp as a sword
Desc4: blade, and its eye shines like a star... but upon closer
Desc5: inspection, you see that the eye is actually a button!

Name: jeweled longsword
Desc1: This exquisitely-crafted blade is honed to a razor-sharp
Desc2: edge, and its blade is embellished with highlighted runes
Desc3: and engravings. Its hilt is encrusted with glittering gems
Desc4: of all sizes, and its pommel is fashioned in the form of a
Desc5: dragon's claw gripping a blue sapphire.

Name: glowing warhammer
Desc1: This large, one-handed warhammer shines with a soft blue
Desc2: glow. It appears to be made of a dark metal, and although
Desc3: looks heavy is in fact quite easy to swing. Its flat, broad
Desc4: head is ornately carved with sigils of power.

Name: high-necked robes
Desc1: These long, voluminous robes have a stiff, high-necked
Desc2: collar which gives a very dramatic appearance to the wearer.
Desc3: The deep green of the robes is offset by brilliant golden
Desc4: runes which adorn the cuffs and hem, and a golden sash
Desc5: around the waist keeps it closed.

Name: scroll of magic missile
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of illuminate
Desc1: This parchemnt is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of vine strike
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: explaining the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of charm animal
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: explaining the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: songsheet of item lore
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Item Lore.

Name: songsheet of valour
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Valour.

Name: songsheet of misfortune
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Misfortune.

Name: songsheet of discord
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Misfortune.

Name: songsheet of brilliance
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Brilliance.

Name: songsheet of wisdom
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Wisdom.

Name: songsheet of might
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Might.

Name: songsheet of agility
Desc1: This parchement is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Agility.

Name: iron ring
Desc1: This is a plain iron ring, polished so that it gleams
Desc2: brilliantly.

Name: copper ring
Desc1: This ring is made of three copper threads, meticulously
Desc2: polished and lacquered, and braided together to form a band.

Name: silver ring
Desc1: This is a thick silver ring, heavily carved with angular
Desc2: lines and designs.

Name: amethyst ring
Desc1: This beautiful, silver ring is set with a trio of small,
Desc2: uncut, lavender-hued amethysts.

Name: golden amulet
Desc1: This amulet is made of heavy yellow gold, worked masterfully
Desc2: into the form of a stylized sun.

Name: silver holy amulet
Desc1: This simple but beautifully-crafted amulet is worked in
Desc2: the shape of a holy symbol, and is made out of blue-white
Desc3: silver. It is hung upon a chain of silver links.

Name: golden braided belt
Desc1: This belt is fashioned out of thick golden bands, to form
Desc2: a wide braid. It is encrusted with small rubies and
Desc3: diamonds, and the buckle is a large platinum star.

Name: platinum tiara
Desc1: This light crown is extremely simple but classically made.
Desc2: It is a single band of platinum, delicately etched and set
Desc3: with a single eye-sized sapphire at the brow.

Name: silver bracers
Desc1: These engraved silver bracers are etched with ancient runes
Desc2: and symbols, and are beautifully crafted.

Name: golden armbands
Desc1: This matched pair of golden armbands are made of heavy
Desc2: yellow gold with the texture of honey, and are unadorned.

Name: maul
Desc1: This huge, two-handed mace is nearly six feet in length. It
Desc2: is so massive that you have difficulty even lifting it, and
Desc3: the damage it does in combat must be incredible, although it
Desc4: is incredibly slow. Only the strongest can wield this weapon
Desc5: with any effect.

Name: black star key
Desc1: This black iron key's head is shaped like a circled
Desc2: five-pointed star. You get a faint feeling of distaste when
Desc3: touching it.

Name: scroll of cure paralysis
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: torch
Desc1: This long wooden stick is bound by stips of oil-soaked
Desc2: cloth. When lit, it provides fairly good illumination.

Name: lantern
Desc1: This is a small iron lantern, its glass bulb protected by
Desc2: shutters. When filled with oil and lit, it provides very
Desc3: good illumination.

Name: bone key
Desc1: This small, fragile-looking key appears to be made of bone.
Desc2: It is quite cold to the touch.

Name: silvery mace
Desc1: This brilliant silvery mace shines with an inner light. Its
Desc2: broad head is studded, and its hilt is wrapped in white
Desc3: leather. A thong hangs from the base of its handle.

Name: black chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This suit of chainmail is enameled with a flat black lacquer
Desc2: finish. It sports cruel-looking spikes on the shoulder
Desc3: guards and has on it a badge made in the image of a red
Desc4: horned skull.

Name: black shield
Desc1: This heavy black iron shield is emblazoned with a red
Desc2: horned skull. It is quite heavy, but is large enough to
Desc3: provide good protection from attacks.

Name: tomb door
Desc1: This large stone door is carved with holy images and
Desc2: symbols. A large plaque in the centre is engraved with an
Desc3: elaborate script, but the age of the writing is such that it
Desc4: is indecipherable to you.

Name: stone door
Desc1: This huge stone portal is completely plain except for a
Desc2: black keyhole set in the exact centre of its grey face.
Desc3: Spidery runes are carved all about this hole, in a script
Desc4: which you have never seen before.

Name: sarcophagus
Desc1: This white stone coffin is seemingly carved out of one huge
Desc2: piece of rock, and is made in the likeliness of the long-
Desc3: dead noble for whom it was commissioned. You can see no seam
Desc4: or binding which would enable it to open.

Name: lever
Desc1: This simple iron lever is set in the centre of a steel
Desc2: plate. Its round knob is dull and smoothed by much use.

Name: manhole
Desc1: This is a three-foot-wide hole in the centre of the street,
Desc2: concealed by a perforated stone cover which allows the
Desc3: stream of water and refuse to drain into the sewers.

Name: iron sink
Desc1: This large iron sink is crudely fashioned to resemble a
Desc2: toad, its gaping mouth open wide. Four webbed feet hold it
Desc3: high off of the ground. Upon further examination, you think
Desc4: that the inside is extensively rusted... until you notice
Desc5: the pool of red liquid on the floor beneath the sink and
Desc6: realize that the 'rust' is actually dried blood.

Name: fireplace
Desc1: This squat, gaping fireplace is completely blackened with
Desc2: soot. A large iron hook hangs inside for a pot which isn't
Desc3: there, and the bricks which it is made of are beginning to
Desc4: crumble and fall out.

Name: brick
Desc1: Searching the bricks in the fireplace, you eventually find
Desc2: one whose deceptive newness is masked by dirt. It is
Desc3: actually made of steel, and moves easily under your touch.

Name: black door
Desc1: Steel bands reinforce this black wooden door. A small
Desc2: shuttered slit is cut at eye level, allowing whomever is
Desc3: inside to look out, but not allowing you to look in. An
Desc4: elaborate depression in the shape of a five-pointed star
Desc5: is set just above the handle of the door.

Name: spiked collar
Desc1: This heavy iron collar is studded with cruel-looking spikes.
Desc2: It is large enough that it must have been worn by an animal
Desc3: of great size, and could comfortably fit around the neck of
Desc4: a human. It has some strange runes inscribed about its edge.

Name: rope and grapple
Desc1: This is a coil of braided hemp rope, strongly woven and
Desc2: well-made. It could hold the weight of even the heaviest
Desc3: adventurer. It is attached to a heavy four-pronged iron
Desc4: grapple, and is useful for climbing up out of pits or over
Desc5: obstacles.

Name: red skull
Desc1: This huge horned skull is carved right into the face of the
Desc2: wall. It is so finely made that is appears to be alive,
Desc3: leering hideously at you. Its large eye sockets are like
Desc4: bottomless pits, with no light reflecting from within the
Desc5: polished holes whatsoever. Its strong jaw is clenched shut,
Desc6: and its apparently razor-sharp teeth fit perfectly together.

Name: scroll of greater curse
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of divine favour
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of divine disfavour
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of black wind
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of godheal
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of god's wrath
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of great healing rain
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of paralyze
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of divine fury
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: sacrificial robes
Desc1: These jet black robes are made of a heavy, tightly-woven
Desc2: cloth. The cuffs, collar and hem are adorned with blood-red
Desc3: sigils and glyphs. They radiate a definite aura of evil.

Name: emerald-tipped crozier
Desc1: This long cherrywood staff has been polished to a mirror
Desc2: shine and gilded with elaborate designs along its length.
Desc3: At its end, an emerald curl glitters and shines in the the
Desc4: light. This holy weapon allows a priest to channel divine
Desc5: intervention from his or her god!

Name: bloodstained shortsword
Desc1: This needle-pointed blade is about two feet long, and is
Desc2: razor-sharp. It is made of some dark metal, and seems to be
Desc3: permanently stained with blood. A red rune glows brightly
Desc4: at the base of the blade.

Name: moonblade
Desc1: This finely-made sword glows with a silvery light. It is
Desc2: extremely sharp and seems to be made of some sort of
Desc3: translucent metal. Pale yellow runes engraved into its
Desc4: surface glow softly.

Name: switch
Desc1: This is a simple iron switch, set under the edge of the
Desc2: stone table.

Name: stone table
Desc1: This is a huge stone table, its edge right at your eye
Desc2: level. Deep cracks riddle its surface, and it is worn with
Desc3: age and heavy use. A stone chair of appropriate size stands
Desc4: nearby.

Name: shortbow
Desc1: This small curved bow is made out of a light, polished
Desc2: wood. It is tightly strung, and has a light pull. It is
Desc3: fairly effective at close range, but has not the power for
Desc4: extreme range or damage. It comes with a small quiver
Desc5: filled with arrows.

Name: huge darkwood club
Desc1: This massive club is about six feet in length, and is banded
Desc2: about the hilt with a thick strap of greasy leather. It
Desc3: would be nearly impossible for any normal being to wield
Desc4: this, much less even pick it up!

Name: platinum ring
Desc1: This small, shiny platinum band is unadorned but is very
Desc2: beautiful in a simple sort of way. It is perfectly round,
Desc3: and isn't scratched in the slightest, which is a testament
Desc4: to its maker.

Name: golden belt
Desc1: This wide belt seems to be made of golden chain links, and
Desc2: is fastened with a solid platinum buckle crafted in the
Desc3: shape of a coiled cobra.

Name: ruby necklace
Desc1: This glittering necklace is made of a fine silver chain,
Desc2: with small rubies set about it in mountings shaped like the
Desc3: leaves of flowers.

Name: black leather tunic
Desc1: This leather vest is made of a glossy black leather which
Desc2: seems to absorb the surrounding light. It does not weigh
Desc3: much at all, and is very flexible.

Name: holy medallion
Desc1: This beautiful platinum medallion is exquisitely crafted
Desc2: with the symbols of the gods. It seems to vibrate quietly
Desc3: when you touch its smooth surface.

Name: platinum bracers
Desc1: These thin silver bracers would be plain if not for the
Desc2: strange, swirling runes engraved along them. The metal seems
Desc3: warm and strangely pliant, as if some unnatural life lurked
Desc4: within.

Name: gold ring
Desc1: This glittering golden ring is quite large, and is studded
Desc2: with opalescent black jewels.

Name: elven war-spear
Desc1: This magnificent spear has a three-foot-long shaft of pale
Desc2: white wood as hard as steel. Its razor-sharp head is leaf-
Desc3: shaped, and could cut a hair lengthwise. It is used by
Desc4: grasping the centre of the shaft with one hand, and the butt
Desc5: with the other, giving excellent maneuverability and
Desc6: accuracy. This is a favourite of the elven hunters.

Name: laen longsword
Desc1: The longsword is made of an unknown crystal-like substance.
Desc2: You notice it gleam with power when it reflects the sun's
Desc3: light.

Name: vorpal sword
Desc1: This long, strangely-crafted sword is made out of some
Desc2: unknown type of metal, which glitters like silver, but is
Desc3: as dark as jet. Its blade is so sharp that even the
Desc4: slightest touch with the edge could sever a finger. This
Desc5: otherwordly weapon would prove deadly in battle.

Name: sunsword
Desc1: This heavy golden sword burns with a brilliant fiery light.
Desc2: Its hilt is wrapped in black leather, its pommel and guards
Desc3: elaborately engraved with stylized suns. The arcane power
Desc4: emanating from this weapon is enormous, and it would be
Desc5: impressive in battle.

Name: prismatic claymore
Desc1: This blade of four feet has been crafted from an alien metal
Desc2: of ever-changing colours. The sword looks quite sharp and
Desc3: hums with magical energy. Five gems have been fashioned into
Desc4: the hilt: amber, amethyst, onyx, ruby and emerald. Each one
Desc5: is marked with a small silver rune and they all seem to glow
Desc6: in unison.

Name: minor healing potion
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with a shimmering red
Desc2: elixir. It is closed by a simple cork stopper.

Name: scroll of divine mercy
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: songsheet of life
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Life.

Name: ebony greataxe
Desc1: This large crystalline greataxe absorbs all light like a
Desc2: hole in space. It is extremely cold to the touch, and is
Desc3: surrounded with a sinister aura.

Name: blackened skin-bound book
Desc1: This ancient tome smells rank and seems to be made of the
Desc2: blackened skin of a human! Inside contains many spidery-
Desc3: runed pages.

Name: cracks
Desc1: Searching the table, you find a crack wide enough to put
Desc2: your arm through. Looking inside, you see a sturdy iron
Desc3: switch embedded deep within!

Name: bas-relief image
Desc1: This beautifully-carved image is that of an angular, glowing
Desc2: figure garbed in flowing robes. Great feathered wings spread
Desc3: out majestically from its back, and its head is bowed as if
Desc4: in supplication. Its androgynous face radiates a feeling of
Desc5: serenity and peace.

Name: brass plaque
Desc1: This rectangular brass plaque has been engraved thus:
Desc2: No form
Desc3: No mouth with which to speak
Desc4: Yet sings with a thousand voices
Desc5: No legs upon which to stand
Desc6: Yet runs faster than any man.

Name: ebony triangle
Desc1: This is a triangular piece of ebony so black that it almost
Desc2: appears to be a rip in space. It is inverted so that it
Desc3: points toward the ground. A golden sun adorns the bottom-
Desc4: most point, a silvery-white crescent moon is in the top left
Desc5: corner, and in the top right corner is a seven-pointed star
Desc6: of blue-tinged silver.

Name: golden sun symbol
Desc1: This simply-wrought sun symbol seems to be made of a fine
Desc2: yellow gold. It is not embedded in the ebony triangle, but
Desc3: appears to be affixed to it somehow. Upon closer inspection,
Desc4: you see that although you cannot remove it, it may be
Desc5: possible to move it somehow. It occupies the southern point
Desc6: of the triangle.

Name: silvery moon symbol
Desc1: This waxing crescent moon appears to be made of a white
Desc2: metal, possibly platinum. It is fixed to the triangle, but
Desc3: you think it may be able to be moved in some way.

Name: seven-pointed star symbol
Desc1: This star is crafted out of a bluish silver, and its seven
Desc2: points are evenly spaced about its perimeter. It is set in
Desc3: the top right corner of the ebony triangle, and although it
Desc4: is affixed there you get the impression that it is meant to
Desc5: be moved.

Name: stone face
Desc1: As you look closer, the stone face comes to life. Its eyes
Desc2: flicker open, and as it opens its lips, a chilling, hollow
Desc3: voice whispers the words:
Desc4: Never seen, always felt
Desc5: Without you are dead as stone.

Name: minotaur statue
Desc1: This crudely-wrought statue easily fills the entire wall
Desc2: from floor to ceiling. It depicts a hideous bull-headed
Desc3: creature with the muscular torso of a man, and hairy legs
Desc4: with cloven hooves. It wields a massive greataxe, and the
Desc5: expression on its face is one of sadistic joy. You notice
Desc6: some words scratched into the floor next to the statue.

Name: statue's stone greataxe
Desc1: This massive axe is huge even for a two-handed weapon. It
Desc2: has a single massive blade, and looks like the axes
Desc3: executioners use to remove their victims' heads from their
Desc4: necks. It appears that there is a joint at the base of the
Desc5: greataxe's handle, where it is gripped by the statue,
Desc6: allowing it to be moved somewhat.

Name: statue's horned head
Desc1: Long and terrible horns jut out from either side of the
Desc2: minotaur statue's head. Looking closer, you notice they are
Desc3: both jointed at their bases. Your curiosity aroused, you
Desc4: inspect the head thoroughly and find some other mysterious
Desc5: discoveries -- both the statue's eyes and nose ring appear
Desc6: to have been set in after the creation of the statue.

Name: statue's eyes
Desc1: The minotaur's eyes are much more skillfully crafted than
Desc2: the rest of the statue, and appear to have been set in after
Desc3: the main statue body was created. They reflect what looks
Desc4: like an attitude of utter fearlessness and ferocity, and you
Desc5: shudder when you think that the real beast must truly exist.
Desc6: At any rate, since they are separate, they might be moved.

Name: words scratched into floor
Desc1: There are but a few straggling characters scratched into the
Desc2: floor here, and due to their shaky hand you presume that
Desc3: they were written in haste. Apparently parts have been
Desc4: worn out with the passage of time. They read: "Do n#t push
Desc5: th# le## ey#! #or#, ##e, h###, #### is th# #ay thr##gh."
Desc6: There appears to be more, but much is scratched out.

Name: statue's nose ring
Desc1: This is a simple stone hoop set through the nostrils of the
Desc2: statue's nose. It appears to be able to move freely, and
Desc3: the construction of the whole face indicates to you that
Desc4: this statue is not all that it seems.

Name: bone staircase
Desc1: This disturbing stair is seemingly comprised of hundreds of
Desc2: bleached bones. There are bones of all types of creatures
Desc3: here, including many odd, alien ones that must have come
Desc4: from beasts you have never heard of. You cannot tell what
Desc5: holds the staircase together, as its bewilderingly rickety
Desc6: shape defies most natural laws of construction.

Name: iron door
Desc1: This massive iron door must be at least twelve feet in
Desc2: height, and six feet across. It is heavily riveted and
Desc3: reinforced, and although you cannot possibly know how thick
Desc4: it is, you surmise it would be nearly impossible to batter
Desc5: down. A black hole about an inch in diameter is located on
Desc6: the right edge of the door.

Name: wooden table
Desc1: This is a fairly ordinary oaken table, about six feet by
Desc2: four feet in size. It has four stumps as legs, and stands
Desc3: three feet off of the ground.

Name: stone shelves
Desc1: These crude stone shelves have been carved out of the wall
Desc2: by the use of some sharp, heavy instrument. Placed on these
Desc3: shelves is a variety of disgusting objects, ranging from
Desc4: a pile of rancid scalps to a jar full of fingerbones. Dead
Desc5: bats and reptiles also occupy space here.

Name: bone-handled headcutter
Desc1: This is a massive, double-handed axe with a shaft made out
Desc2: of the petrified bone of some unknown creature. Its blade is
Desc3: huge and heavy, and its single edge appears to be razor-
Desc4: sharp.

Name: ruby key
Desc1: This is a large silver key, with an eye-sized ruby set in
Desc2: the handle. It is set upon a thick leather thong.

Name: serpent staff
Desc1: This long, twisted mahogany staff is carved in the form of a
Desc2: slender snake. Small glittering emeralds in its eyes glow
Desc3: with an inner fire, and it is warm to the touch.

Name: golden broadsword
Desc1: This long, leaf-bladed broadsword shines with a mirrorlike
Desc2: golden finish. Its crossguard is fashioned to look like a
Desc3: pair of spreading wings, and the pommel is a bird's claw
Desc4: clutching an amber stone. A strange, stylized five-pointed
Desc5: star is etched into the blade near its base.

Name: golden breastplate
Desc1: This elegant golden breastplate has been crafted to look
Desc2: like a muscled torso, the model of which must have been
Desc3: impressive indeed. It is polished well enough that you can
Desc4: clearly see your reflection in its surface, and is
Desc5: surprisingly light for its size.

Name: rosewood staff
Desc1: This long, straight staff is quite slender and looks as if
Desc2: you could snap it in two, but in actuality cannot even be
Desc3: bent in the slightest. It is plain and unadorned, with the
Desc4: exception of small runes encircling the top and bottom ends.

Name: shimmering white robes
Desc1: These extremely plain and unadorned robes seem to made out
Desc2: of plain cotton, but there is definitely something special
Desc3: about them that you just can't put your finger on. They are
Desc4: soft and comfortable, and their mere touch soothes you. Holy
Desc5: symbols are worked into the hem with a simple stitch.

Name: cure poison potion
Desc1: This small metal flask is stopped up with a cork. Opening
Desc2: it up, you see a thick violet liquid sloshing about. It
Desc3: smells like sour berries, but none like you have ever
Desc4: smelled before.

Name: starsteel scimitar
Desc1: This curved sword appears to have been crafted from an
Desc2: extremely rare metal called starsteel. The blade shines
Desc3: bluish-silver and the edge glitters brightly. A single
Desc4: glittering diamond has been set in its pommel, and spiral
Desc5: symbols inlaid in its hilt glow warmly.

Name: red robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but it quite light.

Name: black robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: white robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: green robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: blue robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: violet robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: yellow robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: orange robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: leather belt
Desc1: This is a plain leather belt, with a square iron buckle to
Desc2: hold it closed.

Name: iron ration
Desc1: This is a small package containing specially-preserved and
Desc2: cured meat, some dried fruits, and sack of varied nuts. It
Desc3: is the staple of far-ranging adventurers who either have no
Desc4: hunting skills or who don't have the inclination to hunt for
Desc5: their food.

Name: waterskin
Desc1: This is a small waterskin made of waterproofed leather. It
Desc2: holds a few litres of water.

Name: incense
Desc1: This is a small stick of incense. It is sometimes burned in
Desc2: religious ceremonies as it has a somewhat soothing effect
Desc3: when inhaled and helps concentration.

Name: bone charm
Desc1: This is a strange, yellowed bone amulet strung on a crude
Desc2: string. it has unsettling symbols carved on its surface, and
Desc3: it feels slightly warm in your palm.

Name: brass lamp
Desc1: This is an ancient, heavily-etched brass lamp. It has been
Desc2: polished to the point that you can see the reflection of
Desc3: your face clearly in its surface. It is filled with a sweet-
Desc4: smelling scented oil.

Name: glass mirror
Desc1: This is a circular glass mirror, set in a carved wooden
Desc2: frame. It is a fairly common sight, and one can be found in
Desc3: nearly every maiden's possession.

Name: carved ivory mask
Desc1: This is an odd ivory face-plate, with two silken strings to
Desc2: tie behind your ears to keep it in place. It has two thin
Desc3: eye slits to see through, and is ornately carved with
Desc4: delicate swirling designs.

Name: silk robe
Desc1: This is a beautiful silken robe, glossy midnight blue in
Desc2: colour. It is durable and extremely smooth to the touch. On
Desc3: its back a slender, sinuous dragon-like creature is curled
Desc4: about a magnificent silver orb. It is bound about the waist
Desc5: with a shimmering silver sash.

Name: tankard of mead
Desc1: This is a large, heavy wooden mug filled with a sweet honey
Desc2: mead. It is very tasty.

Name: jug of dark ale
Desc1: This is a fair-sized earthenware jug of dark brewed ale. It
Desc2: is quite strong, and has a slightly bitter taste.

Name: bottle of wine
Desc1: This is a small corked bottle of red wine. It is not of the
Desc2: highest quality, but nonetheless has a slight tartness and
Desc3: full flavour.

Name: roast mutton
Desc1: This is a greasy, but well-done joint of mutton. It smells
Desc2: wonderful!

Name: beef stew
Desc1: This is a small earthenware bowl filled with a thick,
Desc2: nutritious stew comprised of beef and onions.

Name: fine broadsword
Desc1: This is an extremely well-crafted blade of high steel. Its
Desc2: apparent age has not affected its condition, and it still
Desc3: holds a sharp edge.

Name: scroll of magic armour
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of flash
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of shockshield
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of prot. from evil
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonationsctly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of prot. from good
Desc1: This unholy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of cure blindness
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of blight
Desc1: This unholy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of poison bolt
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of burning aura
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of acid jet
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: songsheet of charm
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Charm.

Name: songsheet of foolishness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Foolishness.

Name: songsheet of stupidity
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Stupidity.

Name: songsheet of weakness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Weakness.

Name: songsheet of clumsiness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Clumsiness.

Name: songsheet of traveling
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Traveling.

Name: songsheet of blasting
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Blasting.

Name: scroll of elemental chaos
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of stone strike
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of freedom
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of entangle
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of slow
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of speed
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of vampiric touch
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of enslave
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of confusion
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of sunbolt
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of control undead
Desc1: This unholy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of blind
Desc1: This unholy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: hellblade
Desc1: Dark fire rises from this blade, even as damnation is
Desc2: spelled out in twisted runes along its length. Screams
Desc3: of agony can be heard as this sword weaves through the air,
Desc4: its keen edge unstoppable against most protection. Swords
Desc5: such as this can only come from the netherworld, and most
Desc6: carry a horrific price for wielding its power.

Name: scroll of hold person
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: ancient scroll
Desc1: This ancient scroll holds cryptic writing within it that
Desc2: seem glow with a dangerous power. They look to be priestly
Desc3: runes inscribed upon its aged skin.

Name: scroll of holy force
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of unholy force
Desc1: This unholy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: tarnished chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This is a tunic of iron chain armour. It appears to be well-
Desc2: used, as it is covered with a thin layer of rust and many
Desc3: nicks and scratches.

Name: padded vest
Desc1: This is a heavy vest made out of crudely-quilted cloth. It
Desc2: is one-size-fits-all, with a rope belt to cinch the waist.
Desc3: It provides decent protection, but is very heavy for its
Desc4: combat worth.

Name: padded pants
Desc1: This is a simple pair of heavy cloth pants. They are of
Desc2: questionable quality, and are tailored to fit nearly anyone.
Desc3: A rope is tied about the waist to keep them up.

Name: padded helm
Desc1: This is an open-face helmet made out of heavy quilted cloth.
Desc2: Its multiple layers of crude cloth make it fairly heavy for
Desc3: its meagre protection, but it is better than entering combat
Desc4: without one. A bare head makes an inviting target to
Desc5: opponents.

Name: padded gloves
Desc1: These heavy gloves are made of a canvas-like cloth, crudely
Desc2: stitched. They are a common sight on any working man's hands
Desc3: as they protect well from chafing, and provide some
Desc4: protection from damage.

Name: padded boots
Desc1: These knee-length boots are made of heavy quilted cloth,
Desc2: with coiled rope soles. They provide little protection, and
Desc3: are fairly heavy, but they are better than nothing.

Name: claw glyph
Desc1: This is a carving of a cruelly-hooked, clawed hand. It is
Desc2: inscribed in the centre of the marble wall, and is circled
Desc3: by two concentric rings. Directly underneath the claw glyph
Desc4: is a small, round button.

Name: iron key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted in the form
Desc2: of a coiled serpent.

Name: golden battleaxe
Desc1: This heavy, double-bladed hand axe appears to be made of a
Desc2: glittering gold. Its razor-sharp blade gleams in the light,
Desc3: illuminating the miniscule runes covering its surface.

Name: flame glyph
Desc1: This is a carving of a stylized flame, surrounded by two
Desc2: concentric rings. Directly underneath it is a small round
Desc3: button.

Name: obsidian key
Desc1: This is a large shiny key carved from obsidian stone. Its
Desc2: handle is wrapped with silver thread.

Name: mithril cutlass
Desc1: This three-foot-long blade is crafted out of the finest
Desc2: metal known -- mithril. Its blade is so keen it could cut a
Desc3: hair, and its balance is perfect. Its slightly-curved blade
Desc4: can slice through steel and flesh with equal ease.

Name: fist glyph
Desc1: This is an image of a mailed, clenched fist carved into the
Desc2: wall. It is surrounded by a pair of concentric circles. One
Desc3: of the circles appears to be outlined, as though it were a
Desc4: button carved into the glyph.

Name: stone key
Desc1: This is a large stone key, made out of a black-flecked
Desc2: granite.

Name: sign
Desc1: ** Choose your path wisely **

Name: copper key
Desc1: This is a large copper key. Its handle has an eye stamped
Desc2: into it.

Name: shimmering greatsword
Desc1: This exquisite silvery greatsword is polished to a
Desc2: mirrorlike sheen. Its hilt is wrapped in cords of gold, and
Desc3: is heavily worked with holy symbols.

Name: platinum mace
Desc1: This well-balanced mace has a round head made out of
Desc2: reinforced platinum, with a shaft of black iron. Its head is
Desc3: inscribed with holy symbols, and there is a powerful aura of
Desc4: power surrounding it.

Name: black flail
Desc1: This large, jet-black flail has glowing red runes burning
Desc2: along its length. Its three heads are spiked and would cause
Desc3: great damage in battle.

Name: crystal shortsword
Desc1: This razor-edged blade is made of chiseled green crystal.
Desc2: Its hilt is crafted out of black steel, and is bound with
Desc3: silver cord.

Name: ebony ninjato
Desc1: This straight singled-edged blade is made out of some
Desc2: strange black metal. Its hilt is forged into the shape of a
Desc3: black panther with glowing amber stones for eyes.

Name: flametongue
Desc1: This long, needle-pointed blade is made of shining high
Desc2: steel. Its hilt is carved obsidian, and is inlayed with
Desc3: small rubies. When drawn, the blade bursts into flame,
Desc4: burning those whom it hits.

Name: darkwood staff
Desc1: This is a living branch from a darkwood tree. It is warm to
Desc2: the touch, and you can feel the lifeblood flowing within.
Desc3: A silver sheath caps the bottom of the staff, and the centre
Desc4: is carved with intricate looping designs to provide good
Desc5: grip.

Name: obsidian runestaff
Desc1: This is a six-foot-long staff of a glossy jet black
Desc2: substance. Its surface is heavily carved with swirling runes
Desc3: which seem to pulse and glow redly with an inner light.

Name: jeweled main-gauche
Desc1: This long-bladed knife is meant to be wielded in the left
Desc2: hand as a defensive weapon. It has a wide guard and strong
Desc3: blade, which allow it to turn aside most weapons. It is
Desc4: quite ornate, and an eye-sized ruby is set in its pommel.

Name: silver rapier
Desc1: This light sword has a long, thin blade designed for
Desc2: thrusting, which shines with a soft white light. It handles
Desc3: beautifully, and it seems to move with a will of its own.

Name: clawed gloves
Desc1: These heavy gloves are made out of stiff cloth, and they
Desc2: each have three steel claws jutting off of their backs. They
Desc3: are used by mystics to increase their hand-to-hand damage.

Name: witchwood spear
Desc1: This spear is crafted from a magically-grown hardwood, which
Desc2: when cut from the living tree, can be crafted into high
Desc3: quality magical weapons. This long spear is inlaid with
Desc4: silvery runes, and its foot-long bladed head narrows to a
Desc5: razor-sharp point.

Name: jeweled scimitar
Desc1: This elaborately-worked scimitar is made of the finest
Desc2: high steel, and is worked with many exquisite gems. Its
Desc3: hand guard is delicately worked to portray a snake biting
Desc4: its own tail.

Name: brass key
Desc1: This shiny brass key has the image of a burning flame on its
Desc2: handle.

Name: glowing broadsword
Desc1: This beautifully-crafted broadsword is honed to a razor-
Desc2: sharp edge. Silvery runes etched along its blade glow
Desc3: softly.

Name: runed chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This steel-link chainmail vest is reinforced with thin
Desc2: metal plates. It is of exquisite craftsmanship, and the
Desc3: runes engraved in its surface seem to glitter in the light.

Name: steel nunchaku
Desc1: This small flail is made up of two steel rods joined
Desc2: together by a short iron chain.

Name: ninjato
Desc1: This finely-crafted steel blade is honed to a razor-sharp
Desc2: edge, and bears an ornately-designed wooden hilt.

Name: kusari gama
Desc1: This huge flail consists of a sickle on one end attached
Desc2: to a large weighted chain.

Name: black tabi
Desc1: These padded black boots resemble sandals worn overtop
Desc2: knee-length leggings. Their soles are woven in such a way so
Desc3: that the sounds of movement are muffled greatly.

Name: hooded mask
Desc1: This mask is made out of a flat black material, specially
Desc2: treated to not reflect the light. It conceals the wearer's
Desc3: head, leaving nothing but a slit to see through.

Name: black ninja robes
Desc1: These tight black robes are made out of a tough, non-
Desc2: reflective fabric. They are slightly elastic to allow
Desc3: freedom of movement, but are fitted so they do not flap or
Desc4: make any noise.

Name: emerald-hilted rapier
Desc1: This long, diamond-bladed rapier sparkles endlessly, causing
Desc2: you to fall into a slight daze. Its hilt, gleaming with
Desc3: emeralds, emits a faint green glowing aura. Examining the
Desc4: blade closer you realize that it is razor sharp and you
Desc5: notice the words "Lord Chance Nifield" engraved upon its
Desc6: pommel.

Name: tower shield
Desc1: This huge iron shield is bolted together with rivets, and
Desc2: is held onto the forearm by thick leather straps. It
Desc3: provides a virtual wall of defense against attack, but gets
Desc4: in the way of your attacks as well as the opponents. The
Desc5: incredible weight of this shield prohibits its use by weaker
Desc6: adventurers.

Name: soulsword
Desc1: This ghostly weapon flickers with charged energy from the
Desc2: astral plane. Its nature is such that it magically bonds
Desc3: with the bearer, and cannot be removed except by spells. It
Desc4: is rumoured that Soulswords will remain with the wielder
Desc5: even after death, accompanying him into the afterlife.

Name: scroll of blur
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of stinking cloud
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of mageshield
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of mute
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of dancing blades
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of vulnerability
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of fireball
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of deathtouch
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of eldritch bolt
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of senselessness
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of rapid healing
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of acid rain
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of partial petrify
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of poison cloud
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of rotting flesh
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of iron faith
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of healing rain
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of greater bless
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of glitterdust
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of holy armour
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of unholy armour
Desc1: This unholy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of cure disease
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of remove curse
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of greater healing
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of disrupt
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of major healing rain
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: scroll of godstrike
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: holy miter
Desc1: This tall, elaborately-decorated hat is worn by the upper
Desc2: levels of the clergy. It is inscribed with holy symbols of
Desc3: protection.

Name: silvery skullcap
Desc1: This thin skullcap is made of a shining silver-like metal.
Desc2: It is heavily inscribed with angular runes, glowing a faint
Desc3: blue. An emanation of power surrounds it.

Name: eagle helm
Desc1: This fine steel helm is crafted to look like an eagle's
Desc2: head. The beak is short, curved, and sharp, and the feathers
Desc3: are engraved into the surface of the helm with remarkable
Desc4: workmanship. The eagle's black eyes are of glossy stone.

Name: wolf helm
Desc1: This exquisite helm is crafted from the finest steel, and is
Desc2: light as well as strong. It is crafted in the form of a
Desc3: snarling wolf's head with the jaws wide open, giving the
Desc4: appearance that the wearer is being swallowed alive.

Name: runed cowl
Desc1: This midnight-blue hood is inscribed with spiralling silver
Desc2: glyphs. A fine silver chain attached to it is used to fasten
Desc3: it to a cloak or shirt.

Name: crested war helm
Desc1: This elaborate helmet is crafted from the lightest
Desc2: high-steel, and is designed with only one thing in mind --
Desc3: effectiveness in combat. Its visored face offers only a
Desc4: small eyeslit to see through, and small enchanted jewels
Desc5: set in the sides aid the user in combat.

Name: jade amulet
Desc1: This small, circular pendant is carved and polished from
Desc2: a deep green jade. It is inscribed with a single exotic
Desc3: rune.

Name: amethyst pendant
Desc1: This is a crudely-cut piece of amethyst in a plain iron
Desc2: setting.

Name: ethereal amulet
Desc1: This is a smoky piece of glass hung on a thin silvery chain.
Desc2: Some small, dark-coloured object is set in the centre of
Desc3: the glass, and radiates an eerie, shifting aura.

Name: holy vestements
Desc1: These elaborate white robes are decorated with gold lace and
Desc2: small precious gems. Holy symbols are woven into the hem and
Desc3: cuffs with golden thread.

Name: gilded robes
Desc1: These gorgeous robes are made out of glittering cloth of
Desc2: gold, and have golden buttons and trim. Small glowing runes
Desc3: are etched into the collar.

Name: runed robes
Desc1: These midnight-blue robes are inscribed with spiralling
Desc2: silver glyphs. Silver bands adorn the cuffs, collar and hem.
Desc3: An aura of arcane power radiates from within.

Name: wyvernhide tunic
Desc1: This thick leather tunic is made from boiled wyvern's hide.
Desc2: The dull brown scales are extremely tough, and provide
Desc3: excellent protection from attack. Wyvernhide is highly
Desc4: prized as wyverns are known for their ferocity in combat.

Name: cat's-eye pendant
Desc1: This small golden pendant is set with a chrysoberyl gem,
Desc2: commonly referred to as a cat's eye. It is worn on a thin
Desc3: gold chain, and, although quite beautiful, radiates an
Desc4: unsettling aura.

Name: gianthair vest
Desc1: This is a thick padded vest made of giant's hair. Giant hair
Desc2: is widely used in the making of ropes and is used in the
Desc3: construction of many armours, as it is tough and durable.
Desc4: A vest made of giant hair is both protective and light, and
Desc5: provides protection from the elements.

Name: red enameled scalemail
Desc1: This heavy scalemail shirt is crafted from the finest steel.
Desc2: The scales have been individually lacquered with a crimson
Desc3: substance, and are polished to a brilliant shine. It feels
Desc4: unnaturally cool to the touch.

Name: chainmail halter
Desc1: This is a chainmail halter-top, with cloth padding
Desc2: underneath. It is worn by women wishing to be fashionable as
Desc3: well as effective in combat.

Name: steel brassiere
Desc1: This is a light steel breastplate for women, padded with
Desc2: leather. It is slightly cumbersome, but provides great
Desc3: protection.

Name: fine breastplate
Desc1: This marvellously-crafted breastplate is made of the finest
Desc2: tempered steel, designed to be light and extremely strong.
Desc3: It is the armour of choice for many knights and heavy
Desc4: footmen.

Name: adamantite chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This heavy suit of chainmail armour gleams with the smooth
Desc2: darkness of the metal known as adamantite. Nearly
Desc3: indestructible and quite rare, only master smiths have the
Desc4: necessary skill to craft such works of art.

Name: shadow cloak
Desc1: This nightblack cloak is made from some strange, non-
Desc2: reflective cloth, and is smooth to the touch. It is not
Desc3: stirred by the wind or weather, but just hangs motionless.

Name: crimson cloak
Desc1: This long cloak is made of fine, brilliant red silk, and is
Desc2: embroidered with gold thread. A thick gold chain and clasp
Desc3: hold it closed at the neck. A glittering diamond in the
Desc4: clasp is engraved with a single angular rune.

Name: elven cloak
Desc1: This lightweight cloak is made of a smooth, close-knit
Desc2: cloth. It shifts and shimmers, and blends into the
Desc3: surroundings, helping the wearer avoid detection. A small
Desc4: silver clasp in the shape of a leaf holds it closed at the
Desc5: throat.

Name: adamantite bracers
Desc1: These heavy, dull grey bracers are crafted from the
Desc2: juggernaut of all metals -- adamantite. It is known for its
Desc3: massive weight and incredible durability. As with anything
Desc4: made from adamantite, these bracers are heavy and nearly
Desc5: impenetrable.

Name: serpent armbands
Desc1: This is a pair of armbands crafted to look like snakes
Desc2: entwining each arm. Their sinuous spirals are made from some
Desc3: dull green metal. Each tiny scale is picked out with
Desc4: marvellous skill, and the serpents' eyes are small rubies.

Name: crimson bracers
Desc1: These steel bracers have been lacquered a dull red. Curving
Desc2: runes engraved along their length glow a faint orange, like
Desc3: dim coals on a hearth. A small ruby is set in the centre of
Desc4: the face of each bracer.

Name: silver bracelet
Desc1: This is a simple silver link bracelet, commonly worn as
Desc2: adornment.

Name: ivory bracers
Desc1: These beautiful ivory bracers are carved with intricate
Desc2: animals, many of which you have never seen before. They
Desc3: are light and delicate, and seem well-used.

Name: fingerbone bracelet
Desc1: This is a simple leather thong strung with fingerbones from
Desc2: various races... some very familiar. The bones are carved
Desc3: with crude shamanistic runes.

Name: silk gloves
Desc1: This is a beautifully-crafted pair of silk gloves. They are
Desc2: light and protective, though somewhat costly.

Name: gauntlets of power
Desc1: These heavy plate gauntlets are made of strong black iron.
Desc2: Engraved in the centre of the back of each gauntlet is a
Desc3: glowing yellow rune.

Name: white satin gloves
Desc1: These simple white gloves are made of a soft white satin,
Desc2: stitched with golden thread. A holy symbol is embroidered
Desc3: into the back of each glove.

Name: embroidered black gauntlets
Desc1: These heavy gauntlets seem to be made of some dull black
Desc2: leather. They are stitched with heavy black thread, and
Desc3: unholy symbols are stitched on their backs.

Name: sapphire ring
Desc1: This small silver ring is set with a pale, glittering
Desc2: sapphire. The gem is as translucent as a piece of ice, and
Desc3: just as cold.

Name: mithril ring
Desc1: This small, intricate ring is made of pure mithril, and is
Desc2: carved in the shape of many intertwining bodies. Tiny
Desc3: diamonds are set for eyes, and the ring glitters brightly
Desc4: in the light. Its exquisite craftmanship means it was likely
Desc5: a dwarf lord's prized possession.

Name: opal ring
Desc1: This heavy platinum ring is set with a massive opal, carved
Desc2: by some magical means in the shape of a skull. Sinister
Desc3: runes are etched along the length of the shining band.

Name: moonstone ring
Desc1: This beautiful silvery ring is made of three intertwining
Desc2: bands. Set in the centre is a cluster of three moonstones
Desc3: which glow with a soft light.

Name: malachite ring
Desc1: This heavy malachite ring is carved in the shape of a snake
Desc2: biting its own tail. Small, fluidly-engraved runes are set
Desc3: in the inside of the ring.

Name: belt of might
Desc1: This is a plain leather belt, with a solid iron buckle
Desc2: fashioned into two clasping hands. Its ordinary appearance
Desc3: hides a potent power.

Name: fine platinum chain
Desc1: This is a long, extremely thin chain of brilliant platinum.
Desc2: Gold thread is intertwined in between the shining links.
Desc3: This type of chain is commonly worn wrapped about the waist
Desc4: by wealthy women.

Name: silk trousers
Desc1: This is a pair of brilliant silk pants, of excellent
Desc2: workmanship. They are light and loose, and tight around the
Desc3: ankles and waist.

Name: leather skirt
Desc1: This is a soft leather skirt, coming down to just above the
Desc2: knees. It is comfortable and flexible, and has a slit up the
Desc3: side for ease of movement.

Name: silvery chain leggings
Desc1: These brilliant leggings are crafted from some silvery metal
Desc2: chain mesh. A band of disks about the waist is etched with
Desc3: a series of strange letters in some foreign tongue.

Name: black plate leggings
Desc1: These crude iron plates are inscribed with harsh, sprawling
Desc2: runes, and are heavily nicked and scratched. However, they
Desc3: are surprisingly light for their apparent size.

Name: dwarven work boots
Desc1: These heavy leather boots are reinforced with steel bands,
Desc2: and have heavy metal caps on the toes. They are of sturdy
Desc3: dwarven manufacture, meant for durability and toughness --
Desc4: ugly, but effective.

Name: elven boots
Desc1: These well-made boots are crafted from some soft, but
Desc2: extremely durable leather. They come up past the knee, and
Desc3: are normally folded over at the tops. Such boots are said to
Desc4: aid a person in the arts of stalking.

Name: winged sandals
Desc1: These silvery sandals are adorned with a small pair of
Desc2: feathery white wings on each heel.

Name: snakeskin boots
Desc1: This is a pair of glittering black snakeskin boots. The
Desc2: scales are sharp and opalescent, and gleam like oil in the
Desc3: light.

Name: mirrored shield
Desc1: This is a perfectly round shield of steel. Its face has been
Desc2: polished to a literally mirrorlike shine, and its
Desc3: reflection is dazzling.

Name: heavy bone mace
Desc1: This massive mace is seemingly carved from the legbone of
Desc2: some huge animal. Its head is knobbed and is covered in
Desc3: wicked-looking protrusions.

Name: starsteel greatsword
Desc1: This huge two-handed sword is crafted from some glittering,
Desc2: silvery metal. The light refracts off of it in rainbows, its
Desc3: perfect surface reflecting like a mirror. Its elegant hilt
Desc4: is bound in black leather. The pommel is adorned with a
Desc5: softly glowing diamond the size of a bull's eye, and
Desc6: sinuous patterns are etched into the double crossguards.

Name: dwarven-craft hammer
Desc1: This heavy, two-handed hammer is imbued with powerful
Desc2: striking magics. It is used by the elite dwarven smiths to
Desc3: craft the most precious of metals -- mithril. These hammers
Desc4: are the only things that have the power to craft mithril,
Desc5: and consequently make incredible weapons in battle; however,
Desc6: they are lacking greatly in accuracy.

Name: trident
Desc1: This is a heavy, two-handed weapon much like a spear. Its
Desc2: shaft is crafted from a durable hardwood, and its triple-
Desc3: pronged head of high steel. The tip-heavy construction of
Desc4: the trident makes it a somewhat clumsy weapon if one is not
Desc5: used to it, but it is effective nonetheless.

Name: warpblade
Desc1: The blade of this strange weapon seems to fade in and out
Desc2: of existence -- one minute a solid grey length, the next as
Desc3: insubstantial as smoke. Odd sigils are etched up and down
Desc4: the length of the blade, and golden threads are worked into
Desc5: the normal-seeming steel hilt.

Name: hell-flail
Desc1: This massive, three-headed flail is made of some heavy,
Desc2: soot-coloured metal. It reeks of brimstone and charred
Desc3: flesh. Evil-looking runes glow like the fires of hell on the
Desc4: brutally-spiked head.

Name: thunderstaff
Desc1: This slender, silvery staff crackles with power. Lightning
Desc2: flickers up and down its length, and magical runes are
Desc3: engraved in jagged patterns all over it.

Name: frost sceptre
Desc1: This heavy glass sceptre feels as cold as ice. Its broad,
Desc2: flat head is engraved with a single, brightly glowing rune.
Desc3: The handle is wrapped in white leather, and a thong hangs
Desc4: from the pommel.

Name: serpent scourge
Desc1: This vicious-looking weapon consists of a cluster of long
Desc2: lashes attached to an iron handle. Each four-foot leather
Desc3: lash is painted green and is fitted with a wicked iron tip
Desc4: crafted in the likeness of a snake's head. A small green
Desc5: emerald set in the pommel glows malevolently.

Name: black scimitar
Desc1: This wicked-looking blade is heavily serrated. It is heavy
Desc2: and unwieldy, but would do great damage to unarmoured
Desc3: opponents.

Name: oaken staff
Desc1: This heavy oaken staff appears to be carved with strange
Desc2: druidic runes and symbols. It is extremely hard and sturdy.

Name: golden sickle
Desc1: This foot-long sickle is wickedly curved, and gleams
Desc2: brightly in the light. Its golden surface is engraved with
Desc3: images of trailing ivy and mistletoe. The razor-sharp edge
Desc4: of its blade glitters unnaturally.

Name: bladed staff
Desc1: This exotic weapon consists of a four-foot shaft of hardwood
Desc2: with two long, curved iron blades mounted on the ends. It
Desc3: appears unwieldy but is in fact a deadly and effective
Desc4: weapon when used in the right hands.

Name: heavy black rod
Desc1: This three-foot-long rod flickers from light grey, to
Desc2: charcoal, to night black, then back to grey again in an
Desc3: endless cycle of shifting shades. It is completely unmarked
Desc4: and is as smooth as glass.

Name: crystal spear
Desc1: This is a four-foot-long spear made out of some glittering,
Desc2: faceted crystal. It is extremely sharp, and its surface from
Desc3: the head down has been smoothed and carved to provide better
Desc4: grip.

Name: blue potion
Desc1: This is a small glass vial, filled with a thick, dark blue
Desc2: liquid. An eye is burned into the cork.

Name: turquoise potion
Desc1: This is a crystal bottle, filled with a pale turquoise
Desc2: elixir. It is stoppered with a steel plug, which has a
Desc3: symbol of a drop imprinted on it.

Name: green potion
