Desc1: This is a small steel-banded glass bottle, filled with a
Desc2: dull-coloured green liquid. The stopper is branded with a
Desc3: small symbol in the shape of a crescent moon.

Name: yellow potion
Desc1: This is a glass vial filled with a thin, bright yellow
Desc2: liquid. Stamped into the cork is a small symbol of a sun.

Name: frothing pink potion
Desc1: This fragile glass vial is filled with a pale pink elixir.
Desc2: The liquid is bubbling and churning up white foam. Three
Desc3: lines are stamped into the cork.

Name: silvery potion
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with a glittering silver
Desc2: liquid. Engraved upon the steel stopper is a small cross.

Name: orange potion
Desc1: This is a large glass flask, the bottom half of which is
Desc2: wrapped in a leather covering. A thick orange liquid sloshes
Desc3: about within. Upon the stopper is carved a clenched fist.

Name: white potion
Desc1: This thick crystal bottle is filled with a thin white
Desc2: liquid with the consistency of milk. A strange rune is
Desc3: carved into the stopper.

Name: black orb
Desc1: This fist-sized orb is engraved with swirling lines and
Desc2: designs. Spaced evenly about the orb are six different
Desc3: runes, carved deeply into its surface.

Name: belt of faith
Desc1: Crafted from a mix of mithril and adamantite, this belt is
Desc2: a symbol of protection. A platinum circle adorned with a
Desc3: diamond, a ruby, and an onyx sits as the buckle. Inscripted
Desc4: upon it are the words "Protection of faith." It is very
Desc5: finely made and gives off an aura of power.

Name: darkwood ring
Desc1: This polished black ring is made out of the wood of the
Desc2: sturdy darkwood tree, which is known for its iron-like
Desc3: strength. The ring is carved with elaborate sigils and
Desc4: runes, and it radiates a faint warmth.

Name: green metal key
Desc1: This large, heavy key is made of some rough green metal. Its
Desc2: many teeth jut out at strange angles. The key's head is
Desc3: crafted in the shape of a serpent's head.

Name: large iron key
Desc1: This massive iron key is quite crudely made. Its solid
Desc2: construction makes it fairly invulnerable to damage,
Desc3: however.

Name: tree trunk
Desc1: A large tree that has been ripped from the ground, only
Desc2: someone with extreme strength could imagine wielding it.
Desc3: Large handprints have shrunk one side of it, forming a
Desc4: handle of sorts. It could easily cause great damage to any
Desc5: unlucky enough to meet its bark.

Name: cyclops eye
Desc1: This huge eyeball is about two feet in diameter, and glows
Desc2: with a greenish hue. It is fairly heavy and cumbersome.

Name: greater red dragon scale
Desc1: This huge reddish scale is larger than a tower shield and
Desc2: as solid as iron. It is incredibly light for its size,
Desc3: though, which is fortunate since otherwise it would be
Desc4: impossible to lift.

Name: spider silk
Desc1: This is a coil of shimmering, silky thread, smooth and cool
Desc2: to the touch.

Name: crystal sword
Desc1: This is a light two-handed sword, made out of some
Desc2: glittering multifaceted crystal. Its edges are sharpened to
Desc3: the point where they could cut a hair.

Name: crystal club
Desc1: This large, heavy club is made out of a glittering,
Desc2: multifaceted crystal.

Name: rolled parchment
Desc1: To chieftain Ss'keth'an -- Affairs are proceeding as
Desc2: planned. You shall be well rewarded for your defense of the
Desc3: crystal pass. We have many slaves that would suit your needs
Desc4: admirably. Remember, it is VITAL that no one passes through
Desc5: the crystal tunnel. See that none do. You know what swift
Desc6: vengeance would be exacted otherwise.  -- Lord Cambron

Name: large broken tree
Desc1: This twisted black tree juts out over the edge of the chasm
Desc2: here. Upon closer inspection, you notice a path hidden by
Desc3: bushes surrounding the base of the tree. The path leads down
Desc4: onto a concealed ledge, where a pair of stairs lead down the
Desc5: face of the cliff!

Name: greater hellhound hide
Desc1: This is the thick, heavy hide of a greater hellhound. Its
Desc2: black fur is dry and straight, and reeks of brimstone.

Name: magma amulet
Desc1: This dully-glowing pendant is made of grey iron. Set in the
Desc2: centre of its face is a smooth red stone, and it hangs upon
Desc3: a braid of thick black hair.

Name: large boulder
Desc1: This massive stone is charred and heavily gouged by some
Desc2: huge clawed animal. However, at your touch it moves
Desc3: slightly, and you think that it may be possible to turn it!

Name: Kher grass
Desc1: This is a bundle of black, unclean-looking weeds. It smells
Desc2: sour, and is almost greasy.

Name: cross key
Desc1: This heavy gold key's handle is shaped like an X. The barrel
Desc2: and teeth are smooth and shiny.

Name: runed key
Desc1: This small red key is inscribed with glittering black runes.
Desc2: It is very heavy for its size, and seems to glow warmly when
Desc3: you hold it.

Name: skull key
Desc1: This large, light key is made of polished ivory. Its many
Desc2: teeth are sharp, and its handle is carved in the form of a
Desc3: grinning skull.

Name: skull sword
Desc1: This huge, one-handed sword is crafted out of some dark
Desc2: metal. Its blade is serrated and razor-sharp, and is
Desc3: engraved with skulls along its length. Its long bone handle
Desc4: is as strong as iron, and appears to be the legbone of some
Desc5: creature. A small skull is set in the pommel.

Name: glowing red amulet
Desc1: This heavy iron amulet is surrounded by a dull red glow. It
Desc2: is inset with rubies and is carved in the shape of a black
Desc3: sun. It hangs upon a fine chain of black metal, and seems
Desc4: warm to the touch.

Name: gleaming steel device
Desc1: This shiny metal contraption is smooth and seamless. Its
Desc2: myriad parts fit together bewilderingly, so that you do not
Desc3: know where one part begins and the next ends. You have never
Desc4: seen anything like it. Its tall, pillar-like shape is broken
Desc5: by three dark slots spaced evenly about its surface. A faint
Desc6: hum comes from within, and it is slightly warm to the touch.

Name: dark temple key
Desc1: This heavy obsidian key is smooth and warm to the touch. Its
Desc2: head is crafted in the shape of a horned skull, with glowing
Desc3: rubies for eyes. The skull seems to grin at you maliciously,
Desc4: and you get a feeling of disease while this is near you.

Name: katana
Desc1: This is a light one-handed sword. It is about three and a
Desc2: half feet long, midway in size between a broadsword and a
Desc3: greatsword. Its slightly curved blade is razor-sharp, and
Desc4: the sword is apparently made by a master craftsman. Its
Desc5: black hilt is carved in the shape of a rearing panther.

Name: black plate corselet
Desc1: This is a heavy platemail corselet, made of black iron.
Desc2: Underneath is a black chainmail shirt of the same material.
Desc3: It is extremely heavy, but is massive and will provide
Desc4: excellent protection from attack. Glowing red runes glitter
Desc5: over its entire surface, and appear to crawl and move when
Desc6: you're not looking directly at them.

Name: golden chalice
Desc1: This large, heavy goblet is encrusted with jewels, and is
Desc2: exquisitely carved with flocks of angels. A holy prayer is
Desc3: inscribed in flowing letters about its base.

Name: hideous altar
Desc1: This massive altar is crafted out of red stone, in the shape
Desc2: of a horned skull. Its features are picked out with
Desc3: exquisite skill, its open mouth filled with needle-sharp
Desc4: teeth. Its huge eye sockets gaze at you hollowly.

Name: scroll of shadowform
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of ice storm
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of chaos storm
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: multicoloured sash
Desc1: This is a six-foot-long, rainbow-coloured silken sash, worn
Desc2: about the waist. Its brilliant patterns are the result of
Desc3: a cunning dye process. Sewn into the edges are runes of
Desc4: a mithril thread so thin that it is almost invisible.

Name: iron tube
Desc1: This is a strange contraption indeed. It consists of a
Desc2: wooden handle, which is attached to an iron sphere, which
Desc3: in turn is affixed to the end of a two-foot-long iron tube.
Desc4: A metal stud is affixed to the top of the sphere, and small
Desc5: objects can be heard rattling about inside.

Name: silver disk
Desc1: This small flat silver plate is around 5 inches in diameter.
Desc2: It is quite tarnished and worn with age, but you can make
Desc3: out the following inscription:
Desc4: Speak the answer, and you may pass.
Desc5: "Starter of wars, Purifies thoughts.
Desc6: Creates a deity, Without you are lost."

Name: shattered skeleton
Desc1: This poor adventurer appears to have missed a handhold and
Desc2: fallen to his death. Chunks of rock and dirt cover its body
Desc3: and as you look closer, you notice a large silver disk
Desc4: behind the rubble.

Name: crystal ball
Desc1: As you gaze into the crystal ball, a swirly mist dissolves
Desc2: and you witness what appears to be a a miraculous
Desc3: underground city. Upon closer inspection, you notice that
Desc4: all of its inhabitants are dwarves!

Name: silver pedestal
Desc1: This intricately-designed pedestal was most likely magically
Desc2: crafted out of pure silver. It breaks out into a three-
Desc3: pronged clasp at the top where it holds the crystal ball. On
Desc4: closer inspection, you discover that you might be able to
Desc5: to turn the crystal ball in some manner.

Name: lava-rock
Desc1: This sheet of what appears to be cooled lava is rough and
Desc2: textured with several small rocks inbedded within its
Desc3: surface. Looking closely, you discover a large opal
Desc4: stone that appears to be moveable.

Name: glowing ruby
Desc1: This is a perfect, head-sized star ruby, the likes of which
Desc2: you have never seen before. You cannot even begin to imagine
Desc3: its worth. It glows with a pulsing inner light, seeming to
Desc4: throb in time with your heartbeat. It alone is cool within
Desc5: this searing heat, and it seems to beckon to you, its
Desc6: shimmering glow a call for your touch.

Name: sabre of inquisition
Desc1: This fine blade appears to have been manufactured from
Desc2: some type of glass or crystal and then hardened using some
Desc3: chemical mixture. It looks to be very sharp and has a
Desc4: mithril hilt with a crimson flame etched on its pommel.
Desc5: Something catches your eye and you see in very tiny letters
Desc6: the words "Purify or Die" written in flowing script.

Name: small sign
Desc1: Say you want to 'buy healing' to have your damage healed.

Name: sabre
Desc1: This finely-balanced weapon has an extremely sharp blade,
Desc2: measuring two and a half feet long, and slightly curved. It
Desc3: is fairly heavy for its length, but is balanced so well that
Desc4: this makes no difference speedwise.

Name: starcharts
Desc1: Several star charts lay tossed around this room. Among them
Desc2: you see several depicting mythological beasts, and a few
Desc3: with an unreadable script written underneath. You come to
Desc4: the conclusion that they are for summoning purposes.

Name: thin grey tome
Desc1: This simple grey tome seems to sparkle with an interesting
Desc2: light, causing your eyes to be drawn to it immediately.
Desc3: On the cover, the book is titled "Tresspassers".

Name: silver spined tome
Desc1: This plain grey tome is fixated with a silver spine, which
Desc2: is fashioned to resemble several wild roses. Glancing at the
Desc3: cover, you read the topic "Magical Incantations".

Name: flat black tome
Desc1: This large black book appears to be almost fake, as it does
Desc2: not appear to have any pages. Upon closer inspection, you
Desc3: discover a switch.

Name: rune-carved staff
Desc1: This four-foot-long oaken staff is etched, rather crudely,
Desc2: with several tribal sigils and pictograms of some unknown
Desc3: culture. Several of the pictograms depict a figure holding a
Desc4: staff in battle against a large ape-like beast, under which
Desc5: is a strange, unknown script.

Name: glass key
Desc1: This two-pronged glass key emits a faint magical aura.

Name: silvery plate corselet
Desc1: This light corselet is fashioned from an extremely stong,
Desc2: glittering metal. It is elaborately engraved with swirling
Desc3: designs, highlighted in gold. The crest of the town of
Desc4: Silvermere is emblazoned on its chest, proudly displayed in
Desc5: gold and jewels.

Name: silvery crested shield
Desc1: This large, curved shield is crafted from a fine, silvery
Desc2: metal, and glitters brightly. Emblazoned on its smooth face
Desc3: is the proud symbol of the town of Silvermere.

Name: fine silvery broadsword
Desc1: This is an extremely well-crafted blade of a strong,
Desc2: brilliantly shining metal. It appears to be razor-sharp, and
Desc3: is surprisingly light for its size. Its wide blade is
Desc4: engraved with sinuous runes up half its length. The straight
Desc5: hilt and crossguards are inset with gold and small jewels.

Name: decapitated head
Desc1: The bloody head of some poor bastard stares outward with a
Desc2: dead gaze. It could be any simple commoner that met this
Desc3: horrid end. Blood is clotted and dried all over the neck
Desc4: where it was chopped from its body with some grisly weapon.

Name: altar
Desc1: This large, bloodstained altar has wide blood gutters
Desc2: leading down to a hollow at one end. In this hollow, a
Desc3: black, fist-sized gem is set. Presumably blood and the gem
Desc4: are used for some sadistic ritual -- it is clear that
Desc5: sacrifices made on this stone slab would bathe the black
Desc6: stone in blood.

Name: huge darkwood tree
Desc1: This massive, twisted darkwood tree is so huge it is wider
Desc2: than a house. Its thick branches droop down heavily, laden
Desc3: with deep green leaves. It is covered in a variety of
Desc4: odd-looking knots.

Name: pipe
Desc1: This filthy, slimy pipe reeks with a disgusting scent.
Desc2: Partially concealed just inside, however, is a two-way
Desc3: switch!

Name: eye socket
Desc1: This is a dark eye socket in the face of the carved skull.
Desc2: Hidden inside is a large stone button!

Name: songsheet of draining
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Draining.

Name: songsheet of silence
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Silence.

Name: songsheet of lethargy
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Lethargy.

Name: songsheet of dazzling
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Dazzling.

Name: songsheet of quickness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Quickness.

Name: songsheet of pain
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Pain.

Name: songsheet of stunning
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Stunning.

Name: songsheet of shockwave
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Shockwave.

Name: songsheet of heroism
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Heroism.

Name: songsheet of sonic blast
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Sonic Blast.

Name: songsheet of evasion
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Evasion.

Name: obsidian claymore
Desc1: A massive one-handed sword, it has been crafted from the
Desc2: stone of obsidian. Waves of fire erupt from the blood red
Desc3: symbols that run up the blade. The hilt is entwined with a
Desc4: strange black fabric that allows you to handle it. It hisses
Desc5: as it moves through the air, leaving a trail of flame.

Name: scroll of solid fog
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of wind of haste
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of mana storm
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of corrosion
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of meteor swarm
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of mystic mist
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of spirit horde
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of dragonfire
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of stoneskin
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of blaze
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of creeping doom
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of maelstrom
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of plasma bolt
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of plague
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of earthquake
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of earthfist
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: ninja battle armour
Desc1: This cunningly-crafted suit of armour is made from bamboo
Desc2: and a strange, thin black leather. It is very light yet
Desc3: strong, and provides ample freedom of movement with a
Desc4: maximum of protection.

Name: poisoned shuriken
Desc1: This small steel disk has four razor-sharp blades protruding
Desc2: from its edge. A dull black substance has been smeared on
Desc3: the points.

Name: smoke bomb
Desc1: This small, paper-wrapped package smells slightly of powder
Desc2: and chemicals.

Name: demon's skull mask
Desc1: This mask is the skull of something hideous. Spikey
Desc2: protrusions rim the eye sockets, adding to the thing's
Desc3: demonic visage. The mouth is frozen into a hideously evil
Desc4: grin, and its hollow black eye sockets appear to have a
Desc5: reddish glow. You get a strong feeling of fear just looking
Desc6: at the thing and have second thoughts about putting it on.

Name: grey leather-bound tome
Desc1: This huge, heavy tome is covered with swirling silvery runes
Desc2: and symbols. Inside, yellowed parchment pages are inscribed
Desc3: with spidery black letters.

Name: charred scroll
Desc1: This paper has been burned heavily and looks as though
Desc2: it could turn to ash at any moment. Written carefully upon
Desc3: the paper are fiery runes of power that dance and sway
Desc4: in a druidic dance, revealing the translation of a spell.

Name: serrated battle axe
Desc1: This is a large double-bladed axe, used in one hand. Its
Desc2: huge, serrated blades are razor-sharp, and jagged runes have
Desc3: been cut into its haft.

Name: rusty iron key
Desc1: This large, heavy key is covered in a layer of thick brown
Desc2: rust. Engraved in its handle appears to be two words in the
Desc3: old script, reading "Western Door".

Name: crowbar
Desc1: This is a two-foot long length of iron, with a point on one
Desc2: end and a hammer-like claw at the other. It is mainly used
Desc3: for prying things open or for breaking chains, though it can
Desc4: be used as a weapon in a pinch.

Name: rusted gate
Desc1: This tall, rusting ironwork gate must once have been a fine
Desc2: work of art, as its intricate spirals and curves show. Now,
Desc3: however, it is bent and cannot even fulfill its use as a
Desc4: gate, for the rust has fused it to the fence. Thick creeping
Desc5: weeds once entwined through its bars, but have since been
Desc6: cut and thrown to the side.

Name: rusty fence
Desc1: This high ironwork fence is topped by rusty, though still
Desc2: sharp, spearpoints. Its once-intricate craftmanship is now
Desc3: marred by the thick brown rust coating its surface and its
Desc4: bent bars. Creeping weeds entwined between its bars
Desc5: completely block your view past the fence.

Name: chained door
Desc1: This large wooden door is locked by a heavy iron chain,
Desc2: bolted to iron loops affixed to the warehouse's walls.
Desc3: Though on the surface the chains look unbreakable, they are
Desc4: in fact old and somewhat rusted, and with some work and the
Desc5: right tools they could be broken.

Name: western wall
Desc1: This wall is extremely clean compared to the rest of the
Desc2: sewer -- in other words, it is not outright filthy. A thin
Desc3: layer of slime and mould covers its surface, as well as an
Desc4: abnormal number of small black holes.

Name: small black holes
Desc1: Looking into some of the small black holes, you discover a
Desc2: smooth metal stud lurking within one of them!

Name: smooth metal stud
Desc1: This is a small metallic button, and it appears to be well-
Desc2: used. It moves slightly at your touch.

Name: wooden table
Desc1: This is a rather ordinary-looking wooden table, made to
Desc2: last. Its thick face and legs are heavily nicked and cut
Desc3: with use.

Name: chair
Desc1: This is a plain wooden chair, its little ornamental carving
Desc2: smoothed away by much use. Its seat is likewise smoothed,
Desc3: and its legs and back are nicked from being pushed into
Desc4: things.

Name: stove
Desc1: This fat black wood-burning stove is covered in grease and
Desc2: soot, and appears to be heavily used. It stinks of burnt
Desc3: flesh and fat.

Name: fireplace
Desc1: This large stone fireplace is covered in soot, and holds a
Desc2: bubbling cauldron full of a rank-smelling stew. The fire is
Desc3: burning some of the evil-looking weeds taken from the
Desc4: garden outside, and they give off a greasy black smoke that
Desc5: makes you gag.

Name: ancient door
Desc1: This huge ancient door is elegantly decorated with delicate
Desc2: scrollwork and stylized vines. It appears to have weathered
Desc3: the years quite well, and is nearly as strong as it was when
Desc4: it was new. A square lock gapes from its right side, though
Desc5: the key to this door must be long lost.

Name: hills
Desc1: These hills are made of a light grey rock, almost the colour
Desc2: of powdered bone, and are run through with veins of a deep
Desc3: metallic red. Their faces are sheer, sharp, and unscalable,
Desc4: and rumour tells that the red veins are actually rivulets of
Desc5: blood from adventurers who have tried to scale their
Desc6: heights.

Name: road
Desc1: This is a poorly-maintained gravel road, covered with dirt
Desc2: and debris. Black weeds occasionally poke through its
Desc3: surface. It is hard to tell whether the road is frequented
Desc4: by a few people, or traveled infrequently by many, as the
Desc5: tracks are obscured by those of what you presume to be
Desc6: animals.

Name: avalanche of jagged rubble
Desc1: This massive pile of collapsed stone appears to be
Desc2: completely impassable, as the stones are both too large and
Desc3: too sharp to handle. However, several man-sized holes can be
Desc4: seen leading inside the rubble, and although it would be
Desc5: dangerous, a few of them may be passable.

Name: displacer beast tentacle
Desc1: This is the jet-black severed tentacle of a displacer beast.
Desc2: A mass of bony spikes protrude from the end, and it looks as
Desc3: though it would make an effective weapon.

Name: manticore tail
Desc1: This huge, heavy tail is tipped with a heavy bone ball
Desc2: covered in long spikes. The spines are iron-hard and sharp
Desc3: as razors, and make this tail a deadly weapon, although its
Desc4: extreme weight doesn't allow much in the way of speed.

Name: longbow
Desc1: This slender, curved bow is made out of a long branch of
Desc2: supple wood. It is tightly strung, and has a fair amount of
Desc3: stopping power. Its pull is a little heavy, but it makes for
Desc4: a good, accurate weapon. It comes with a quiver full of
Desc5: black-feathered arrows.

Name: composite bow
Desc1: This long, fabulously-crafted bow is made of horn and light
Desc2: wood, and is pulled taut by a gut string. The strength and
Desc3: range of this bow are nearly unmatched.

Name: black serpent key
Desc1: This glossy, sinuous key depicts the form of a serpent with
Desc2: red, glinting eyes. The teeth of the key are oddly curved as
Desc3: well, and any lock this key fits must be of a completely
Desc4: different construction than any ordinary lock you've seen.

Name: piece of black chitin
Desc1: This is a large, mostly undamaged piece of a violet-black
Desc2: chitin. It is flexible, able to be bent fairly easily, but
Desc3: is also extremely strong and hard to puncture.

Name: path
Desc1: This is a narrow gravel path, threading its way through the
Desc2: confusing labyrinth of hills known as the Dragon's Teeth. It
Desc3: is somewhat difficult to keep one's bearing, as all the
Desc4: hills look nearly the same, and the sheer rocky faces are
Desc5: too tall and jagged to climb for a good look at the
Desc6: surroundings.

Name: two-headed morningstar
Desc1: This heavy weapon consists of a leather-bound oak rod about
Desc2: two feet in length, attached to a pair of ball-tipped
Desc3: chains. The metal balls are covered in blunt protrusions to
Desc4: cause more damage. A golden tassle hanging off the pommel is
Desc5: its only ornamentation.

Name: gnarled wand
Desc1: This foot-long wand seems to be made out of a blackened oak,
Desc2: its length filled with twisting convolutions. Carved in the
Desc3: side of the wand in a crude, jagged script is the word
Desc4: "Shirzak".

Name: large canvas tent
Desc1: This is a simple, but effective, heavy cloth tent. It is
Desc2: quite big, having room for about a dozen well-sized people,
Desc3: and seems to be populated by at least that many, if the
Desc4: sprawled bedrolls and miscellaneous debris are anything to
Desc5: go by.

Name: massive canvas tent
Desc1: This huge tent appears to be of relatively good make, and is
Desc2: supported in the middle by a heavy wooden pole. Apparently
Desc3: it only houses one being, as there is only one bed, the rest
Desc4: of the room being filled with odd knicknacks, large skulls
Desc5: hung on the walls, and an impressive collection of dull
Desc6: shoddy weapons.

Name: bonfire
Desc1: This huge, crackling bonfire shimmers and spits, its black
Desc2: smoke rising up into the sky. A thick hunk of meat, held by
Desc3: an iron spit, roasts over the flame, filling the air with
Desc4: its aroma.

Name: walls
Desc1: The walls of these tunnels are made of a light grey stone,
Desc2: run through with metallic veins the colour of blood. They
Desc3: are deeply gouged in places, though what could tear stone
Desc4: with such ease remains to be seen.

Name: hole
Desc1: The black hole in the ceiling here is too high to reach, and
Desc2: appears to lead upwards at a steep slant.

Name: hole
Desc1: This four-foot-wide hole appears to have been roughly carved
Desc2: out with some extremely-sharp digging instrument... or
Desc3: perhaps, claws.

Name: small hole
Desc1: This dark hole is about four feet across, and appears to
Desc2: lead down into the depths of the hill.

Name: green bubbling pool
Desc1: This wide, bubbling pool smells light and sweet, like the
Desc2: scent of flowers on a breeze. It is illuminated by a
Desc3: soothing green glow that comes from within. The shore of the
Desc4: pool does not seem treacherous, and it would be easy to drin
Desc5: straight from the pool, or to fill up a container with its
Desc6: liquid.

Name: crystal flask
Desc1: This crystal bottle is quite well crafted, and would hold a
Desc2: few mouthfuls of liquid.

Name: glowing crystal flask
Desc1: This small crystal bottle is filled with some sort of slowly
Desc2: bubbling green liquid.

Name: flaming scimitar
Desc1: This metal of alien origin projects an intense, magical
Desc2: flame. The curved blade sprouts from an obsidian hilt, which
Desc3: is strangely cool to touch. A single ruby set in the pommel

Name: silvery longbow
Desc1: This beautifully-made longbow appears to be made of
Desc2: glimmering Silverwood, a sure sign of Elven origin. It has
Desc3: elegant, sinuous runes carved into its length, and although
Desc4: it is tightly strung, it is remarkably easy to draw. A
Desc5: silver-laced quiver of white leather is full of black-
Desc6: feathered arrows, their points sharp as razors.

Name: golden snake earrings
Desc1: This pair of small golden earrings is crafted in the shape
Desc2: of sinuous serpents biting their own tails, thus forming
Desc3: hoops. Their eyes glitter with tiny emeralds, and the scales
Desc4: seem to have been carefully crafted one by one.

Name: curved black dagger
Desc1: This large, thin-bladed dagger is extraordinarily heavy for
Desc2: its size, and is nearly as long as a shortsword. Its blade
Desc3: is heavily carved with softly glowing red runes, and there
Desc4: is a decidedly evil aura surrounding it.

Name: pile of digested bodies
Desc1: This is probably the most disgusting sight you have ever
Desc2: seen. A dozen or so bodies have been partially eaten away by
Desc3: the milky-white fluid which covers them, and pale white eggs
Desc4: embedded in their flesh lay broken and oozing. It is
Desc5: impossible to distinguish what race each body is, as they
Desc6: have been mutilated beyond recognition.

Name: partially digested body
Desc1: This is the body of a creature of unknown race, its skin
Desc2: melted away, a milky fluid covering it. Its flesh is
Desc3: embedded with pale, oval-shaped eggs the colour of maggots,
Desc4: though they have all been broken and ooze liquid. It is
Desc5: impossible to determine who, or what, the body once was.

Name: violet organic walls
Desc1: These strange-looking walls are made of a hard, sticky,
Desc2: violet substance that smells faintly sweet. They are formed
Desc3: in organic patterns, with swirling rounded designs. Although
Desc4: they are interesting to look at, they are also extremely
Desc5: alien, and somewhat disturbing.

Name: partially concealed hole
Desc1: This large hole is somewhat hidden by a number of tentacle-
Desc2: like organs forming a crude door. The pulse and move as you
Desc3: watch them. The hole is easily wide enough to allow entry.

Name: black mountains
Desc1: The stone of these mountains is coal black and as sharp as
Desc2: flint. It is shot through with thin metallic red veins,
Desc3: which reflect the light with crimson sparkles. This mountain
Desc4: range is known to be practically unscalable, and is nearly
Desc5: devoid of plant life. Very few creatures can survive in such
Desc6: harshness, and those that do are deadly.

Name: crevice trail
Desc1: This is a narrow rocky trail passing along the bottom of a
Desc2: natural crevice in the mountain. Occasionally there is a
Desc3: small, but unfathomably deep crack to leap over, and often
Desc4: the trail is nearly blocked by fallen rocks and rubble.
Desc5: There is evidence of tracks of some sort, though the rocky
Desc6: terrain makes them unidentifiable.

Name: thick brown vines
Desc1: These heavy, almost-leathery vines vary in thickness from
Desc2: one inch to almost four. They appear quite strong, and could
Desc3: possibly bear the weight of someone climbing upon them.

Name: filthy nests
Desc1: These nests are extremely disgusting and dirty, being filled
Desc2: with rotting meat, debris, and various worthless odds and
Desc3: ends. Bits of bone and leather are scattered about, as well
Desc4: as broken pieces of weapons and armour.

Name: severed head of Markus
Desc1: This is the gruesome, bloody head of Commander Markus of the
Desc2: Western Garrison. His once-proud eyes are now glazed and
Desc3: lifeless, and his once-dark skin is now pale and clammy. His
Desc4: swollen tongue lolls grotesquely out of his mouth.

Name: locked wooden box
Desc1: This small, heavy, rectangular box appears to be made of
Desc2: polished darkwood. Its corners are capped with shining iron,
Desc3: and it has a heavy lock on it.

Name: crossbow
Desc1: This powerful weapon is comprised of a small, but extremely
Desc2: powerful, metal bow affixed to a two-foot-long wooden stock.
Desc3: The bow is extremely difficult to cock, making this a slow
Desc4: weapon, but its steel-tipped bolts can pierce through
Desc5: armour with ease. It comes with a quiver full of short,
Desc6: sharp bolts.

Name: heavy crossbow
Desc1: This is a more powerful version of the standard crossbow.
Desc2: Its bow is very tightly strung, and requires much strength
Desc3: to re-cock, making it very slow to fire. Nonetheless, it is
Desc4: extremely accurate, and armour is nearly useless against its
Desc5: heavy bolts. It comes with a quiver full of the small,
Desc6: weighty, steel-tipped bolts it requires.

Name: sling
Desc1: This is a simple leather thong, with a pouch affixed to its
Desc2: middle. To use, a stone is placed within the pouch, then the
Desc3: sling is whirled about at great speeds. When one end of the
Desc4: sling is released, the stone flies at the target. It comes
Desc5: with a pouch full of smooth, round stones.

Name: staff-sling
Desc1: This weapon looks like a shortish wooden staff, with a
Desc2: leather sling affixed to the end. It is able to throw stones
Desc3: faster and further than a normal sling, but it is slower to
Desc4: use and it requires two hands. It comes with a pouch full of
Desc5: stones.

Name: grey rolled parchment
Desc1: This thin piece of parchment is covered in spidery letters.
Desc2: After scanning the document, you discover it is instructions
Desc3: on the learning and casting of a spell named Frenzy!

Name: tattered scroll
Desc1: This long, ripped scroll is covered by row upon row of
Desc2: thin, evenly-spaced handwriting, describing the methods of
Desc3: learning and casting a spell named Mass Frenzy! This spell
Desc4: duplicates the effects of the Frenzy spell, but is cast upon
Desc5: oneself and one's allies.

Name: holy writ
Desc1: This thin manual describes the ways of properly praying to
Desc2: one's deity in order to be filled with righteous power! This
Desc3: Righteousness gives the target an increase in combat power,
Desc4: coupled with a small healing of one's wounds over time.

Name: skin-covered book
Desc1: In this unholy manual, you uncover the evil, secret
Desc2: techniques of the blood ritual! This Blood Ritual allows the
Desc3: recipient to be filled with a minute power of the Blood God,
Desc4: giving an increase in combat power along with a small amount
Desc5: of healing over time. This spell is powered by the pain and
Desc6: suffering of others, and is needless to say quite evil.

Name: barkskin scroll
Desc1: This thick, weathered bark scroll is inscribed with many
Desc2: passages written in a bold, flowing hand. Upon scanning its
Desc3: contents, you discover that it contains the secret methods
Desc4: of learning and casting the Regeneration spell! This
Desc5: powerful but short-lived spell rapidly heals the target's
Desc6: wounds.

Name: double crossbow
Desc1: This strange contraption appears to be a heavy crossbow with
Desc2: two bows, one on top of the stock, the other on the bottom!
Desc3: The bolts are held in an ingenious auto-reloading magazine,
Desc4: which must be reloaded every so often. Cocking both bows and
Desc5: reloading the magazine makes re-arming this weapon fairly
Desc6: slow, but the firing of it is quick as lightning.

Name: rapier
Desc1: This excellent weapon has a three-foot length of thin
Desc2: sharpened steel, designed for thrusting and lunging. It is
Desc3: marvellously balanced, and greatly improves defense as it is
Desc4: so quick to maneuver.

Name: main-gauche
Desc1: This off-handed dagger is designed for parrying, and is used
Desc2: in conjunction with another weapon such as a rapier. It is
Desc3: finely made from the best steel.

Name: serpentine sword
Desc1: This disturbing-looking weapon has a three-foot razor-sharp
Desc2: blade, wavy like the name suggests. Its black hilt is
Desc3: adorned with a single tiny emerald in the pommel.

Name: serpentine dagger
Desc1: This long, wavy-bladed dagger is nearly as big as a
Desc2: shortsword. Its edge is honed to be razor-sharp, and its
Desc3: black hilt is adorned with a single tiny emerald.

Name: barbed whip
Desc1: This long, heavy whip is made of thick leather strands
Desc2: intertwined with thin metal wires. Along the length of the
Desc3: whip are hooked metal barbs, and a large cluster of these
Desc4: is affixed to the tip of the whip.

Name: black chitin helm
Desc1: This exotic-looking helm is quite beautiful in an alien sort
Desc2: of way. It seems to be made of a deep violet-black insect
Desc3: carapace, and has been crafted to resemble the head of one
Desc4: of these insects, complete with antennae and glossy black
Desc5: eyes on the forehead of the helm. It is extraordinarily
Desc6: strong for its weight.

Name: black chitin armour
Desc1: This exotic-looking armour seems to be made out of glossy,
Desc2: violet-black plates of insect carapace. It has been crafted
Desc3: in such a way as to maximize protection given, and has been
Desc4: treated with some special formula and bonded with spider
Desc5: silk to increase strength. It is indeed incredibly hard and
Desc6: strong for its weight.

Name: black chitin leggings
Desc1: These exotic-looking leggings seem to have been made out of
Desc2: glossy, violet-black plates of insect chitin. They have been
Desc3: bonded together with spider silk and treated with a secret
Desc4: formula which makes them extremely hard and glossy.

Name: black chitin shield
Desc1: This exotic-looking shield seems to have been crafted from
Desc2: three large, interlocking plates of violet-black insect
Desc3: chitin. They have been bonded together with spider silk, and
Desc4: treated with a secret formula, rendering them extremely
Desc5: hard. The shield is very light for its size, and would
Desc6: provide excellent protection.

Name: white gold ring
Desc1: This elegantly-crafted band is made of three intertwined
Desc2: loops of the finest pale gold. Small diamonds set around its
Desc3: perimeter glitter brightly, and a prayer is engraved in
Desc4: small letters inside the band.

Name: pewter door
Desc1: These massive pewter doors are beautifully carved with all
Desc2: manner of wild beast, including a good many who obviously
Desc3: are not from this land. They must be enchanted as they open
Desc4: with ease, despite their obvious weight.

Name: throne
Desc1: This large, heavy throne is carved out of adamantite. Its
Desc2: two arms are made to look like serpents, with their tails
Desc3: stretching back and entwining intricately to form the back
Desc4: and seat. The serpent on the left is black, while the one on
Desc5: the right is white. Somehow you get an impression of great
Desc6: power emanating from it.

Name: black and white serpent ring
Desc1: This intricate ring is crafted out of coloured adamantite,
Desc2: and is made to look like two intertwined snakes, each biting
Desc3: the other's tail. Each tiny scale is picked out in perfect
Desc4: detail, and each small eye is a round, glittering grey
Desc5: crystal.

Name: Magebane sword
Desc1: This long, wickedly-sharp sword is crafted from the finest
Desc2: steel possible. It is named the Magebane for its edge, which
Desc3: is covered in many small serrated points. The combination of
Desc4: the sharpness and these tiny barbs cause painful, jagged
Desc5: wounds in the target, disrupting concentration (and thus
Desc6: spellcasting).

Name: lockpicks
Desc1: This small pouch is filled with all the necessary tools and
Desc2: picks to aid one in unlocking tricky doors.

Name: thief's kit
Desc1: This small box contains a full set of lockpicks, as well as
Desc2: other assorted tools that aid in not only picking locks, but
Desc3: also disarming traps.

Name: pewter tankard
Desc1: This is a heavy pewter tankard, dented from extreme use in
Desc2: bar brawls. Traces of vomit can be seen within.

Name: dead cat
Desc1: This is a stiff, stinking, dead cat. It once used to be a
Desc2: cute little fluffy creature, but now it's dead!

Name: ruby-eyed skull ring
Desc1: This shining black ring seems to be made out of an unknown
Desc2: dark, glittering metal, and is extremely cold to the touch.
Desc3: A tiny, perfect dark skull is affixed to it, its eyes
Desc4: burning with an unnatural red flame. The ring has a
Desc5: noticeable aura of evil surrounding it, as well as one of
Desc6: extreme suffering.

Name: massive black doors
Desc1: These huge, ominous doors are crafted from jet-black stone,
Desc2: and tower a good twenty feet above you. They are simple and
Desc3: unornamented, and their only significant feature is the
Desc4: smaller, locked entrance door providing a way through.

Name: alleyway
Desc1: This narrow, unlit alley is filled with trash and other
Desc2: unbecoming articles. It stinks heavily of rot and offal,
Desc3: and rats scurry away as you look.

Name: street
Desc1: This wide, flagstoned street is in a moderate state of
Desc2: disrepair. Trash is scattered haphazardly about the streets,
Desc3: and it is obvious that attention to cleanliness is not one
Desc4: of the priorities here. The tall, rickety buildings flanking
Desc5: the street have a decidedly seedy and unkempt look about
Desc6: them.

Name: iron sign
Desc1: A small iron plaque is riveted to the wall here, and it
Desc2: reads: "Bank of Rhudaur: Admission charge is 5 gold
Desc3: crowns, non-negotiable."

Name: smoky black talisman
Desc1: This small dark disk is hung upon a fine silver chain.
Desc2: Strange runes are inscribed upon its surface, which read:
Desc3: "Walk UP from the park fountain with me."

Name: severed head of Goru-Nezar
Desc1: This large, heavy head once belonged to the ogre-mage lord,
Desc2: Goru-Nezar. Now its lifeless eyes stare out ominously, and
Desc3: its tongue lolls out grotesquely.

Name: Dusk
Desc1: A long spear fashioned from a glittering metal, it seems to
Desc2: have a black aura about it, but you sense no evil. Marked on
Desc3: the spear is a symbol of a full moon, fashioned in dark blue
Desc4: metal. Great power radiates from the weapon, and it seems
Desc5: to dim everything around you.

Name: ebony kris
Desc1: This wavy-bladed dagger is nearly the size of a shortsword,
Desc2: and is extremely sharp. Its blade is coated with a dripping
Desc3: black ichor, which steams and foams when it hits the ground.

Name: twisted bone staff
Desc1: This long, yellowed bone staff is twisted along its length
Desc2: and curls at the top like a goat's horn. Engraved upon its
Desc3: surface are runes of power.

Name: small diamond
Desc1: This tiny, glittering diamond has been well cut, and the
Desc2: light reflects from within beautifully.

Name: log raft
Desc1: This small floating platform is simply a number of small
Desc2: logs lashed together with rope. It is somewhat heavy and
Desc3: extremely cumbersome to carry.

Name: wooden skiff
Desc1: This somewhat shabbily-made boat is barely large enough for
Desc2: one person. Its pair of small oars are barely long enough
Desc3: to use and would give you splinters, but nonetheless it is
Desc4: waterworthy.

Name: marsh light
Desc1: This strangely-crafted lamp is made out of a slightly opaque
Desc2: glass. A pale, flickering green light dances within it,
Desc3: seeming to whisper odd and disturbing things. Around the
Desc4: lamp is a black iron frame, with a handle affixed to the
Desc5: top.

Name: silver river
Desc1: The Silver river is reknowned for its beauty, majesty, and
Desc2: mystery, as well as for its danger. Lurking beneath the
Desc3: glittering silvery surface, capricious and sometimes evil
Desc4: creatures wait for unsuspecting travelers. A perpetual cover
Desc5: of fine white mist muffles the sounds here and prevents
Desc6: seeing very far.

Name: silvermere wall
Desc1: The massive town wall of Silvermere once was used to keep
Desc2: out waves of invaders, and now serves a somewhat similar
Desc3: purpose -- warding off maligned creatures in the wild. There
Desc4: appears no place to land a boat along the base of the wall,
Desc5: as its sheer face descends right into the river.

Name: dark forest
Desc1: The forbidding forest north of Silvermere is an even more
Desc2: ominous cousin of the eastern Darkwood forest. Its trees are
Desc3: packed tightly together, as if suspiciously and consciously
Desc4: forming a wall to keep out intruders. A sense of ancient
Desc5: watchfulness pervades the air surrounding this oldest of
Desc6: woods, and there appears to be no place to land at its foot.

Name: long bridge
Desc1: This long, arching bridge spans the Silver river, connecting
Desc2: Silvermere to the fenced-in graveyard. It is of ancient
Desc3: make, and excellent quality -- although it appears overly
Desc4: slender for a bridge of its length, its strength is
Desc5: surprising. The river passes swiftly beneath it, and it is
Desc6: raised up high enough that it is not possible to climb up.

Name: rocky waterfall
Desc1: Here the Silver river cascades down a rocky face inside the
Desc2: cave, crashing down into a dark, frothing pool with a
Desc3: thundrous roar. Up the side of the waterfall, a crudely-hewn
Desc4: stair can be seen leading up into the darkness, presumably
Desc5: to the top of the waterfall.

Name: dark brown walls of stone
Desc1: These smoothed, naturally-carved walls are of a deep brown
Desc2: earthy stone, mixed with the occasional darker mineral vein.
Desc3: A pale green fungus or lichen covers many parts of the walls
Desc4: here, and gives off a faintly acrid odour.

Name: pale green lichen
Desc1: This tough, acrid-smelling lichen looks quite unappetizing.
Desc2: Bits of dirt and moisture can be seen trapped within it.

Name: elevated rocky ledge
Desc1: It is hard to tell whether or not this stone ledge is
Desc2: natural or has been crafted, as its shape appears normal but
Desc3: has an unnatural symmetry to it. A few small "steps" lead
Desc4: up to it from the cavern floor, and end in front of the
Desc5: carved wall face.

Name: carved wall face with design
Desc1: This smooth stone wall has been carved with the image of
Desc2: a dancing demon, seemingly capering with glee. The carving
Desc3: is about two feet in height, and is well-detailed. Even the
Desc4: eyes, although they are stone, seem to glare at you evilly,
Desc5: such was the skill of the craftsman!

Name: black cauldron
Desc1: This massive black cauldron is large enough to hold an
Desc2: entire person, and from the looks of it, has indeed been
Desc3: used for such a purpose. Vile slime coats the inside of the
Desc4: cauldron, and it reeks of evilness.

Name: skull wand
Desc1: This thick-hafted wand is more like a rod, in that it is
Desc2: short, about two feet long, and thick as a pole. It is
Desc3: crafted from some dark, polished wood, and is tipped with
Desc4: a gleaming silver skull. Runes carved into the length of the
Desc5: wand glow with a dull, fiery red.

Name: manastone
Desc1: This is a cool blue stone of unknown origin, and it pulsates
Desc2: brightly and appears to have some great magical power held
Desc3: within its core. A chain of gold is attached to the stone
Desc4: for wearing around one's neck.

Name: ancient statues
Desc1: These huge, weatherbeaten statues must have been carved some
Desc2: thousands of years ago, judging from their unfamiliar style
Desc3: of workmanship and the degree of decay. They appear to be
Desc4: warrior-kings, each holding up a palm in greeting... or
Desc5: possibly warning. You think you can see a hint of sadness
Desc6: etched into the statues' ancient, scarred faces.

Name: huge stone
Desc1: This gigantic stone almost looks like a giant tortoise. It
Desc2: sits off to the north of the river, its rocky foundation
Desc3: forcing the river's path to the south.

Name: huge fallen tree
Desc1: This massive tree appears somewhat bent and twisted, and is
Desc2: scorched all down one side, presumably by lightning. It is
Desc3: stuck in some rocks in the centre of the river, and careful
Desc4: navigation is required to get around it.

Name: silvery stream
Desc1: This rapidly-flowing stream is an offshoot of the Silver
Desc2: River. It threads its way along the bottom of a wide crack
Desc3: in the Dragon's Teeth hills. The stony walls loom high above
Desc4: you, and occasionally a stone falls with a loud splash into
Desc5: the waters near you.

Name: silvery pool
Desc1: This large pool is fed from a small tributary of the Silver
Desc2: River. It must drain down into the earth somewhere, as the
Desc3: water does not rise despite the constant influx of water.

Name: darkened ironwood forest
Desc1: The trees of this forest are huge, towering skywards, their
Desc2: tops unseen far above. Their bark is of a strange dull
Desc3: metallic grey, the colour of iron. An aura of watchfulness
Desc4: pervades this area, and while it is not overtly hostile,
Desc5: you get the distinct impression you are not welcome here.

Name: wavy-bladed dagger
Desc1: This long dagger is practically a shortsword in length. Its
Desc2: wavy blade is a jet black, and its hilt is of polished black
Desc3: iron.

Name: shillelagh
Desc1: This gnarled wooden club is inlaid with brightly glittering
Desc2: gold. It emanates a strange magical aura.

Name: huge tree
Desc1: This massive ironwood tree could not be encircled by any
Desc2: less than thirty people with their arms outstretched. Its
Desc3: many branches would make it easy to climb up into, though
Desc4: to reach any heights would be tiring.

Name: golden honeycomb
Desc1: This large, delectable honeycomb drips with the glittering
Desc2: golden honey of the killer bees.

Name: bushes
Desc1: This strange hedge seems to have been cultivated by someone.
Desc2: Peering closer, an opening of some kind can be seen beneath
Desc3: it!

Name: bright red plant
Desc1: This strange, crimson plant has many long sinuous branches,
Desc2: and thick reddish roots which climb up the walls. Its five-
Desc3: pointed leaves are of a shining golden colour, and it
Desc4: evidently bears fruit as some are shriveled on the ground
Desc5: beside it.

Name: small green fruit
Desc1: These bite-sized fruits are a pale green in colour, and
Desc2: are banded with black stripes. They have a faintly sweet
Desc3: smell.

Name: huge broken willow
Desc1: This massive, ruined willow tree stands by the water. A
Desc2: wide crack in its side appears to lead within it!

Name: woodland robes
Desc1: These forest-green robes are adorned with black and grey
Desc2: stitching, depicting several different woodland creatures.
Desc3: The robes are of a fine, almost silky fabric, and feel warm
Desc4: to the touch. A palpable aura of power emanates from them.

Name: pearl ring
Desc1: This elaborately-carved platinum ring is set with a huge
Desc2: opalescent pearl. The band is made to resemble intertwined
Desc3: vines, with small leaves forming the clasps which hold the
Desc4: pearl.

Name: bronzewood forest
Desc1: The trees of this forest are quite large, towering far above
Desc2: you, but not quite as tall as the ironwood trees. Their skin
Desc3: is a dull, nonreflective bronze colour, and their leaves are
Desc4: of a glossy black. They are straighter and their bark is
Desc5: smoother than the other trees in this forest, and their
Desc6: branches are longer and carry more leaves.

Name: unicorn horn
Desc1: This three-foot-long horn is one of the most beautiful
Desc2: objects you have ever seen. Its spiraling length is a
Desc3: shining pearly white, and its tip is razor-sharp. Since the
Desc4: only way to obtain a unicorn horn is to kill one and take
Desc5: it, these horns are shunned with disgust by the good-
Desc6: hearted.

Name: copperwood forest
Desc1: The trees of this forest are not as tall as the ironwood
Desc2: trees, but they still tower far above you. Their bark is an
Desc3: almost-glossy copper colour, and their leaves are shiny and
Desc4: brown.

Name: large tree
Desc1: This massive copperwood tree could not be encircled by any
Desc2: less than twenty people with their arms outstretched. Its
Desc3: many branches would make it easy to climb up into, though
Desc4: to reach any heights would be tiring.

Name: handful of brown nuts
Desc1: These small nuts are round and hard, and smell quite
Desc2: appetizing. They have tiny black speckles around their
Desc3: width.

Name: strange mushrooms
Desc1: These odd-looking mushrooms seem to have been coated with a
Desc2: glittering dust of some sort.

Name: witchwood breastplate
Desc1: This odd breastplate is crafted out of a magical, living
Desc2: wood. It is engraved with sorcerous runes which shift and
Desc3: change as you watch. The breastplate is slightly warm to the
Desc4: touch, as the wood's life force is magically kept alive to
Desc5: strengthen the armour.

Name: silverwood plate corselet
Desc1: This is a corselet of enchanted silverwood, inlaid with
Desc2: precious gems and gold. It is strong as steel, but is
Desc3: nonetheless quite light. A gift surely fit for a king.

Name: silverwood forest
Desc1: The trees of this forest are tall, with golden leaves and
Desc2: smooth silvery bark. They are slender but very strong, with
Desc3: long, high limbs.

Name: rope bridge
Desc1: This slender rope bridge is made of plaited elven rope, and
Desc2: is much stronger than it looks.

Name: elven waybread
Desc1: This delicious-smelling cake is wrapped in the golden leaves
Desc2: of the silverwood tree. Light, tasty and filling, they make
Desc3: ideal rations for adventurers.

Name: massive wooden club
Desc1: This huge wooden club is over six feet in length. Wieldable
Desc2: by only the strongest fighters, this weapon is not an
Desc3: elegant weapon in combat, but it deals massive damage.

Name: spiked gauntlets
Desc1: These heavy steel gauntlets have spikes protruding from the
Desc2: knuckles and the back of the hand. Their palms are of thick
Desc3: leather so that they will provide better grip.

Name: ancient stone wall
Desc1: This ancient stone wall towers about a hundred feet over
Desc2: you. It is made of huge dark blue blocks, their surfaces
Desc3: barely marred by the passage of time.

Name: demolished doors
Desc1: These huge steel-banded wood doors have been blasted asunder
Desc2: by some fiery magic. The scorch marks appear quite fresh,
Desc3: and it is probable that they have been made only recently.

Name: white fang
Desc1: This is a four-inch-long fang, bone-white, and somewhat cold
Desc2: to the touch.

Name: black fang
Desc1: This is a four-inch-long fang, black as pitch and very
Desc2: sharp. It irritates your skin to touch it.

Name: green fang
Desc1: This is a four-inch-long fang, coloured deep green. Holding
Desc2: it in your hand makes you feel somewhat sick.

Name: blue fang
Desc1: This is a four-inch-long fang, azure blue and quite sharp.
Desc2: The hair on your hand stands straight out when you hold it.

Name: red fang
Desc1: This is a four-inch-long fang, red as blood, and somewhat
Desc2: warm to the touch.

Name: dragonclaw staff
Desc1: This four-foot-long staff is crafted from pure adamantite.
Desc2: Its slender shaft has been generously engraved with symbols
Desc3: of power. Upon one end a small dragon's claw has been
Desc4: affixed, an orb of polished sapphire in its grasp. Deep
Desc5: within the orb, blue flashes spark occasionally.

Name: silverwood staff
Desc1: This elegant staff is a living branch of the silverwood
Desc2: trees, long and slender and warm with life. Starting halfway
Desc3: up the shaft and continuing to its end, stars of all shape
Desc4: and size have been carved into the wood and have been
Desc5: coloured gold, with no apparent damage to the living wood.
Desc6: The silverwood staff radiates a palpable magical aura.

Name: spiked plate corselet
Desc1: This is a massive steel plate corselet, studded with wicked
Desc2: spikes all over its surface. Although it is extremely heavy,
Desc3: it is also exceedingly strong.

Name: crumbling bible
Desc1: This ancient religious tome has lost all of its pages, save
Desc2: one which is in perfect condition. Upon this last page is
Desc3: the holy incantation necessary to learn a spell to restore
Desc4: flesh that has been transformed to stone by unnatural means.

Name: blades of balance
Desc1: These twin swords are exquisitely balanced and honed to a
Desc2: razor-sharp edge. One is pure white, and engraved with
Desc3: flowing, sinuous runes, the other is jet black and etched
Desc4: with angular symbols. They cannot be wielded separately,
Desc5: and in conjunction make excellent weapons.

Name: chrome key
Desc1: This small, shining key is made of brilliantly-reflective
Desc2: metal. Etched into the end is a small, lidded eye.

Name: demonhide bracers
Desc1: These deep red bracers are crafted out of the black-spined
Desc2: skin of a demon. They are tough and form-fitting. On the
Desc3: inside wrist of each bracer, a glowing blue symbol of the
Desc4: Kai Lords is emblazoned.

Name: mithril helm
Desc1: This gorgeous full-helm has been crafted to look like the
Desc2: head of a dwarven king. Atop it a golden crown has been
Desc3: affixed, and the faceplate is crafted in the likeness of a
Desc4: stern dwarf-face. The helm glimmers slightly and is
Desc5: completely unscratched.

Name: holy avenger
Desc1: This long, straight blade is crafted from adamantite, and
Desc2: polished to a silvery sheen. Its cross-hilt is wrapped with
Desc3: golden cord. Engraved up and down the blade's length are
Desc4: holy inscriptions, and an aura of power protects the wielder
Desc5: from evil foes, making him more difficult to hit.

Name: icehammer
Desc1: This massive sledgehammer seems to be made out of solid,
Desc2: glittering blue ice. It radiates an aura of intense cold,
Desc3: but despite this it can be handled without harm.

Name: shattered skeleton
Desc1: This broken, chewed carcass has evidently been here a long
Desc2: time, judging by the dirt encrusting its bones. At second
Desc3: glance, one of the bones seems to be free of blood and dirt,
Desc4: and sticks out of the ground rather than out of the
Desc5: skeleton.

Name: black silk robes
Desc1: These fine robes are woven out of a glossy black silk. They
Desc2: are embroidered with black thread, and are surprisingly
Desc3: tough. At second glance intricate symbols can be seen
Desc4: stitched all over their surface.

Name: black silk pants
Desc1: These fine pants are woven out of a glossy black silk. They
Desc2: are embroidered with black thread, and are surprisingly
Desc3: tough. At second glance intricate symbols can be seen
Desc4: stitched all over their surface.

Name: black silk slippers
Desc1: These fine slippers are woven out of a glossy black silk.
Desc2: They are embroidered with black thread, and are surprisingly
Desc3: tough. At second glance intricate symbols can be seen
Desc4: stitched all over their surface.

Name: black silk gloves
Desc1: These fine gloves are woven out of a glossy black silk. They
Desc2: are embroidered with black thread, and are surprisingly
Desc3: tough. At second glance intricate symbols can be seen
Desc4: stitched all over their surface.

Name: contraption
Desc1: This is a heavy metal plate, about six inches thick and ten
Desc2: by ten feet square. It is affixed to the wall here by some
Desc3: unknown means. Covering its surface are many levers and
Desc4: switches, buttons and knobs of all descriptions and sizes.
Desc5: What the odd contraption could be for is anyone's guess.

Name: dragon key
Desc1: This odd key has a head shaped like the visage of a toothily
Desc2: grinning dragon. The barrel and teeth of the key are of a
Desc3: black metal, and set in the barrel are five tiny stones, one
Desc4: each of blue, red, green, black and white.

Name: white dragon carving
Desc1: This three-foot-diameter white marble carving features a
Desc2: roaring dragon's head, encircled by icicles. Five odd curved
Desc3: slots ring the carving, one of which is filled by a white
Desc4: fang.

Name: black dragon carving
Desc1: This three-foot-diameter obsidian carving features a roaring
Desc2: dragon's head, encircled by fuming droplets. Five odd curved
Desc3: slots ring the carving, two of which are filled by white and
Desc4: black fangs.

Name: green dragon carving
Desc1: This three-foot-diameter green jade carving features a
Desc2: roaring dragon's head, encircled by wispy fumes. Five odd
Desc3: slots ring the carving, three of which are filled with
Desc4: white, black and green fangs.

Name: blue dragon carving
Desc1: This three-foot-diameter lapis carving features a roaring
Desc2: dragon's head, encircled by crackling lightning. Five odd
Desc3: slots ring the carving, all but one of which are filled with
Desc4: white, black, green and blue fangs.

Name: dragon carving
Desc1: This three-foot-diameter granite carving features a roaring
Desc2: dragon's head, encircled by double lines. Five odd curved
Desc3: slots ring the carving.

Name: blood lance
Desc1: This seven-foot-long lance is coloured blood red, and is
Desc2: wickedly barbed. Unholy symbols etched up and down its
Desc3: length give off a smoky yellow light.

Name: black tome
Desc1: This huge, heavy tome is covered with swirling silvery runes
Desc2: and symbols. Inside, yellowed parchment pages are inscribed
Desc3: with two spells: Chaos Shield, which concentrates chaotic
Desc4: power around the target in a crackling field, and Mana Flux,
Desc5: which draws energy from the surrounding area to regenerate
Desc6: mana. Both spells sometimes have undesired effects.

Name: forgotten scroll
Desc1: Detailed upon this ancient, rotting leather parchment is a
Desc2: form of divine incantation. It provides the chants required
Desc3: to draw power from the forgotten gods, allowing you to
Desc4: sacrifice your health to benefit another.

Name: iceforge anvil
Desc1: This huge black-iron anvil seems to have been made for a
Desc2: giant, as it is six feet up to its flat hammering surface! A
Desc3: thick coating of ice surrounds the anvil, and waves of cold
Desc4: emanate from it. Upon close scrutiny, glowing blue runes can
Desc5: be seen etched into its surface. Ancient rumours have told
Desc6: of enchanted anvils being used to craft magical armaments.

Name: frozen hydra
Desc1: This huge, seven-headed beast is covered in a three-foot-
Desc2: thick prison of ice, its snarling visage forever frozen. It
Desc3: appears heavily armoured and armed, its teeth being long and
Desc4: swordlike, its necks long and agile. Gripped in one of its
Desc5: mouths is a large, glittering icy hammer, maul-sized for
Desc6: someone of human stature.

Name: frozen giant
Desc1: This thirty-foot-tall giant is encased in a living tomb of
Desc2: ice three feet thick. His massively-muscled arms are frozen
Desc3: reaching out as if grasping at something, and his face is
Desc4: fixed in an outraged frown.

Name: ancient tome
Desc1: This large, heavy tome lays open, a thin, red silk bookmark
Desc2: nestled between its pages. The ancient, yellow pages are
Desc3: covered in a thin, spidery text which reads:

Name: small book
Desc1: This ancient book's pages have all crumbled to dust, but
Desc2: its lacquered covers have not. There is writing on the
Desc3: inside cover, as well as a small illustration, and though
Desc4: they are faded and hard to make out, they read as follows:

Name: painting
Desc1: This large painting is set in a plain wooden frame. It is
Desc2: covered with a thick layer of dust, and is somewhat worse
Desc3: for wear. However, this couldn't possibly make the woman in
Desc4: the painting less attractive, as she is possibly the ugliest
Desc5: woman you have ever seen. A face only a son could love, and
Desc6: that must have been the case, as at the bottom is "Mother".

Name: stone mouth
Desc1: As you gaze at the mouth, the lips begin to move, whispering
Desc2: a ghostly rhyme which goes like this:

Name: plaque on gate
Desc1: This ornate iron gate is tall and spike-topped, and would
Desc2: easily prevent entry by scaling. Its thick bars make any
Desc3: thought of bashing it down immediately flee your head. A
Desc4: beautiful platinum plaque set in the gate sports seven
Desc5: glittering stones -- ruby, emerald, diamond, amethyst,
Desc6: sapphire, onyx and topaz -- and looks somewhat like this:

Name: palace key
Desc1: This intricate golden key is engraved with the name of King
Desc2: Yeshuz.

Name: elf-head
Desc1: This bloody head once belonged to a forest-loving wood-elf.
Desc2: Now its blue tongue lolls grotesquely, its sightless eyes
Desc3: staring out blankly in death.

Name: head of the woodelf lord
Desc1: Even in death, the elf-lord seems to have an air of
Desc2: serenity about him. Too bad he's worm food now.

Name: eye of the beholder
Desc1: This large globular eye radiates anti-magic intensely. It is
Desc2: somewhat heavy, and gives you the creeps as it stares
Desc3: lifelessly at you.

Name: nexus spear
Desc1: This long, slender spear is crafted out of a glittering
Desc2: silvery metal. Blue sparkles of energy crackle forth
Desc3: periodically, leaving the smell of ozone in the air. It
Desc4: radiates an aura of intense power, and is lethal in the
Desc5: hands of a skilled fighter.

Name: staff of the elements
Desc1: This strange staff is made of four intertwined metallic
Desc2: rods, one blue, one green, one red and one silver. It
Desc3: crackles with arcane energy, as the powers from all four
Desc4: elements meet, fuse and conflict.

Name: adamantite spear
Desc1: This long, heavy spear is crafted from one of the hardest
Desc2: and heaviest metals known -- adamantite. Its dark surface
Desc3: almost seems to absorb light, and its head is razor-sharp
Desc4: and glimmers in the light.

Name: gleaming contraption
Desc1: This large, box-like object gleams like polished silver,
Desc2: greatly in contrast to the surrounding junk. There is a wide
Desc3: opening in the front, the High Guild of Magery's seal on one
Desc4: side, and a plaque covered with instructions on the other.

Name: plaque
Desc1: This rectangular plaque is inscribed with the following:
Desc2: "This Recycler Cube is used to get rid of old or unwanted
Desc3: items. It will only accept select items, but the items it
Desc4: does accept are those which most shopkeepers do not. Simply
Desc5: SELL the item here, and an appropriate gold reimbursement
Desc6: will arrive through the slot."

Name: mining helm
Desc1: This is a large metal hat with a hollow at the top for
Desc2: placing a candle or other light source. Currently a glowing
Desc3: stone has been placed there, naturally glowing with a
Desc4: phosphorescent tinge. It can offer decent protection for the
Desc5: head as well as decent light for underground tunnels.

Name: nexus chakram
Desc1: This exotic weapon is a razor-sharp circle of gleaming
Desc2: steel, which, when thrown, magically returns to its wielder.
Desc3: The blade is three inches wide, with the weapon being one
Desc4: foot in diameter. Strange runes inscribed upon its surface
Desc5: glow fiercely.

Name: whirling vortex
Desc1: Brilliant colours swirl about in midair here, as some sort
Desc2: of extra-planar rift breaks the air. Energy crackles all
Desc3: about this arcane portal... Who knows where it might lead?

Name: shining metallic robes
Desc1: These heavy garments are made from some seamless, glittering
Desc2: silvery fabric, which is smooth as silk. A strange energy
Desc3: courses though the robes, which crackle with sparkling
Desc4: motes whenever their shining folds are shifted.

Name: obsidian obelisk
Desc1: This tall, pointed obelisk is night-black and as smooth as
Desc2: glass. Intricate runes carved into its surface emanate a
Desc3: strange aura of power.

Name: pipe
Desc1: This thick, silvery pipe glistens with cool condensation.
Desc2: Seams in the metalwork are sealed tightly with rivets, and
Desc3: fresh water drips down periodically. Judging from the
Desc4: workmanship, it is likely the handiwork of gnomes.

Name: rubble
Desc1: Searching through the rubble, you find a stone tile set into
Desc2: the floor.

Name: boulder
Desc1: This large boulder is somewhat suspiciously round, and looks
Desc2: to have been carved out of the walls of the tunnel.

Name: gate key
Desc1: This simple key is fashioned of a strange black metal.
Desc2: Impossibly tiny teeth line both sides of it, suggesting an
Desc3: incredibly-complex locking mechanism. For some reason, you
Desc4: get a sick feeling in the pit of your stomach and want to
Desc5: dispose of the key quickly.

Name: bloodstone orb
Desc1: This small, heavy stone orb is swirled with green and red,
Desc2: and feels slightly warm to the touch. A single glowing rune
Desc3: in the side pulsates with hidden power.

Name: glowing key
Desc1: This small key is slightly translucent, and has no teeth or
Desc2: lock interface whatsoever. Circular runes are carved around
Desc3: the small head, and the key glows from within with a pale
Desc4: blue light.

Name: adamantite key
Desc1: This large key is crafted from the dusky grey metal known as
Desc2: adamantite. It is indestructible and quite heavy for its
Desc3: size. Stamped into the head of the key is a bold royal
Desc4: insignia.

Name: dark blue orb
Desc1: This is a small, royal-blue sphere, roughly one foot in
Desc2: diameter. It glows and pulses with an inner light,
Desc3: practically oozing with dark power.

Name: opal brooch
Desc1: This intricate brooch is heavily encrusted with small opals
Desc2: arranged into the official royal insignia of the monarchy.
Desc3: It is a sign of very high rank or achievement.

Name: shelf and jars
Desc1: This large shelf is covered in dirt and dust, and many tiny
Desc2: disgusting creatures crawl about it in squalor. Partially
Desc3: concealed behind the row of jars is a crude stone button
Desc4: recessed into the wall!

Name: golden key
Desc1: This small, heavy key is made of pure reddish gold. Its
Desc2: smooth surface is unadorned, but seems to radiate a strange
Desc3: force that makes your hair stand on end.

Name: wooden desk
Desc1: This old wooden desk looks like it has been severly abused,
Desc2: its surface being cut and worn. All its drawers are missing,
Desc3: but this is fortunate, as it allows you to see a hidden
Desc4: iron switch lurking deep within!

Name: amber talisman
Desc1: This small, circular disc is engraved with a curving sigil
Desc2: of peculiar design.

Name: huge keg
Desc1: This massive wooden barrel is nearly large enough to stand
Desc2: in without stooping. An ornate silver tap is set securely
Desc3: in the centre of the front of the keg, and glimmers in the
Desc4: light.

Name: greasy leather bracelet
Desc1: This heavy, thick bracelet is filthy and looks well-used.
Desc2: A single strange rune has been burned into one side of it.
Desc3: Upon closer inspection, you notice that the leather is in
Desc4: fact the skin of a human!

Name: mutilated corpses
Desc1: Many disemboweled bodies have been hung by meathooks here
Desc2: to allow easy access by whatever filthy beast consumes them.
Desc3: The stench here is incredible, making you gag and forcing
Desc4: you back.

Name: giant apparatus
Desc1: This massive steel and glass device appears to process a
Desc2: fluid which flows into it from a huge wooden vat. Noxious
Desc3: clouds of yellow fumes puff out occasionally, filling the
Desc4: air with a deadly reek.

Name: moldy key
Desc1: This large, heavy iron key is covered with a thin layer of
Desc2: mold and fungus. It appears to be quite old and abused.

Name: rune-etched sceptre
Desc1: This golden sceptre is about three and a half feet long, and
Desc2: is decorated from head to handle in glowing runes. Jeweled
Desc3: studs ring the head and seem to shine with a life all their
Desc4: own. Easily swung with one hand, the sceptre seems magically
Desc5: guided to where you want it to strike.

Name: adamantite katana
Desc1: This four-foot-long sword is one of the finest examples of
Desc2: craftmanship you have ever seen. Made from the powerful, but
Desc3: heavy metal, adamantite, it is a weapon to strike terror
Desc4: into a foe. Perfectly balanced and sharper than a razor, in
Desc5: a master's hands it is a whirling blade of death.

Name: jeweled adamantite longsword
Desc1: This is a cobalt blue longsword, forged of the finest
Desc2: adamantite. Its hilt is lined with deep crimson rubies that
Desc3: are carved with intricate runes and shimmer with magical
Desc4: luster. At the tip of the hilt is a large black skull that
Desc5: seems locked in a permanent grin.

Name: cat-o-nine tails
Desc1: This long-handled whip has nine three-foot leather "tails"
Desc2: attached to a knob at its end. Metal spikes and razors are
Desc3: embedded in the lashes, and would cause immense pain to
Desc4: anyone struck.

Name: adamantite claymore
Desc1: This is a large one-handed sword, nearly the size of a
Desc2: bastard-sword and crafted out of adamantite. The hilt is
Desc3: wound with black leather and intertwined with fine mithril
Desc4: thread. Dark blue energy pulses up and down the length of
Desc5: the blade, making the hair on the back of your neck stand on
Desc6: end.

Name: obsidian field plate
Desc1: This is a corselet of finely-crafted obsidian, inlined with
Desc2: a thick layer of soft leather padding. Its shoulder guards
Desc3: each have three large spikes protruding from them, making
Desc4: side attacks difficult. Swirling runes cover the surface,
Desc5: seeming to dance mesmerizingly in grand, complex patterns.

Name: carved statues
Desc1: These two statues flank the gate, each crafted in the form
Desc2: of a tall dark-elf warrior garbed in chainmail and bearing
Desc3: a long blade. Strangely, they seem somewhat warm to the
Desc4: touch, almost as if life force pulsed within them.

Name: small glass flask
Desc1: This rounded flask is filled with an oily fluid, which
Desc2: bubbles and froths unnaturally.

Name: diamond-studded ring
Desc1: This is a small, fragile-looking silver band with evenly-
Desc2: spaced diamond studs placed around its circumference.
Desc3: Impossibly tiny runes inlaid with mithril glitter brightly
Desc4: when exposed to light.

Name: silversilk trousers
Desc1: This is a marvelously-sewn pair of silversilk pants, inlaid
Desc2: with precious runes of gold. They are light and supple, and
Desc3: are a treasure indeed.

Name: large silvery cross
Desc1: This is the fabled Cross of Vengeance, which, when used,
Desc2: imbues its wielder with a mighty power. Its heavy, foot-long
Desc3: body is etched with glowing red runes, and its surface is
Desc4: untarnished despite its seemingly incredible age.

Name: ivory bracelet
Desc1: This simple-looking, but nonetheless beautifully-crafted,
Desc2: bracelet is made from the purest ivory. Bands of yellow gold
Desc3: and platinum are staggered at evenly-spaced intervals all
Desc4: around its length, and there is an inscription written in an
Desc5: ancient tongue on the inside.

Name: arcane tome
Desc1: This is a small, hand-sized book. On its cover is an exotic
Desc2: design decorated by a strikingly ornate description.
Desc3: Glancing about its tattered pages, you find an ancient
Desc4: incantation which may be of use to mages.

Name: darkwood shield
Desc1: This small shield is carved from the bark of an ancient
Desc2: darkwood tree. It is very thick, so as to provide good
Desc3: protection, but it is still much lighter than any metal
Desc4: shield. A slight warmth seems to radiate from it, and its
Desc5: surface almost pulses with life.

Name: pristine scroll
Desc1: The runes of this magical scroll seem to burn into your
Desc2: brain as you look at them, yet for some reason you cannot
Desc3: make them out. Only by reading the scroll completely could
Desc4: anything be learned from it.

Name: mithril-runed tunic
Desc1: This light, exquisitely beautiful tunic is made of the
Desc2: finest leathers, engraved with spectacular mithril-inlaid
Desc3: runes. An aura of power radiates from its surface in waves.

Name: door with puzzle lock
Desc1: This ingenious puzzle lock is crafted in such a cunning
Desc2: manner that it would require a great intellect to solve it,
Desc3: if the solution was not already known. No keyhole can be
Desc4: seen to open the door, so solving the puzzle is necessary
Desc5: to continue.

Name: nightblack portal
Desc1: This oval rift in space pulsates with an evil, chaotic
Desc2: power. Negative energy leaks out and surrounds you, leaving
Desc3: you numb and trembling. Whatever lies beyond would be sure
Desc4: death for the weak, and difficult at best even for mighty
Desc5: heroes.

Name: black orb
Desc1: This head-sized orb floats in the air with apparent ease.
Desc2: Its smooth, featureless surface is shrouded in arcing energy
Desc3: which makes you wince at its intensity.

Name: throne
Desc1: This exquisitely-carved throne is truly fit for a king -- or
Desc2: queen, in this case. An intricate button in the shape of a
Desc3: skull can easily be seen carved into one arm of the throne.

Name: ruby emblem
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCRUBY.EMB

Name: red key
Desc1: This key is made of plain iron and was not hard to
Desc2: manufacture. The ridges of the key are fairly simple, tellin
Desc3: you the lock is not that secure. It is painted bright red,
Desc4: you can assume to match whichever house it belongs to.

Name: mithril chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This chainmail shirt is crafted from mithril, the strongest
Desc2: substance known to exist. The dwarves are the only ones
Desc3: known to have the skill to fashion mithril, and such exotic
Desc4: wonders are rare and precious.

Name: fine chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This exquisite chainmail shirt is crafted from the finest
Desc2: high-steel. Painstaking work has gone into its shining
Desc3: interlinked rings. It would provide good protection from
Desc4: blows in combat.

Name: ogre-skin shirt
Desc1: This heavy shirt is made from the thick, boiled skin of an
Desc2: ogre. Known for their toughness, Ogres are usually unwilling
Desc3: to part with their skin, but when the occasion arises it
Desc4: makes excellent armour.

Name: silvery shield
