Desc1: This large, curved knight's shield gleams with a silvery
Desc2: light. A thin border of golden runes frames the rearing
Desc3: shape of a lion.

Name: dwarven chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This heavy suit of chainmail is a product of the masterful
Desc2: skill of the dwarves. Made of two thin layers of tiny, but
Desc3: unbelievably strong, rings, it provides a level of protectio
Desc4: seldom seen in light armours.

Name: crystal platemail
Desc1: This exotic suit of armour has apparently been made from
Desc2: smoky black crystal. Runes embedded deep in its surface
Desc3: give evidence of its magical origin, and pulse with a dim
Desc4: green fire.

Name: long battle shield
Desc1: This long, rectangular shield is used by elite armies to
Desc2: form walls, behind which they can fight safely. Semi-
Desc3: circular holes are cut on either side, through which spears
Desc4: or other thrusting weapons have room to attack.

Name: prismatic robes
Desc1: These brilliant robes reflect the light in the myriad
Desc2: colours of the rainbow. They are smooth and light like silk,
Desc3: but are far more durable and are obviously of magical
Desc4: origin.

Name: lacquered battle armour
Desc1: This leather tunic is crafted from stiff, black leather, and
Desc2: has been emblazoned with swirling golden emblems. Small
Desc3: semi-precious gems glitter in adornment on the breast. From
Desc4: the look and quality of it, it was likely the personal
Desc5: armour of a high-ranking leader.

Name: adamantite platemail tunic
Desc1: This massive suit of plate armour is made of interlocking
Desc2: plates of dark, gleaming adamantite. Nearly impenetrable,
Desc3: this suit of armour would greatly protect the wearer in
Desc4: combat, if the weight is bearable.

Name: skull shield
Desc1: This massive shield has elaborately-carved skulls set in
Desc2: its black iron front. Embedded in the centre of the shield's
Desc3: face is a gleaming skull, its visage forever frozen in a
Desc4: hideous grin.

Name: astral robes
Desc1: Strange, haunting visions of the astral plane continually
Desc2: shift and writhe across the surface of these pale golden
Desc3: robes. Made of some light, but incredibly strong, material,
Desc4: the magic inherent in these robes can be felt by even the
Desc5: most magic-deadened individual.

Name: behemoth hide
Desc1: This hideous-looking armour is fashioned from the worked
Desc2: hide of a behemoth. Stronger than steel, the behemoth's
Desc3: spiked skin gives the wearer an ominous and deadly
Desc4: appearance while providing incredible protection.

Name: dragonscale armour
Desc1: Gleaming with a permanent polish, dragonscale armour is
Desc2: highly-ranked in its worth. The overlapping dragon scales
Desc3: provide nearly-unsurpassed protection, making many other
Desc4: suits of armour seem almost useless in comparison.

Name: aegis shield
Desc1: This huge, round shield is intricately carved in a manner
Desc2: not seen in hundreds of years. Raised in the centre of the
Desc3: shield, a long-forgotten god's face stares out, the
Desc4: sapphires in his eyes gleaming like lightning. It has
Desc5: survived for countless generations, and aside from its
Desc6: antiquated appearance it is completely unmarked.

Name: silversilk tunic
Desc1: This beautiful shirt is made of the finest material known to
Desc2: man -- silversilk. Only the elves know how to weave this
Desc3: marvelous magical cloth, which is as light as silk while
Desc4: being strong as steel, and just as impenetrable.

Name: fine greatsword
Desc1: This heavy, two-handed sword has an extremely sharp four-
Desc2: foot blade that can punch through even the heaviest armour
Desc3: with ease. It is made from high steel and is commonly seen
Desc4: in the possession of high ranking officers.

Name: fine mace
Desc1: This sturdy weapon is crafted out of high-steel, and has
Desc2: been fashioned in such a way that it is excellently
Desc3: balanced. This allows for heavier hitting with no reduction
Desc4: in speed.

Name: black steel halberd
Desc1: This massive, unwieldy weapon has a wickedly-curved head,
Desc2: and is fashioned from a gleaming steel the colour of soot.
Desc3: Wound about its haft is a thin cord which provides a good
Desc4: grip.

Name: great bronzewood club
Desc1: This massive club appears to be a branch hewn from one of
Desc2: the far-off bronzewood trees, with the smaller branches
Desc3: removed. Its grip is bound tightly in leather, and the
Desc4: weapon swings surprisingly well for its size.

Name: ashwood staff
Desc1: This long, slender staff has weighty silver caps on the ends
Desc2: for better striking power. It is nicely balanced. Thin
Desc3: leather strips have been wound about the centre for grip.

Name: dwarven axe
Desc1: This heavy, one-handed axe is short-hafted and has a single
Desc2: blade shaped like a half moon. Well-balanced and durable, it
Desc3: is a fine example of the fact that daily dwarven handiwork
Desc4: greatly surpasses most works of masters of other races.

Name: dwarven hammer
Desc1: This light hammer has a rectangular head of the finest
Desc2: dwarf-iron. It is easy to swing yet hits hard, and would
Desc3: make an excellent weapon.

Name: three-headed flail
Desc1: This massive flail is quite impressive -- it has three
Desc2: spherical, studded heads attached to long chains, which
Desc3: would cause great damage in combat. Its thick wooden haft
Desc4: is banded with iron for reinforcement. A difficult weapon
Desc5: to use, it is rarely seen in the possession of unseasoned
Desc6: fighters.

Name: long golden staff
Desc1: This long golden staff is exquisitely carved with intricate
Desc2: symbols all along its length. At one end is a circular head,
Desc3: with a blazing emerald glittering in its centre.

Name: runic warhammer
Desc1: This massive, heavy hammer's granite head is intricately
Desc2: carved with jagged runes of a crude sort. The runes glow
Desc3: a fierce red and seem to pulsate to your heartbeat. Its
Desc4: haft is of leather-bound ironwood, and appears well-worn.

Name: demon-carved halberd
Desc1: This hideous creation's blade is carved with all manner of
Desc2: grotesquely-leering demonic faces. Its heavy edge is sharp
Desc3: as a razor, and its thick haft is intricately carved to
Desc4: resemble intertwined limbs.

Name: dragontooth trident
Desc1: This long, heavy, two-handed trident's shaft is made from
Desc2: a single piece of witchwood, known to amplify the power of
Desc3: spells cast into it. Its wicked-looking head consists of
Desc4: three-forearm-length dragon's teeth, naturally as sharp as
Desc5: razors and as strong as steel.

Name: starsteel mace
Desc1: This long-shafted mace has been crafted from a strange and
Desc2: extremely rare metal called starsteel. It shines bluish-
Desc3: silver, and its head is round and studded. A single
Desc4: glittering diamond has been set in its pommel, and spiral
Desc5: symbols inlaid in its haft glow warmly.

Name: wicked bone scythe
Desc1: This massive weapon looks like it was conjured up in
Desc2: someone's nightmare. Its long, curved blade is almost talon-
Desc3: like in appearance, and glitters with razor-edged sharpness.
Desc4: The haft is made out of yellowed bone, carved with faces
Desc5: screaming in torment and with images of leering demons.

Name: stormhammer
Desc1: This heavy stone weapon seems almost crudely made, but is
Desc2: imbued with incredible destructive magics. Lightning
Desc3: crackles all about it, occasionally discharging when the
Desc4: hammer strikes its mark.

Name: shimmering vial
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled to the brim with an oily,
Desc2: opalescent liquid that glows and shimmers with a pale light.

Name: black potion
Desc1: This heavy metal flask is filled with a vile, oily fluid
Desc2: that reeks of rotting vegetation. Small bits of unknown
Desc3: matter float about in it revoltingly.

Name: golden vial
Desc1: This long, elegantly-crafted crystal vial is filled with
Desc2: a brightly-glowing golden fluid. The light from the liquid
Desc3: pulses and hums with a strange force, causing the crystal
Desc4: of the vial to ring musically!

Name: azurite stone
Desc1: This small, ornamental stone is opaque and a deep mottled
Desc2: blue in colour.

Name: agate stone
Desc1: This small, ornamental stone is banded with brown, blue, red
Desc2: and white stripes.

Name: hematite stone
Desc1: This small, ornamental stone is a silvery grey-black
Desc2: colour.

Name: malachite stone
Desc1: This small, ornamental stone is coloured a rich light and
Desc2: dark green.

Name: obsidian stone
Desc1: This small, ornamental stone is glassy and jet black in
Desc2: colour.

Name: turquoise stone
Desc1: This small, ornamental stone is a mottled light and dark
Desc2: aqua.

Name: bloodstone
Desc1: This small, semi-precious stone is red in colour, with
Desc2: flecks and spots of blackness.

Name: carnelian stone
Desc1: This small, semi-precious stone is dark orange in colour.

Name: moonstone
Desc1: This small, semi-precious stone is semi-opaque, and is white
Desc2: with a pale blue hue.

Name: onyx stone
Desc1: This small, semi-precious stone is black and shiny.

Name: piece of crystal
Desc1: This small, semi-precious stone is clear and multi-faceted.
Desc2: It shines brilliantly in the light.

Name: piece of amber
Desc1: This small, fancy stone is a transparent golden colour, and
Desc2: is highly prized in certain primitive villages.

Name: amethyst stone
Desc1: This small, fancy stone is a beautiful semi-transparent
Desc2: purple in colour.

Name: piece of jade
Desc1: This small, fancy stone is a milky green in colour.

Name: aquamarine stone
Desc1: This small, precious stone is quite smooth, and a pale
Desc2: blue-green in colour.

Name: garnet
Desc1: This small, precious stone is clear and deep red in colour.

Name: pearl
Desc1: This small, precious stone is pure white and seems to glow
Desc2: in the light.

Name: topaz stone
Desc1: This small, precious stone is a golden yellow in colour.

Name: black opal
Desc1: This small gem is dark green in colour, with black mottling
Desc2: and golden flecks.

Name: fire opal
Desc1: This small gem is a fiery red in colour, and glitters in the
Desc2: light.

Name: opal
Desc1: This small gem is a pale blue in colour, with green and gold
Desc2: mottling.

Name: diamond
Desc1: This small, transparent jewel is a brilliantly glittering
Desc2: blue-white in colour, and is highly prized for use in
Desc3: jewelry.

Name: emerald
Desc1: This small, transparent jewel is a brilliantly glittering
Desc2: green in colour, and is highly prized for use in jewelry.

Name: ruby
Desc1: This small, transparent jewel is a brilliantly glittering
Desc2: crimson red in colour, and is highly prized for use in
Desc3: jewelry.

Name: sapphire
Desc1: This small, transparent jewel is a brilliantly glittering
Desc2: medium blue in colour, and is highly prized for use in
Desc3: jewelry.

Name: wooden box
Desc1: This simple pine box is about one foot long and half as
Desc2: wide and deep. Objects inside rattle about freely.

Name: oak chest
Desc1: This medium-sized chest is of simple but elegant
Desc2: construction. Long, interlocking planks of sanded oak form
Desc3: its rectangular shape, and the clattering of object can be
Desc4: heard from within when it is moved.

Name: massive wooden chest
Desc1: This huge wooden chest is crafted from heavy pine. It is
Desc2: simply made, but very sturdy. It has no lock, and when moved
Desc3: things can be heard rattling around inside it.

Name: iron-banded chest
Desc1: This medium-sized chest is made of thick wood, and is bound
Desc2: with sturdy iron strips. When moved, objects rattle about
Desc3: inside.

Name: silver box
Desc1: This smallish silver box is ornately carved with rampant
Desc2: animals. When moved, objects rattle about inside.

Name: huge darkwood chest
Desc1: This heavy chest is crafted from silver-bound planks of
Desc2: darkwood. Its massive, rectangular frame holds objects of
Desc3: value, for when it is moved rattling sounds can be heard
Desc4: from within.

Name: golden box
Desc1: This elaborate wrought-gold box is inlaid with beautiful
Desc2: filigrees and designs. Something inside rattles about
Desc3: noisily when the box is moved or shook.

Name: steel chest
Desc1: This solid steel chest appears to have been crafted by a
Desc2: blacksmith, as the work is crude but solid. Objects inside
Desc3: rattle about when it is moved.

Name: silverwood chest
Desc1: This large, gorgeous silverwood chest is heavily inlaid with
Desc2: golden ornamentation and small precious stones. Objects
Desc3: inside rattle about when it is moved.
Desc4: from within.

Name: crater
Desc1: The crater is hot and blackened by the impact of whatever
Desc2: meteorite crashed here. Metallic splinters litter the area,
Desc3: and glitter with a strange, otherworldy light.

Name: gouged walls
Desc1: The gouges in the walls are quite large, indicating that
Desc2: whatever beast chewed its way through here has large,
Desc3: unnaturally sharp teeth. Embedded deep in the gouges are
Desc4: tiny slivers of a glittering metal, though what that means
Desc5: is anyone's guess.

Name: gleaming shard
Desc1: This long, straight shard glitters with an otherworldly
Desc2: bluish hue. It is made of a metal unknown to this land, and
Desc3: it both indestructible and razor-sharp.

Name: grey bushes
Desc1: The bushes are fairly unremarkable. Their bark is a dark
Desc2: grey, and is extremely dry-- their leaves are small, round
Desc3: and light grey.

Name: grey bushes
Desc1: The bushes are fairly unremarkable. Their bark is a dark
Desc2: grey, and is extremely dry-- their leaves are small, round
Desc3: and light grey. Upon closer inspection, a narrow crack can
Desc4: be seen lurking behind them!

Name: golden hide
Desc1: This glittering hide is covered in coarse golden hair. It is
Desc2: extremely dense for its size, making it very heavy and quite
Desc3: a nuisance to carry around. It could possibly be made into
Desc4: armour, but only by a skilled craftsman.

Name: silver flute
Desc1: This beautiful silver flute sings with a clear, beautiful
Desc2: tone when played.

Name: golden harp
Desc1: This exquisite golden harp is crafted with intricate
Desc2: swirling patterns. Its strings are fine and well-strung,
Desc3: and the melody that it plays when its strings are plucked
Desc4: is heavenly.

Name: bardic lute
Desc1: This rare lute is a remnant of the days of the legendary
Desc2: bards. Its resonance is perfect and its construction is a
Desc3: mastery of woodcraft.

Name: room ticket
Desc1: This small ticket is good for a night's rest in an inn or
Desc2: tavern. Usually worth the price, as resting in a comfortable
Desc3: inn bed is more beneficial than anywhere else.

Name: swamp boots
Desc1: These long boots come up nearly to your crotch, and are
Desc2: covered in a coarse, dense black pelt. They seem to be
Desc3: completely waterproof.

Name: fine throwing knife
Desc1: This well-balanced, razor-sharp blade makes a formidable
Desc2: weapon at short range. It is both accurate and damaging in
Desc3: the hands of an expert.

Name: black retchweed
Desc1: This coarse, wiry plant is one of the fouler species of
Desc2: vegetation in swamps. Known to cause death and deformity in
Desc3: whomever eats it, it can be used to create powerful poisons
Desc4: for which there is no known antidote.

Name: swamp
Desc1: This spooky swamp stinks of rotting vegetation and gaseous
Desc2: fumes. The ground alternates from soft spongy masses, to
Desc3: soupy poisonous marsh seemingly at random, making navigation
Desc4: hazardous in the extreme. Strange sounds echo throughout the
Desc5: concealing mists, and shadows continually flicker in your
Desc6: peripheral vision. You get the feeling of being watched.

Name: gnomish fish-helm
Desc1: This strangely-crafted device is made to ressemble a fish's
Desc2: head. Covering the mouth and nose is an airtight wooden
Desc3: device that hooks up to a small pack of sort on the back. It
Desc4: allows breathing of water, but only under extremely cold
Desc5: conditions. Somewhat fragile, it is not useful in combat
Desc6: situations.

Name: climbing harness
Desc1: This heavy leather harness is complete with hooks and rope.
Desc2: It is used by climbers to anchor themselves while climbing,
Desc3: and is invaluable when making the treacherous climbs up
Desc4: mountains.

Name: iron crown
Desc1: This light circlet is surprisingly finely-crafted, despite
Desc2: the fact it is only iron. An eye-sized amber stone set in
Desc3: its front glitters brightly.

Name: spectral sword
Desc1: This long, glowing blade is slender and sharp, and appears
Desc2: like it doesn't actually exist fully in this plane. It is
Desc3: a pale yellowish-white, with the hilt being white-gold.

Name: throne
Desc1: This large gilded throne appears to have been crafted for
Desc2: someone of large stature, as it is a little big even for a
Desc3: fully-grown man. The throne's arms are carved to ressemble
Desc4: lion's paws, and at the top of the throne is a glaring
Desc5: eagle's head, its beak open in a soundless shriek.

Name: patch of black mushrooms
Desc1: These small mushrooms are jet black in colour, and have a
Desc2: distinctly distasteful odour. Their stalks are long and
Desc3: spindly, their caps wide and thin.

Name: Eternal Fire
Desc1: This flaming ball burns with a bright, warm light that
Desc2: doesn't harm but is warm and comforting. Its radiance
Desc3: penetrates into every dark corner, and lifts the spirits
Desc4: just to see it.

Name: pickaxe
Desc1: This large tool has a heavy metal head, one side of which
Desc2: has a curved spike, the other sporting a broad axe-like
Desc3: blade. It is indispensible to miners, who use it to hack
Desc4: out the rock and then to break it up to expose the ore. It
Desc5: also makes a good weapon.

Name: mountain of rubble
Desc1: This gigantic cave-in has completely sealed the entrance to
Desc2: this cave. There is no apparent way out...

Name: Storm Spirit
Desc1: This small crystal sphere contains the essence of lightning.
Desc2: Swirling about inside as crackling arcs, which make the orb
Desc3: flash and spark wildly.

Name: mine pass
Desc1: This small wooden card is etched with the symbol of the
Desc2: Miner's Guild of Khazarad. Only people bearing this pass
Desc3: may enter the mines.

Name: copper ore
Desc1: This rough chunk of rock contains a large portion of copper.
Desc2: Somewhat valuable, copper is used in many everyday
Desc3: applications. Before the copper can be extracted from the
Desc4: ore, it must be smelted and the rock skimmed off the surface
Desc5: of the metal.

Name: silver ore
Desc1: This rough chunk of rock contains a large portion of silver.
Desc2: Fairly valuable, it is mainly used in jewlery and high-
Desc3: quality dishware. The ore must be smelted so that the silver
Desc4: can be extracted-- until then, it is nearly worthless.

Name: gold ore
Desc1: This rough chunk of rock contains a large portion of yellow
Desc2: gold. One of the most valuable metals around, gold is used
Desc3: in most jewelry and embellishments, and is a favourite of
Desc4: the dwarves. However, the ore is nearly worthless until it
Desc5: is smelted.

Name: iron ore
Desc1: This rough chunk of rock contains a large portion of iron.
Desc2: Useful in creating weaponry and eveyrday items, it can be
Desc3: refined to make steel. Before being usable, however, the
Desc4: iron must be extracted from the ore by smelting it.

Name: obsidian talisman
Desc1: This small, circular disk is heavily engraved with intricate
Desc2: runes, and emanates a strange aura of power. It is quite
Desc3: heavy for its size, and when touched makes the hair stand on
Desc4: end.

Name: Heartstone
Desc1: This heavy, glittering jewel is blood red in colour. It
Desc2: shines with a thousand facets, and is warm to the touch.

Name: gold signet ring
Desc1: This small golden ring is worn by heavy use, and bears a
Desc2: striking symbol on its face. Circular, with a skull and two
Desc3: crossed axes, the symbol is a mystery.

Name: cracked obelisk
Desc1: This tall, pointed obelisk is night-black and as smooth as
Desc2: glass. Intricate runes carved into its surface emanate a
Desc3: strange aura of power. A large crack runs down through it,
Desc4: however, and the emanation of energy fluctuates wildly,
Desc5: sending prickles running along your skin.

Name: runic key
Desc1: This key is inscribed with many strange, intelligible
Desc2: symbols that seem to writhe as you look at them.

Name: gleaming dagger
Desc1: This long, straight dagger glitters with an otherworldly
Desc2: bluish hue. It is made of a metal unknown to this land, and
Desc3: is both indestructible and razor-sharp.

Name: enchanted dagger
Desc1: This long, straight dagger glitters with an otherworldly
Desc2: bluish hue. It is made of a metal unknown to this land, and
Desc3: is both indestructible and razor-sharp.

Name: Spirit Dagger of Goijar
Desc1: This long, straight dagger glitters with an otherworldly
Desc2: bluish hue. It is made of a metal unknown to this land, and
Desc3: is both indestructible and razor-sharp. Glowing with a
Desc4: ghostly halo of spectral fire, this weapon is designed for a
Desc5: special purpose.

Name: golden chest
Desc1: This large, heavy chest is heavily embellished with
Desc2: intricate dwarven ornamentation. The symbol of King Kulgar
Desc3: is emblazoned on the lid, and it is obvious that it is full
Desc4: of valuables.

Name: adamantite chest
Desc1: This large, heavy chest is plainly decorated, but has been
Desc2: polished to a nearly mirrorlike shine. Silver studs lining
Desc3: its edges glimmer brightly, and it is obvious that the chest
Desc4: is full of valuables.

Name: black iron chest
Desc1: This large, heavy chest is made of black iron, which has
Desc2: been polished so that the container gleams like a beetle's
Desc3: carapace. A hideous demonic face has been carved into its
Desc4: lid, and it is obvious that the chest is full of valuables.

Name: Ice Tear
Desc1: This small, smooth object glitters like ice but is as hard
Desc2: as diamond. Bluish-white and cold, it radiates an aura of
Desc3: sorrow that is unmistakeable.

Name: small cloth pouch
Desc1: This is a dirty canvas bag, large enough to hold a few
Desc2: personal belongings.

Name: dirty parchment
Desc1: Inscribed on this parchment is a crude map, with sprawling
Desc2: text in a child-like hand:

Name: small black mushrooms
Desc1: These small mushrooms are jet black in colour, and have a
Desc2: distinctly distasteful odour. Their stalks are long and
Desc3: spindly, their caps wide and thin.

Name: bag of poison
Desc1: This small leather bag is filled with a lethal concoction
Desc2: of poisons.

Name: altar
Desc1: This bowl-shaped silver altar looks like it was once used
Desc2: to burn offerings or to provide light. It is permanently
Desc3: affixed to the shrine's marble floor, which is probably why
Desc4: it has not been stolen.

Name: acid gland
Desc1: This rubbery lump is covered with a thin layer of slime. It
Desc2: is pale white in colour, and has a distasteful smell faintly
Desc3: reminiscent of rotting flesh.

Name: golden hide tunic
Desc1: This heavy shirt is made out of a dense golden hide, which
Desc2: glitters beautifully in the light. It is covered in coarse,
Desc3: almost wirelike hairs of gold, and appears to have been
Desc4: bolted together with shining steel rivets.

Name: metal plate
Desc1: This square metal plate is somewhat larger than a human's
Desc2: hand-span, and is set in the side of the passageway's wall
Desc3: beside the dead-end.

Name: serrated scimitar
Desc1: This heavy, sawtoothed scimitar is engraved with harsh
Desc2: orcish runes. Its hilt and pommel are made of bone, worn
Desc3: dark with age.

Name: pig on a spit
Desc1: This is a fat, greasy, roasted pig impaled on a wooden spit.
Desc2: Slowly cooked over a fire, it is delicious but extremely
Desc3: fattening.

Name: roots
Desc1: These long, snaking roots are about an inch thick and are
Desc2: greenish-yellow in colour. Their aroma is quite pleasant,
Desc3: sweet and fragrant as flowers-- a strange find in these
Desc4: gloomy tunnels. A handful could be gotten with some small
Desc5: difficulty, by ripping or cutting them out.

Name: unfertilized eggs
Desc1: These half-dozen eggs are each about six inches long, and
Desc2: are pasty white in colour. They have a faint sweet smell and
Desc3: are a little sticky to the touch.

Name: bushes
Desc1: At first the bushes appear to dense to move through, and are
Desc2: definitely too hardy to chop up. However, after some
Desc3: searching, you find a small opening to the north which could
Desc4: be passed through.

Name: alder chest
Desc1: This large, iron-banded alder chest is nearly too heavy to
Desc2: move. Iron handles on its sides allow it to be carried, and
Desc3: whatever is inside rattles about noisily.

Name: steel key
Desc1: This large, shining key is well-crafted and seems to be used
Desc2: often. Stamped in its head is the shape of a roaring lion.

Name: skeleton key
Desc1: This small, fragile key appears to be made out of yellow
Desc2: bone. The handle is a rat's skull, with small glass marbles
Desc3: for eyes.

Name: statue
Desc1: This towering stone figure stands at least twenty feet tall.
Desc2: Crafted in the image of cloaked man, its features are
Desc3: shrouded in the depths of its hood, and its sleeves are
Desc4: rolled up to its elbows. Inscribed upon its base is an
Desc5: intricate text which can be deciphered upon closer
Desc6: inspection.

Name: text inscription
Desc1: "When the light be quenched and shadow falls upon the earth,
Desc2: the seas will boil, the sky will turn as red as blood, and
Desc3: the earth itself will crack and spew forth all-consuming
Desc4: flame. Then darkness will reign over the people of the
Desc5: land, and all shall bow before the Dark One and his dread
Desc6: lords."

Name: jade wave carving
Desc1: Beautifully crafted from a single block of jade, this
Desc2: sculpture is carved to ressemble a curved wave crashing down
Desc3: upon the rocks. It is affixed to the stone altar, but for
Desc4: some reason seems moveable.

Name: obsidian mountain carving
Desc1: This exquisite sculpture is carved to represent a jagged,
Desc2: treacherous mountain range. It is affixed to the stone altar
Desc3: upon which it sits, however it seems able to be moved
Desc4: slightly.

Name: white marble fog carving
Desc1: This beautifully-crafted sculpture depicts the intricate
Desc2: swirling details of a foggy cloud. Upon closer inspection,
Desc3: the fog carving appears able to be moved somewhat.

Name: sunstone flame carving
Desc1: This priceless sunstone sculpture is crafted to ressemble
Desc2: a single burning flame, each tiny lick picked out in
Desc3: exquisite detail. Although affixed to the stone altar, it
Desc4: appears able to be moved somewhat.

Name: titanium fork
Desc1: This shining, titanium device greatly resembles an oversized
Desc2: tuning fork, attached to a strange crystal-studded
Desc3: handle. Of gnomish manufacture, it is a queer device that
Desc4: only the brilliant gnome inventors could create.
Desc6: <Type AIM FORK WEST to use on a western wall, and so on.>

Name: tree
Desc1: This ancient darkwood tree must be hundreds of years old, if
Desc2: not millenia. Large enough in girth to house a village of
Desc3: people, this grandfather of trees is unparraleled in all of
Desc4: the land.

Name: door
Desc1: This large darkwood door is carved with elaborate swirling
Desc2: patterns and sigils. A silvery doorplate set in the upper
Desc3: middle of the door bears a single rune of warning.

Name: ivory statue
Desc1: This small ivory statue is crafted to ressemble a head with
Desc2: eight faces. Each face has one single glaring eye, each a
Desc3: different colour; one red, one orange, one yellow, one
Desc4: green, one blue, one violet, one black and one white.

Name: basalt key
Desc1: This black, porous stone key is indestructible despite its
Desc2: fragile appearance.

Name: brass knuckles
Desc1: These shining knuckles are gripped in the fist to increase
Desc2: punching damage. Though they provide little protection,
Desc3: they are definitely worthwhile if fists are the primary
Desc4: form of attack. Used mostly by mystics, they are limited in
Desc5: use to the more advanced practitioners.

Name: yellowed note
Desc1: This worn, tattered parchment is inscribed with a few
Desc2: straggling sentences, reading:

Name: smudged paper
Desc1: This small piece of paper has a few lines scribbled on it:
Desc3: "Still no way to get up waterfall. Shadow Fist brotherhood
Desc4: will not be pleased. Remember to send spy to gnome
Desc5: alchemist to see if any levitation potions available."

Name: potion of levitation
Desc1: This small glass vial has a bulbous round bottom, and is
Desc2: filled with a bubbling white liquid. Stamped on its cork is
Desc3: a pair of wings.

Name: waterfall
Desc1: The Silver river thunders down through a gaping hole in the
Desc2: ceiling of the cave here, pouring down into a turbulent
Desc3: pool.

Name: double-terminated quartz
Desc1: This is a six-inch piece of clouded quartz. It shines when
Desc2: light strikes it, refracting off of its many facets.

Name: cave roots
Desc1: These long, snaking roots are about an inch thick and are
Desc2: greenish-yellow in colour. Their aroma is quite pleasant,
Desc3: sweet and fragrant as flowers.

Name: magical quartz rod
Desc1: This short quartz rod pulses with a pale, spectral light.
Desc2: Its strange enchantment causes it to hum slightly, and it is
Desc3: warm to the touch.

Name: barrier
Desc1: This shimmering, nearly invisible barrier can only be seen
Desc2: by the slight opalescent ripples that occasionally break
Desc3: its surface. It covers the passageway to the north, and
Desc4: seems impenetrable.

Name: golden egg
Desc1: This large, heavy egg is warm to the touch, and glimmers
Desc2: beautifully in the light. Its surface is mirror-smooth and
Desc3: is completely unmarred.

Name: skull mask
Desc1: This large face-mask appears to be crafted from a human
Desc2: skull. Painted black and laquered, it is placed over the
Desc3: face and attached by a pair of thin leather straps so that
Desc4: it fits snugly. The eye socks glow faintly red, giving the
Desc5: wearer a demonic appearance.

Name: phoenix feather
Desc1: This brilliant golden feather burns with a fiery hue. Rare
Desc2: and priceless, feathers of the legendary phoenix are only
Desc3: ever found in the possession of those who have aided the
Desc4: creature in some way.

Name: mandible
Desc1: This long, unwieldly item is a jaw ripped from a giant sized
Desc2: insect. Razor-sharp, it can tear through armour with ease
Desc3: but it is difficult to wield.

Name: wire key
Desc1: This small key is made of a complex intertwining of steel
Desc2: wires.

Name: ruby ninjato
Desc1: This magnificent blade is amazing to behold. Fashioned from
Desc2: a collection of bright, crimson rubies, it is single edged,
Desc3: yet that edge could slice great wounds in any foe. An aura
Desc4: of heat seems to come from its jeweled surface, and runes
Desc5: of power have been etched into the stone. A mithril hilt
Desc6: has been fashioned as a claw, grasping the blade mightily.

Name: etched adamant broadsword
Desc1: This double-edged blade has been fashioned from adamant with
Desc2: masterful hands. The edge is very sharp and seems to move
Desc3: with great agility. Etched on the base of the blade are the
Desc4: ancient words "Morte o Mau".  No signs of magic are evident
Desc5: on this blade, from the blade to the leather that binds
Desc6: the hilt, or the pommel ends in a simple silver ball.

Name: antlered helm
Desc1: This is a rigid leather helm, with many druish runes painted
Desc2: on the crown and sides. Two large three-pointed antlers have
Desc3: been grafted to the helm, giving its wearer a fearsome
Desc4: visage.

Name: ancient scroll
Desc1: This ancient scroll holds cryptic writing within it, that
Desc2: seem glow with a dangerous power. They look to be runes of
Desc3: the magi upon its aged skin.

Name: ornate red key
Desc1: This key is made of solid steel, with complicated ridges
Desc2: from handle to end, indicating the lock probably belongs to
Desc3: a vault of some kind. It is painted a dark red and a single
Desc4: ruby is set in the head.

Name: adamantite chest
Desc1: This large, heavy chest is plainly decorated, but has been
Desc2: polished to a nearly mirrorlike shine. Silver studs lining
Desc3: its edges glimmer brightly, and it is obvious that the chest
Desc4: is full of valuables.

Name: orange key
Desc1: This key is made of plain iron and was not hard to
Desc2: manufacture. The ridges of the key are fairly simple telling
Desc3: you the lock is not that secure. It is painted bright
Desc4: orange, you can assume to match whatever house it belongs
Desc5: to.

Name: ornate orange key
Desc1: This key is made of solid steel, with complicated ridges
Desc2: from handle to end, indicating the lock probably belongs to
Desc3: a vault of some kind. It is painted dark orange and a single
Desc4: topaz is set in the head.

Name: topaz emblem
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCTOPAZ.EMB

Name: nexus blade
Desc1: This blade crackles with immense energy. Made from a strange
Desc2: silvery metal it glitters along the edge of the blade.
Desc3: The hilt is elaborately wrapped with a single piece of fine
Desc4: silk, which seems to cause the air around it to tingle with
Desc5: power. The entire sword hums and it seems desperate to be
Desc6: used in combat.

Name: yellow key
Desc1: This key is made of plain iron and was not hard to
Desc2: manufacture. The ridges of the key are fairly simple telling
Desc3: you the lock is not that secure. It is painted bright
Desc4: yellow, you can assume to match whatever house it belongs
Desc5: to.

Name: ornate yellow key
Desc1: This key is made of solid steel, with complicated ridges
Desc2: from handle to end, indicating the lock probably belongs to
Desc3: a vault of some kind. It is painted dark yellow and a single
Desc4: piece of amber is set in the head.

Name: amber emblem
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCAMBER.EMB

Name: ancient paper
Desc1: Almost tattered beyond recognition, this paper has been
Desc2: folded, unfolded, and mangled many times. You can see
Desc3: deep lines in the paper, where ink once was, but has now
Desc4: faded to mix with the dirt that has shaded this paper.

Name: green key
Desc1: This key is made of plain iron and was not hard to
Desc2: manufacture. The ridges of the key are fairly simple telling
Desc3: you the lock is not that secure. It is painted bright green,
Desc4: you can assume to match whatever house it belongs to.

Name: ornate green key
Desc1: This key is made of solid steel, with complicated ridges
Desc2: from handle to end, indicating the lock probably belongs to
Desc3: a vault of some kind. It is painted dark green and a single
Desc4: emerald is set in the head.

Name: ruby-encrusted bracers
Desc1: You hold a pair of intricately crafted bracers, made of a
Desc2: the purest mithril, found deep in the dwarven mines of
Desc3: Khazarad. Encrusted into the metal are many fine, medium
Desc4: sized rubies. The bracers seem to have a magical magnetism
Desc5: to them, and naturally pull towards each other. Engraved in
Desc6: black on the inside of the left bracer is the name: Cyan.

Name: gold key
Desc1: This key is made of plain iron and was not hard to

Name: blackened parchment
Desc1: Unrolling the parchment reveals a strange message written in
Desc2: crimson, almost unreadable letters.

Desc3: you the lock is not that secure. It is painted bright white,
Desc4: you can assume to match whatever house it belongs to.

Name: ornate white key
Desc1: This key is made of solid steel, with complicated ridges
Desc2: from handle to end, indicating the lock probably belongs to
Desc3: a vault of some kind. It is painted white and a single
Desc4: massive diamond is set in the head.
