Name: rotted tree
Desc1: This large, twisted tree stands here before you, hunkered
Desc2: down by disease and rot. It seems on the verge of collapse
Desc3: were it not for the numerous roots that still stick into the
Desc4: ground. A large hole surrouneded by mud and gunk is squarely
Desc5: below the plagued tree, leading below into places unknown.

Name: crimson spiked shield
Desc1: This is a medium sized shield has been fashioned from a
Desc2: form of insect chitin. A large flame has been painted on it,
Desc3: and a great spike protrudes from the center. Though heavy it
Desc4: offers some protection along with dealing damage to boot.

Name: sharktooth trident
Desc1: This heavy, two-handed weapon, is made of a most unusual
Desc2: material. Three jagged prongs covered in razor sharp teeth
Desc3: jut from a barnacle covered shaft of stone. The construction
Desc4: of the weapon and the barnacles make it somewhat unwieldy,
Desc5: but the sharp teeth that litter the prongs would seem to
Desc6: do enough damage to suffice.

Name: etched adamant warhammer
Desc1: This long-shafted warhammer has been crafted of purest
Desc2: adamant. The only markings are carved into the hammers head,
Desc3: "Destrua o Magia". The silvery hammer moves with great speed
Desc4: and can still deliver a crushing blow, knocking its oppenent
Desc5: to the ground. The long shaft of the hammer ends with a
Desc6: flame carved on the bottom, painted a bright crimson.

Name: etched adamant greatsword
Desc1: This massive sword can only be handled with two hands and
Desc2: could easily cleave a man in half. Crafted from fine adamant
Desc3: the blade has been sharpened to a keen edge. Carved with
Desc4: care on the base of the blade are the words "Perdere Magia".
Desc5: The hilt has been covered with rigid leather, and the pommel
Desc6: fashioned in the image of a star.

Name: Demon's Maw
Desc1: Rows of yellowed teeth line the blade of this hideous
Desc2: greataxe. Vile symbols line the blackened obsidian haft of
Desc3: the weapon, and they almost seem to reach for you. The
Desc4: smell of brimstone and burnt flesh is thick from this weapon
Desc5: and the heat that it radiates already cause you to perspire.
Desc6: Beastly hair has been tied in knots on the handle.

Name: runed petrified staff
Desc1: This twisted rock staff was once the branch of a bronzewood,
Desc2: however time has caused it to become unbreakable. Even still
Desc3: various black and brown runes glow from the staff, carved
Desc4: long ago, they still have a life to them giving the staff
Desc5: great magical power.

Name: burning staff
Desc1: An item of myth or mystery, this staff smells as if it were
Desc2: burning and yet you can see no fire. Grasping the staff
Desc3: however causes your hand to almost blister from the heat
Desc4: that erupts from the wood.  Lively golden symbols, scribed
Desc5: into the staff, move and sway to their own beat. Abruptly
Desc6: the staff begins to cool, allowing you to firmly grasp it.

Name: copperwood staff
Desc1: A piece of beautiful copperwood has been used to make this
Desc2: staff. Still full of life, this staff carries a strange
Desc3: numbness with it, and yet makes your skin tingle and your
Desc4: hair stand on end. Various knots stick out of the staff
Desc5: causing light to jump from knot to knot in random patterns.
Desc6: Magic radiates from this staff with great force.

Name: ice crystal staff
Desc1: Magic of great power is the only explanation for this staves
Desc2: existance. Pure ice has been carved and formed into a tall
Desc3: staff. Chills exude from this crystalline wonder, causing
Desc4: the skin on your arms to become a terrain of goose bumps.
Desc5: Near invisible sygils of silver have been carved into
Desc6: various parts of the staff, making its power more evident.

Name: dirty obsidian key
Desc1: A large key fashioned from obsidian has been caked with dust
Desc2: from its lack of use. You blow some of the dust away and
Desc3: realize some of the teeth have been blown away with it. The
Desc4: key appears to be totally worthless.

Name: ancient obsidian key
Desc1: A large key fashioned from obsidian shows immense age and
Desc2: use. It is very worn, and some of the teeth seem to have
Desc3: disappeared entirely, you are sure this key is totally
Desc4: worthless.

Name: flaming portal
Desc1: This oval rift in space pulsates with an evil, chaotic
Desc2: power. Negative energy leaks out and surrounds you, leaving
Desc3: you numb and trembling. Whatever lies beyond would be sure
Desc4: death for the weak, and difficult at best even for mighty
Desc5: heroes.

Name: shuriken
Desc1: This small steel disk has four razor-sharp blades protruding
Desc2: from its edge. It shines brightly from its polish and look
Desc3: ready to deal out damage.

Name: catoblepas eye
Desc1: This huge eyeball is about two feet in diameter, and glows
Desc2: with a greenish hue. Its is fairly heavy and cumbersome.

Name: flaming star
Desc1: This strange object appears to be a piece of magical fire,
Desc2: fashioned into a four pointed star. The heat is intense from
Desc3: this weapon, and it looks as though it would make a deadly
Desc4: projectile weapon.

Name: midnight glare
Desc1: Used traditionally this knife would most likely be the
Desc2: fastest weapon ever created, the blade however is not
Desc3: built well for this, designed specifically to be thrown
Desc4: at the opponent. This knives blade is about five inches
Desc5: long, and the handle about two inches. The blade is made
Desc6: of a strange blue metal that when held is nearly invisible.

Name: practice dummy
Desc1: This large stuffed dummy hangs from a wooden frame, and is
Desc2: used to test combat skills and weapons. It is mildly
Desc3: enchanted so that it can take a hearty beating and still
Desc4: remain intact.

Name: azure shamshir
Desc1: This long, curved sword is made out of an intense blue
Desc2: substance that appears to be glass. It is smooth and
Desc3: exceptionally well crafted, and the handle is made of
Desc4: carved ivory that is extremely comfortable.

Name: light ball
Desc1: This pale white ball radiates a bright light, but exudes no
Desc2: heat and is almost cold to touch. It seems light weight and
Desc3: almost looks as though it could float, keeping your way
Desc4: lighted until its magic expired.

Name: scroll of zeal
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: round table
Desc1: This massive oak table could easily seat forty people. It
Desc2: is well-crafted and inlaid with rosewood panels in an
Desc3: intricate spiralling pattern.

Name: bed
Desc1: This large, comfortable bed is simple in design, but
Desc2: sturdily crafted. A luxurious goose-down mattress insures
Desc3: a good night's rest.

Name: bookshelf
Desc1: This large, wide bookshelf is designed to hold a large
Desc2: number of books of varying size.

Name: long table
Desc1: This simple, sturdy table is similar to those found in most
Desc2: common rooms of taverns and inns. It is heavy and is built
Desc3: solely to last.

Name: wooden chair
Desc1: This elegant wooden chair is ornamented with simple curving
Desc2: designs. Built to last, it is commonly seen in most town
Desc3: houses.

Name: bench
Desc1: This long wooden bench is often seen accompanying the common
Desc2: tables in an inn. It is sturdily built from solid oak wood.

Name: desk
Desc1: This elegant desk has been painstakingly hand-crafted from
Desc2: a variety of precious woods, and is rarely seen outside
Desc3: mansions of the rich.

Name: cabinet
Desc1: Simple in design but otherwise pleasing to the eye, this
Desc2: large cabinet has a great amount of room for storing
Desc3: supplies.

Name: dresser
Desc1: This nicely-carved dresser has three drawers for holding
Desc2: clothing, and is carved out of a nice light pine wood.

Name: rug
Desc1: This beautifully-woven rug is decorated with angular
Desc2: designs in intricate patterns. Painstakingly handmade, it is
Desc3: a treasure to own.

Name: tournament badge
Desc1: This small, bloodstained iron badge is a symbol proving
Desc2: once's participation in a Tournament battle. It has
Desc3: obviously seen much use.

Name: crimson badge
Desc1: This fearsome-looking badge is hammered out of heavy red
Desc2: metal. Crafted to ressemble a clawed fist, it is only worn
Desc3: by the highest-ranking orc in a war band.

Name: black badge
Desc1: This heavy iron badge is crafted in the shape of a clawed
Desc2: fist. It is commonly seen on high-ranking leaders in an orc
Desc3: war band.

Name: orc-head
Desc1: This bloody head once belonged to a foul, vicious orc. Now
Desc2: its blank eyes stare out dully in death, and ichor leaks
Desc3: from its ruined neck.

Name: iron badge
Desc1: This heavy iron badge is crafted in the shape of a clawed
Desc2: fist. It is commonly seen on the low-ranking leaders of the
Desc3: band who command only a few orcs.

Name: glass orb
Desc1: This small glass orb is beautifully-made, and sparkles
Desc2: mysteriously in the light.

Name: crystal orb
Desc1: This small crystal orb is beautifully-made, and sparkles
Desc2: mysteriously in the light.

Name: granite orb
Desc1: This small granite orb is beautifully-made, and quite smooth
Desc2: to the touch.

Name: marble orb
Desc1: This small marble orb is beautifully-made, and quite smooth
Desc2: to the touch.

Name: ashwood wand
Desc1: This long, slender ashwood wand is smoothly carved, and is
Desc2: engraved with arcane silvery runes.

Name: teak wand
Desc1: This long, slender teak wand is smoothly carved, and is
Desc2: engraved with arcane silvery runes.

Name: mahogany wand
Desc1: This long, slender mahogany wand is smoothly carved, and is
Desc2: engraved with arcane silvery runes.

Name: pine wand
Desc1: This long, slender pine wand is smoothly carved, and is
Desc2: engraved with arcane silvery runes.

Name: darkwood rod
Desc1: This heavy darkwood rod is about two feet long, and is
Desc2: covered in all manner of swirling symbols.

Name: silverwood rod
Desc1: This heavy silverwood rod is about two feet long, and is
Desc2: covered in all manner of swirling symbols.

Name: rosewood rod
Desc1: This heavy rosewood rod is about two feet long, and is
Desc2: covered in all manner of swirling symbols.

Name: birch rod
Desc1: This heavy birch rod is about two feet long, and is
Desc2: covered in all manner of swirling symbols.

Name: cedar rod
Desc1: This heavy cedar rod is about two feet long, and is
Desc2: covered in all manner of swirling symbols.

Name: shadow material
Desc1: This strange wispy fragment weighs nothing, and seems to
Desc2: fade in and out of view. It has an unpleasant feel to it.

Name: holy water vial
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with pure, clean water. A
Desc2: stopper keeps its contents inside, and you see a single
Desc3: holy symbol inscribed upon it.

Name: summoning bone
Desc1: This long, smooth bone radiates pure evil. Used by powerful
Desc2: necromancers to trap the souls of the living and force them
Desc3: into an undead state, it is a tool of the netherworld and
Desc4: should be destroyed.

Name: honeycakes
Desc1: These small, round delights are sweetened with honey, and
Desc2: are the primary dessert for the peoples of this area. They
Desc3: are as nutritious as they are delicious.

Name: mulled wine
Desc1: This small wooden cup is filled with a quantity of strong,
Desc2: heated wine.

Name: cup of tea
Desc1: This small wooden cup is filled with a fragrant spicy tea,
Desc2: whose aroma stimulates the senses.

Name: palm tree
Desc1: This tall, slender tree is topped with long, jagged green
Desc2: leaves, and bears a cluster of round brown fruit.

Name: shimmering pool
Desc1: This wide, deep pool is filled with a cool, crystal clear
Desc2: water. It darkens somewhat towards the centre.

Name: angular key
Desc1: This beautifully-crafted brass key is quite large and
Desc2: heavy. It head is cut with an angular geometric design.

Name: three-toothed key
Desc1: This long, heavy key has a strange construction-- three
Desc2: oddly-formed teeth jut out from its barrel instead of the
Desc3: usual one.

Name: well
Desc1: This well is filled with a brackish, muddy water that would
Desc2: probably not be healthy to drink.

Name: basalt obelisk
Desc1: This towering stone obelisk is engraved with geometric
Desc2: symbols, and is topped with a black capstone. At eye-level,
Desc3: two lines in an ancient language read:

Name: basalt obelisk
Desc1: This towering stone obelisk is engraved with geometric
Desc2: symbols, and is topped with a black capstone. At eye-level,
Desc3: two lines in an ancient language read:

Name: basalt obelisk
Desc1: This towering stone obelisk is engraved with geometric
Desc2: symbols, and is topped with a black capstone. At eye-level,
Desc3: two lines in an ancient language read:

Name: mummified miner
Desc1: The twisted shape of a dead miner lays here in a corner.
Desc2: Mummified by the heat and dryness, his face remains forever
Desc3: locked in a horrible soundless scream. His legs have been
Desc4: crushed beneath a heavy sandstone boulder. One of his arms
Desc5: is outstretched, and sitting on the ground a few feet away
Desc6: from his clawlike hand is a tattered leather pouch.

Name: red iron key
Desc1: This short, heavy key is made of a deep-red metal, and is
Desc2: somewhat crudely made.

Name: black altar
Desc1: The black altar is large enough that a large human would
Desc2: easily fit upon its surface. Ancient bloodstains can be seen
Desc3: encrusted upon it. The glaring eye engraved on the altar
Desc4: fairly radiates evil, and has an odd, smooth construction.

Name: copper amulet
Desc1: This small, round amulet is crudely stamped with a symbol
Desc2: representing a roaring lion. It hangs on a heavy chain.

Name: stone hand
Desc1: This is a stone carving of a gnarled, inhuman hand. Its
Desc2: fingers are splayed as if ready to claw at someone.

Name: jeweled altar
Desc1: This large golden altar would bring a fortune if it were
Desc2: melted down, but it is far too massive to move. Embedded in
Desc3: its surface in a circle are many gems: an amethyst, a
Desc4: diamond, and emerald, an onyx, a pearl, a ruby, a sapphire
Desc5: and a topaz.

Name: saracen head
Desc1: This severed head is quite revolting. And it stinks. The
Desc2: desert raiders are apparently not big on personal hygiene.

Name: moon-lamp
Desc1: This intricate creation is an invention of the desert-
Desc2: dwelling Nekojin. It is a specially-enchanted crystal orb,
Desc3: which when exposed to the moon's rays captures this light
Desc4: and radiates it. It is held in a wooden box, much like a
Desc5: lantern.

Name: heavy box
Desc1: This large box is stamped on one side with the Tolgard's
Desc2: trader symbol. It is difficult to tell what is contained
Desc3: within, as the contents are carefully packed to avoid
Desc4: breakage.

Name: tiger-claw necklace
Desc1: Long, perfect tiger claws, covered with golden runes, hang
Desc2: from the platinum chain of this necklace. It seems to hum
Desc3: slightly, and feels oddly light.

Name: silvery scroll
Desc1: This thin scroll is made of hammered silver, and is
Desc2: imprinted with ancient characters. It radiates an aura of
Desc3: power that is unmistakeable.

Name: jeweled turban
Desc1: This elaborate headpiece is made of bright red silk and
Desc2: glittering gold. A sapphire the size of an egg is set in the
Desc3: headband, and sparkles with an unnatural light.

Name: shelf
Desc1: This small shelf is quite bare, apart from two large,
Desc2: ancient-looking books. One of the books has a bright-red
Desc3: cover, and has small pages, but hundreds of them. The other
Desc4: is bound with blue cloth, and is slim, but the pages and
Desc5: cover are at least twice the size of the other.

Name: dwarven ale
Desc1: This is a large, heavy wooden mug filled with the strongest
Desc2: alcohol known in the realm-- dwarven mushroom ale. It has
Desc3: a bitter bite to it, and easily knocks non-dwarves off of
Desc4: their feet.

Name: red iron ore
Desc1: This dense metal is blood-red, and is extremely hard, with
Desc2: an almost oily sheen. The chunk of ore is about the size of
Desc3: someone's head, and is very heavy.

Name: red iron axe
Desc1: This heavy, one-handed axe is short-hafted and has a single
Desc2: blade shaped like a half moon. It is crafted from a dark
Desc3: red metal, that shimmers with an oily sheen. A fine example
Desc4: of quality dwarven handiwork.

Name: red iron hammer
Desc1: This heavy warhammer has a broad striking head that can
Desc2: easily beat down the target. It is made of a strange, blood-
Desc3: red metal, which shimmers with an oily sheen. The weapon is
Desc4: a good example of quality dwarven handiwork.

Name: red iron dagger
Desc1: This long, heavy dagger is practically the size of a
Desc2: shortsword. Its blade is razor-sharp, and is made from an
Desc3: odd blood-red metal that shimmers with an oily sheen. The
Desc4: weapon is a great example of typical dwarven handiwork.

Name: worn stone tablet
Desc1: This ancient stone tablet is engraved with arcane runes,
Desc2: detailing the methods and practice of druidic magic!

Name: papyrus scroll
Desc1: This ancient, crumbling scroll is made from a coarse-grained
Desc2: papyrus plant. Printed on its surface in faded ink is a holy
Desc3: prayer.

Name: khopesh sword
Desc1: This is an end-heavy sword, with a slight forward curve. It
Desc2: is large and heavy, and does considerable damage in combat.
Desc3: It is a little unwieldly and slow.

Name: two-headed pike
Desc1: This long, unwieldly polearm has razor-sharp pike blades at
Desc2: both ends. Difficult to use for the novice warrior, it can
Desc3: be a deadly weapon in the hands of a strong, large
Desc4: opponent.

Name: golden pike
Desc1: This large, heavy weapon is crafted from a glittering gold
Desc2: that seems harder than steel. It has two pike-heads, one at
Desc3: each end, with black blades that can cut through steel with
Desc4: ease.

Name: hydra key
Desc1: This large stone key's head is shaped to ressemble the
Desc2: hideous serpentine form of a hydra.

Name: meteorite rod
Desc1: This three-foot rod is crafted from one of the few metals
Desc2: available in the desert-- meteorite ore. Heavy and ornately
Desc3: engraved, it is curved around at the end like a cane. It is
Desc4: a symbol of the pharaoh's eternal rule, and feels warm to
Desc5: the touch.

Name: golden headdress
Desc1: This elaborate gilded headdress is typically worn by the
Desc2: royalty of the desert peoples-- specifically, the pharaoh.
Desc3: It consists of a tiara-like crown of gold, crafted to
Desc4: ressemble a rearing serpent. Bands of fine gilded cloth hang
Desc5: down from the crown, and lay over the shoulders of the
Desc6: wearer.

Name: crescent moon staff
Desc1: This long, beautiful staff is crafted out of a hardwood with
Desc2: a deep blue-grey colour. Carved along its length is a
Desc3: winding pattern highlighted with silver. It is capped with
Desc4: a silver crescent moon, the points facing outwards, which is
Desc5: engraved with extremely fine letters that glitter in the
Desc6: light.

Name: golden lion key
Desc1: This small, heavy gold key's head is crafted to ressemble a
Desc2: roaring lion. It is smooth and warm to the touch.

Name: spiked obsidian collar
Desc1: This heavy, glittering collar is crafted from unnaturally
Desc2: hard obsidian. Short, sharp spikes jut out of its surface
Desc3: at refgular intervals, and gleam wickedly in the light.

Name: rainbow stone
Desc1: This small, beautiful gem is shaped like a bird's egg, and
Desc2: glows with a soft light. Its colour slowly cycles through
Desc3: rainbow's hues in an almost hypnotic fashion. It is hung
Desc4: upon a fine platinum chain, to be worn about the neck.

Name: sculpture
Desc1: This odd stone construct is quite smooth, and appears to
Desc2: have been polished-- it has an almost mirrorlike sheen.
Desc3: Multicoloured crystals embedded in its surface flash and
Desc4: pulse with a haunting rhythm. There is a gap in the side,
Desc5: which may allow entrance inside.

Name: inscribed leather scroll
Desc1: This worn writ instructs the reader in the holy incantations
Desc2: required to cast a powerful healing spell. It makes no sense
Desc3: to anyone other than a devoted Priest.

Name: sunstone wristband
Desc1: This thin gold wristband is etched with intricate spiral
Desc2: patterns. Set into its surface are many small, circular
Desc3: sunstones, which shine orange-red in the light.

Name: silverbark canoe
Desc1: This small, beautiful canoe is made of carefully-cured and
Desc2: waterproofed silverwood bark. Of elven make, it is virtually
Desc3: unsinkable in shallow waters and is very light.

Name: barbed spear
Desc1: This long, sturdy spear has been crafted out of a tough
Desc2: swamp tree. Its head is made of sharp steel, hooked and
Desc3: barbed to cause painful injury.

Name: severed head of Irikani
Desc1: Even in death, her visage is one of pure evil, and her
Desc2: devlish eyes follow you, giving you an ill feeling in the
Desc3: pit of your stomach. Her hair is coarse and almost burning
Desc4: to touch, and droplets of crimson occasionaly drop from the
Desc5: head, splashing on the ground with a smell of sulphur.

Name: curved fang
Desc1: This four-inch fang belonged to some great beast of a
Desc2: poisonous nature. It is black and hollow, and you can tell
Desc3: that there is some liquid inside that sloshes when you
Desc4: shake it.

Name: spider silk trousers
Desc1: These trousers appear made of some incredibly fine silk.
Desc2: When you touch the cloth it seems as if a million tiny
Desc3: strands of a fine fabric form each thread, and the stitching
Desc4: appears made of some golden fabric, each one appearing to
Desc5: form a sparkling rune.

Name: bone necklace
Desc1: Bones of all shapes are thread together by a single green
Desc2: vine, tied at the back. Each one seems to rattle on their
Desc3: own volition, causing you to think that they might be
Desc4: imbued with some magic power.

Name: dented wizard's hat
Desc1: This pointed hat is decades old, and from the dirt you
Desc2: wonder if it has ever been washed. Despite the grime you
Desc3: see many stars and magic runes running along it's length
Desc4: and along the brim. You note some of the stains would
Desc5: indicate the last owner had befallen tragedy.

Name: net
Desc1: This net is crafted from the vines of a strange plant that
Desc2: grows near the tasloi village. It is perfect size and weight
Desc3: to carry comfortably and toss easily. It is also perfect
Desc4: size to entrap a man.

Name: javelin
Desc1: This long wooden pole runs six feet in length. Vine is
Desc2: used as a grip in the middle of the pole, and the ends
Desc3: have been carved into several fine points,
Desc4: causing great agony to it's victim.

Name: stone javelin
Desc1: This long stone pole runs seven feet in length. You can
Desc2: not tell if it is chiseled stone, or petrified wood,
Desc3: but regardless it feels very sturdy. The pole has a
Desc4: sharp point at each end.

Name: mithril plate leggings
Desc1: This pair of leggings are made of the purest mithril,
Desc2: shining brightly in the light. They appear very heavy,
Desc3: but are surprisingly light when you pick them up. You
Desc4: can tell from the craftsmanship that they were
Desc5: fashioned by a master-smith.

Name: mithril chain leggings
Desc1: Several very tiny chain links, are all woven together
Desc2: to form an almost impenetrable pair of leggings. You
Desc3: can tell by their shine that they've been made of
Desc4: dwarven mithril, and wonder if they belonged to some
Desc5: lord or powerful warrior.

Name: wyvernhide pants
Desc1: These thick leather trousers are made from the hide of
Desc2: some reptilian beast. The brown scales are incredibly
Desc3: durable, and you can tell they provide protection that
Desc4: would rival the thickest animal hide.

Name: black leather leggings
Desc1: This pair of leather leggings is made from a glossy black
Desc2: leather which seems to absorb the surrounding light. It does
Desc3: not weigh much at all, and is very flexible.

Name: chameleon leggings
Desc1: You can tell by the ways the leggings change shade that they
Desc2: were made from the skin of some color changing beast. They
Desc3: feel extremely comfortable and look like they can afford
Desc4: ample protection.

Name: red chitin leggings
Desc1: These bizarre leggings appear to have been made out of the
Desc2: shell plates from some gigantic red crustacean. They are
Desc3: tied together by some glowing vines of some sort, and it
Desc4: appears to have been treated with some mixture that gives
Desc5: it a fine sheen.

Name: red chitin helm
Desc1: This red helmet has been made out of the head plate of
Desc2: some monster crustacean. It feels very durable for its
Desc3: slight weight, but the two holes left from the eye
Desc4: stalks still remind you of its origin.

Name: red chitin armour
Desc1: This red suit of armour is made up of several shells of
Desc2: some massive crab-creature. It feels incredibly tough
Desc3: and has been tied together by several glowing vines,
Desc4: and they seem to have been treated with some strange
Desc5: mixture that makes it give off a glow.

Name: red chitin shield
Desc1: This strange shield looks to be crafted from the red
Desc2: chitin of some large sea-monster. They are interlocked
Desc3: together and tied by some strange glowing vines. It is
Desc4: very light and you wonder if any weapon could pierce
Desc5: its surface.

Name: sapling longbow
Desc1: This slender bow is made out of the sapling of some
Desc2: outlandish forest. The string used is a single glowing
Desc3: vine, that is tightly wound to the ends of the bow. It
Desc4: comes with a quiver full of similar sapling-like
Desc5: arrows, feathered together with a tree-leaf.

Name: bloodstained chakram
Desc1: Red stains cover this circlet of strange metal, and as you
Desc2: grab it you feel an intense sense of evil. Black runes seem
Desc3: to pulsate from the large circle, and you wonder what evil
Desc4: deeds it has done. Much smaller then a regular sized chakram
Desc5: it is small enough to use for stealthy attacks.

Name: bronze chakram
Desc1: A razor-sharp bronze circle, which when hurled, flies out
Desc2: and returns to its wielder.  The blade is three inches wide,
Desc3: with the weapon being one foot in diameter.

Name: ethereal chakram
Desc1: This circle is made of some strange glass-like material,
Desc2: with strange smokey runes radiating from its edges. As you
Desc3: look at the circlet closer it seems like some shifting cloud
Desc4: is inside.

Name: giant spiked collar
Desc1: This collar is crafted from hard leather and appears to have
Desc2: belonged to some giant animal. On its lowest fastening, you
Desc3: think you could probably make it fit. Its sharp spikes are
Desc4: wickedly curved, and anyone wearing this would definitely
Desc5: look cruel and menacing.

Name: fur-lined pouch
Desc1: This pouch fastens around your waist like a belt, except
Desc2: it's two sizes too big.  Upon opening you see many bits of
Desc3: bone, wood and herb inside, it obviously belongs to someone
Desc4: schooled in witch doctoring.

Name: gargantuan stone maul
Desc1: This looks like a gigantic rock with a metal shaft coming
Desc2: out of it.  The head is two feet in diameter, and is very
Desc3: heavy.  It is so massive you have a hard time lifting it off
Desc4: the ground.  You try a couple of practice swings and the
Desc5: weight almost takes your arms off.

Name: giantwood club
Desc1: This was obviously a tree branch of some thousand year old
Desc2: tree before it was fashioned into a rough club.  It is
Desc3: gigantic in size and would have to have belonged to a huge
Desc4: monster. It is six feet in length, you could barely lift it
Desc5: yourself, however you can tell anything struck with this
Desc6: would have to take a step back or be flattened.

Name: lionskin belt
Desc1: This fine belt was made from the hide of some animal and
Desc2: then tanned. It feels very thick, and is buckled with a
Desc3: piece of gold, finely crafted into the image of a lion.  It
Desc4: is heavy to wear around your waist, but still makes a nice
Desc5: fit.

Name: lionskin tunic
Desc1: This tunic is made of dyed animal skin, tanned to a golden
Desc2: brown. The center is inlaid with a finely crafted symbol of
Desc3: a lion. From the feel of the tunic it's very hard to pierce,
Desc4: and the lining is made from a fine fur. The craftsmanship
Desc5: looks a little clumsy, but still durable in a fight.

Name: great spiked club
Desc1: A great stone club with huge spikes, it is a weapon in the
Desc2: crudest fashion. Gigantic in size, it could be stood on its
Desc3: end and be taller than most men.  Anyone who could even
Desc4: wield this would be a force to be reckoned with.

Name: petrified stone corselet
Desc1: A gigantic piece of stone makes up this "corselet".  It is
Desc2: roughly chiseled to look like plate armor, but that doesn't
Desc3: change that it's still a massive piece of rock. It would
Desc4: fend off just about any attack on your torso, you only to
Desc5: worry about the rest of your body when wearing this
Desc6: massive chest protector.

Name: stormmetal greataxe
Desc1: This is a massive, long-handled axe. The double blades are
Desc2: made of a bizzare metal that gives off a blueish tinge as
Desc3: white lightning runs up and down the razor-like edge. As you
Desc4: grasp the handle it gives you a slight shock, and it seems
Desc5: to give off an odd hum as it weaves through the air.

Name: stormmetal scalemail tunic
Desc1: This entire suit is enchanting to behold, the metal lights
Desc2: up all over with lightning, giving the entire suit a
Desc3: blueish tinge. The circles of metal are all tightly woven
Desc4: together to make a hard-to-pierce suit. You note the suit
Desc5: was worn by a very large man as you put it on and have to
Desc6: adjust the straps to fit your smaller frame.

Name: stormmetal bracers
Desc1: A pair of armbands made from a bizzare metal, with a
Desc2: lightning charge running along the length of the bracers
Desc3: giving it a blueish tinge. The metal is incredibly sturdy,
Desc4: etched in runes of some strange language of power. The
Desc5: bracers are oversized but will still fit.

Name: storm crown
Desc1: This is a large circlet finely-crafted in some strange
Desc2: metal. The air crackles with the lightning that circulates
Desc3: all around the crown. A massive sapphire is set in the front
Desc4: of the crown. Upon closer inspection there appears to be a
Desc5: thundercloud hidden deep in the gem.

Name: titanic stone maul
Desc1: This huge maul is made up by a great eight foot rod, topped
Desc2: by a large stone ball. Incredibly difficult to lift, it is
Desc3: very slow to wield, but anything it hits will be crushed by
Desc4: its massive weight. A great weapon for only the strongest
Desc5: combatant, you see by the stains on the stone that it's
Desc6: already found many victims.

Name: beaded belt
Desc1: This belt is made of several coloured beads, woven together
Desc2: with several tiny vines. You can not tell if the glow of
Desc3: the belt comes from the beads or the vines, but a strange
Desc4: warm feeling seems to radiate with each glow.

Name: silver belt
Desc1: This brightly shining belt is made of a single massive band
Desc2: of silvery metal. Green runes adorn the buckle, and they
Desc3: seem to give off their own light.

Name: ogre bone bracelet
Desc1: Strange magical runes dot the length of the leather thong
Desc2: that holds together the bones of a monstrous ogre.

Name: shadow bracelet
Desc1: This dark black bracelet is made of an odd leather than
Desc2: seems to eat at the surrounding light. Running your finger
Desc3: along it gives you a strange cool feeling.

Name: thief's pouch
Desc1: This tiny, leather pouch attachs to the wrist, providing
Desc2: easy access to the tools of a thief which jingle inside.

Name: witchwood bracelet
Desc1: This bracelet is crafted from the magically-grown
Desc2: witchwood tree. Exotic runes are precisely placed in
Desc3: intervals along the band. It feels strangely warm to the
Desc4: touch and you feel a harmony with nature.

Name: mithril bracelets
Desc1: This pair of finely crafted metal is made of dwarven
Desc2: mithril. They are snug fitting and cover your wrists, almost
Desc3: reaching your elbows. The left is adorned with black
Desc4: etchings, and the right hand is detailed in white.

Name: silverwood lute
Desc1: This lute is definitely a rare find, for it is made of the
Desc2: sacred silverwood tree. It glows brightly from the symbols
Desc3: engraved on it, and the strings seems to play a musical tune
Desc4: themselves.

Name: blackwood staff
Desc1: This long staff is made of a thick black wood that feels
Desc2: cold to the touch. Etched upon its length are vile runes
Desc3: that glow a dark red color. You get a sickly feeling in the
Desc4: pit of your stomach when you run your fingers along the
Desc5: letters.

Name: black leather belt
Desc1: This leather belt is made of a glossy black leather which
Desc2: seems to absorb the surrounding light. It does not weigh
Desc3: much at all, and is very flexible.

Name: dark hood
Desc1: This hood is made of some type of black velvet-like cloth.
Desc2: When worn nothing can be seen of the wearer's face. Dark
Desc3: blue runes annoint the brim of this hood, and you get the
Desc4: feeling this item is not for the good of heart.

Name: runed longbow
Desc1: This slender, curved bow is made of some strange dark wood.
Desc2: Bright, glowing runes are burned all over the wood from tip
Desc3: to tip. The tight string that runs down appears to be made
Desc4: of some strange silk but pulls back as if it were the
Desc5: strongest cord. A quiver of arrows, also made of the same
Desc6: darkened wood, come with the bow, their tips a dull red.

Name: shimmering sash
Desc1: This is a six-foot long shimmering silken sash, worn around
Desc2: the waist. It seems to glow and pulsate with its own light.
Desc3: You can just make out runes sewn in some tupe of gold thread
Desc4: but you are forced to look away by the light.

Name: skull-capped staff
Desc1: This six-foot long staff is made of some type of yellowed
Desc2: wood. It almost appears to be rotting until you feel how
Desc3: sturdy it is. On the top of the staff is a grinning human
Desc4: skull, with two red points of light seeming to come from its
Desc5: eyeless sockets.

Name: trollskin boots
Desc1: This pair of boots is well-crafted from the skin of a large
Desc2: troll. They come up to the knee and feel comfortable enough,
Desc3: but it's still hard to grapple with the idea of wearing the
Desc4: skin of a troll.

Name: scaled lantern
Desc1: A small wiry stock holds this strong smelling lantern at
Desc2: arms length. Scales and bone house a small, but bright,
Desc3: glowing ball, which radiates a greenish light.

Name: glowing pearl
Desc1: Suprisingly heavy for such a small object, this pearl
Desc2: radiates a light from within.

Name: giant crab shell
Desc1: This chitinous shell looks to be well worn. Dents and scuffs
Desc2: scar the surface, but it still seems very well suited for
Desc3: protective purposes.

Name: ruby earrings
Desc1: The rubies used to make this pair of earrings have been set
Desc2: into a white gold backing. They have been shaped into roses.
Desc3: The petals are so well defined, it must have taken hours to
Desc4: complete each. At the base of each one is a tiny pair of
Desc5: emeralds, in the shape of leaves.

Name: mithril earrings
Desc1: Tiny rings of mithril have been linked together to form a
Desc2: circular pattern. Looking closely you see that one has a
Desc3: small dent in it, and realize they have been worn before.

Name: diamond earrings
Desc1: These tiny diamonds are set into a thin gold backing. They
Desc2: sparkle brightly without catching the light, and give off a
Desc3: humming sound so soft that you can barely hear it even while
Desc4: wearing them.

Name: sparkling pendant
Desc1: A silver star shaped necklace with gems set into each of the
Desc2: points. The metal is buffed to a high sheen, and the gems
Desc3: sparkle with a life of their own. Looking closely you notice
Desc4: the gems seem to slowly shift colors.

Name: icy scroll
Desc1: This scroll is tinged blue and tied by a bright blue ribbon.
Desc2: It seems to let off a vapor of some sort, and as you touch
Desc3: it, your whole body begins to shiver, as if an arctic wind
Desc4: blew down on you.

Name: cosmic staff
Desc1: This long, slender staff shimmers under the glow of diffused
Desc2: starlight. Glittering sparks encircling it spin about madly,
Desc3: flashing brightly and emitting high-pitched noises. The
Desc4: power of the cosmos is imbued within this staff, which, when
Desc5: tapped, provides arcane strength.

Name: starhammer
Desc1: This beautiful weapon seems to be made out of pure light
Desc2: from the stars, glowing radiantly and shimmering. It hums
Desc3: with arcane power and feels warm to the touch.

Name: severed earth dragon claw
Desc1: This dismembered claw is the shriveled, dead remains of some
Desc2: massive dragon. Its skin was once the color of soil, but in
Desc3: withered form it has blackened some. Five decayed fingers
Desc4: jut out to end in five very sharp nails. It looks like an
Desc5: awkward, but usable weapon.

Name: quest token
Desc1: A token signifying you have completed a quest, turn this in
Desc2: to the proper person and receive your prize.

Name: deathcoil
Desc1: This long, metallic whip has tiny sharp protrusions along
Desc2: its length, designed to lacerate the target. Its heavy grip
Desc3: is bound in a strange grey leather and it almost seems to
Desc4: move with a life of its own!

Name: deathblade
Desc1: This long blade is made of pure black metal and is extremely
Desc2: cold to the touch. Its overpowering evil aura almost seems
Desc3: to drain the life from you.

Name: naginata
Desc1: A lightweight 6-foot long pole wiht a curved blade on the
Desc2: end. The naginata reminds you of a halberd, but is lighter
Desc3: and easier to maneuver in combat. The pole is made from some
Desc4: unrecognizeable wood. It is thick and sturdy, but very
Desc5: light. The blade at the end is long enough that it could
Desc6: easily have been crafted into a sword instead.

Name: kote
Desc1: These armoured sleeves connect behind your shoulders with a
Desc2: thick strip of leather. They are made from tiny metal plates
Desc3: stitched together with a coarse black thread, and an
Desc4: intricate camouflage pattern has been painted on the them.
Desc6: plates.

Name: manriki-gusari
Desc1: You see a length of black chain with weights at each end.
Desc2: The manriki-gusari is easily thrown at your opponent's
Desc3: ankles for tripping and hindering retreat. Used at the
Desc4: correct time, it can give you the upper hand in combat. The
Desc5: length of the chain is just right for tying about your waist
Desc6: and concealing it beneath a belt or sash.

Name: gunsen
Desc1: This compact shield folds out quickly into a large iron fan.
Desc2: It is ideal for deflecting blows in close combat, and then
Desc3: snapping shut to give extra room for a counter blow. Ornate
Desc4: lettering lines each partition, unfolding into a haiku about
Desc5: death.

Name: tonfa
Desc1: The tonfa consists of a long, thick rod made from hardwood
Desc2: and a handle that juts out about a third of the way down the
Desc3: shaft. Used in the hands of a trained ninja, it can be used
Desc4: to effectively break an opponent's weapon, leaving him
Desc5: vulnerable to your attack.

Name: twin shortswords
Desc1: A pair of shortswords, specially crafted for the
Desc2: ambidextrous. There are matching symbols carved down the
Desc3: sides of the blades.

Name: webbed gauntlets
Desc1: This pair of once leather only gauntlets has been fused with
Desc2: think, but very light webbing. The added protection from the
Desc3: webbing in no way restricts the movement of the wearer, as
Desc4: the leather and webbing mix is completely flexible.

Name: bloodstained broadsword
Desc1: This razor-sharp blade is over three feet in length. The
Desc2: metal of the blade and hilt is a deep gray color and doesn't
Desc3: look familiar. Each edge of the blade looks to be
Desc4: permenently stained with blood and a single glowing crimson
Desc5: rune lines the pommel.

Name: ball of webbing
Desc1: This thick ball of webbing is remarkable light and pliable.
Desc2: It looks as if it would make a decent projectile.

Name: leaf blade
Desc1: This seems to be half of a large leaf forming a perfect
Desc2: semicircle. Amazingly rigid for a leaf, the rounded edge is
Desc3: sharper than most blades made of metal.  No handholds appear
Desc4: along the flat edge which makes it awkward for anyone to
Desc5: wield.

Name: giant pearl
Desc1: This pearl is large enough to take both your hands to lift.
Desc2: It's not necessarily heavy, but awkward to lift. The
Desc3: milky-white color reflects rainbow colors in the light.

Name: glowing vine
Desc1: This is roughly a six foot length of thick jungle vine.
Desc2: These plants grow near the Tasloi village and have a soft
Desc3: glow about them. You recognize that the tasloi nets are
Desc4: probably crafted from these vines. The material is sturdy
Desc5: and could be used for a number of purposes.

Name: spider silk robes
Desc1: These robes have been beautifully crafted from the silk of
Desc2: giant spiders. They drape comfortably about your body, and
Desc3: give off a sort of warm feeling. You see a soft rainbow
Desc4: effect when it catches the light.

Name: feathered key
Desc1: The hard thick shafts of bird's feathers have been shaped
Desc2: into the odd semblance of a key. There are no strings or
Desc3: glue, and you can only assume they are held together by
Desc4: magic.

Name: chiseled key
Desc1: This key was chiseled from hard volcanic rock. The edges of
Desc2: the handle are rough and unpolished. The key portion has
Desc3: been smoothed down to fit a lock properly.

Name: magma key
Desc1: Magma was dripped into a mold and slowly cooled to form this
Desc2: key. It is small enough to fit within the palm of your hand,
Desc3: or a tiny lock.

Name: polished key
Desc1: This key is made from hard black volcanic rock. It's been
Desc2: polished to a high sheen. When you hold it too tightly in
Desc3: your hand, you have a slight feeling in the pit of your
Desc4: stomach.

Name: red rock key
Desc1: The porous red volcanic rock has been shaped into a thick
Desc2: key. It seems to absorb body heat and constantly gives off
Desc3: a warm feeling.

Name: crocodile fang
Desc1: This sharp fang is about 3 inches in length, and half an
Desc2: inch thick at the base. The tip of the tooth has been ground
Desc3: smoothly from use, but the fang is still quite sharp.

Name: frozen shard
Desc1: This is a triangular shaped piece of magical ice.
Desc2: Occasionally when an ice golem dies, it shatters and yeilds
Desc3: shards. This piece is about a foot in length and an inch in
Desc4: diameter. You are forced to handle it carefully so the
Desc5: edges don't slice your hand open.

Name: pixie wings
Desc1: These wings are very durable, despite how thin they are.
Desc2: When you hold them up to the light, rainbow patters shine to
Desc3: the floor below. They are beautiful to look at, and silken
Desc4: to the touch.

Name: pulsating heart
Desc1: Thrag's heart continues to pulse with life, long after his
Desc2: body has given up. By putting this in a magical container,
Desc3: you could probably preserve it for quite some time. The size
Desc4: of it reflects how large the beast actually was, and makes
Desc5: it awkward to handle.

Name: scorpion tail
Desc1: This tail yields from one of the white scorpions that live
Desc2: near the city of Khazarad. Medicine men have long favored
Desc3: these for various healing concoctions. Charlatans peddle
Desc4: them at a high price to the lonely as an effective love
Desc5: potion if ground and served in a drink.

Name: spider leg
Desc1: This long and thin spider leg is still twitching its death
Desc2: throes. The leg is suprisingly light and folds neatly in
Desc3: half from the natural segments. A trail of short black hairs
Desc4: runs up one side of the leg.

Name: piece of shell
Desc1: This section of turtle shell is about one foot in diameter.
Desc2: It is extremely thick and seems almost unbreakable. A very
Desc3: heavy blow must have shattered the original shell.
Desc4: Unfortunatly, it appears to be too small to use as a shield.

Name: mamba fang
Desc1: This wicked looking fang is over 3 feet in length and comes
Desc2: to a very fine point. As you shake it you can hear fluid
Desc3: rolling about in what must be a hollow within the fang. With
Desc4: proper preperation this could be a formidable weapon.

Name: crane totem
Desc1: This tiny crystal statue of a crane is nearly transparent
Desc2: and seems very delicate.

Name: dragon totem
Desc1: This small statue of a dragon is made from lava rock and
Desc2: seems to drain the energy from your hand.

Name: gorilla totem
Desc1: This small jade statue of a gorilla feels warm to the touch.

Name: monkey totem
Desc1: This small golden statue of a monkey is nearly freezing
Desc2: to the touch.

Name: viper totem
Desc1: Coiled as if to strike, the obsidian figurine of a viper
Desc2: makes you think twice about putting your hand near it.

Name: golden idol
Desc1: Made of the purest gold this small caricature of a warrior
Desc2: looks fierce even with its oversized proportions. Normally
Desc3: gold of this type is very soft and malleable though the
Desc4: detailed working of this figurine shows no wear and no
Desc5: matter what you try a scratch cannot be left upon it.

Name: sign
Desc1: Gone hunting components, try back later.

Name: songsheet of the elements
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical song of the elements.

Name: scroll of merciful grace
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: songsheet of soothing
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical song of soothing.

Name: scroll of magma blast
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: scroll of acid tempest
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: king crab claw
Desc1: This large claw is awkward to hold because of its bulk. It
Desc2: is about 4 feet in length, including a portion of the arm.
Desc3: The shape of it would make it an effective tool for scooping
Desc4: large amounts of dirt or sand.

Name: scroll of wizard knock
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: salca dart
Desc1: The poison that coats this dart is made from a rare fungas
Desc2: only upon the upper branches of the trees in the jungle.
Desc3: Known to cause weakness in muscles, monkey that accidentally
Desc4: eat it commonly plunge to their deaths unable to hold their
Desc5: weight going from branch to branch.

Name: heavy spear
Desc1: Larger then a normal spear, this weapon is made for those
Desc2: that possess exceptional strength. Many would argue that
Desc3: this is a ballista bolt not a hand to hand weapon but those
Desc4: that have the strength to wield one make a definate argument
Desc5: for its deadliness when skewering opponents.

Name: fluked trident
Desc1: This large spear-like weapon has small ridges along the
Desc2: shaft and in the three prongs that form the head. On closer
Desc3: inspection, it appears that small holes, long and thin were
Desc4: forged into this weapon to decrease weight and improve
Desc5: balance.

Name: fangblade
Desc1: Made from the tooth of a giant viper and crafted by a master
Desc2: weaponsmith, few weapons are the equal to its elegance and
Desc3: deadliness. Bone white with a jewel encrusted pommel it
Desc4: seems as though it has a mind of its own and helps to guide
Desc5: its weilder to draw blood.

Name: bane dart
Desc1: Made from the poisons of a jeweled viper this dart is able
Desc2: to disrupt a spellcasters ability to draw and control
Desc3: magical powers.

Name: stone head
Desc1: This is a giant life-like head made of solid stone, it is
Desc2: very heavy to lift. The former owner of the head seems to
Desc3: have belonged to that of someone of great power. The dead
Desc4: eyes gaze outward in cold, lifeless silence.

Name: thundering scroll
Desc1: This scroll seems charged with rippling energy, you find it
Desc2: shocking to touch!

Name: withered tree
Desc1: This once great tree, now twists and bends like a tired old
Desc2: man. Diseased and near death something seems to keep it
Desc3: clinging to life. Its dried branches stick out like ancient
Desc4: fingers reaching to the sky. Two large holes stick out of
Desc5: the bark where branches once were.

Name: scroll of wrathful curse
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: staff of power
Desc1: This long, exquisite ebony staff has been crafted by the
Desc2: finest smiths, and emblazoned with powerful magic runes by
Desc3: only the strongest enchanters. A smooth multifaceted crystal
Desc4: tops the staff, sending out a glittering spray of rainbow
Desc5: sparkles.

Name: fungus walls
Desc1: What you can see of the walls, they appear to be made of
Desc2: light grey stone. However, most of it is covered with great
Desc3: patches of mold and fungus.

Name: tukata root
Desc1: This rare root is from the tukata plant, which only grows
Desc2: upon the corpses of those killed by poison. Tukata root
Desc3: seems to have the ability to nullify the effects of poison
Desc4: and in the living plant actually create nutrients to live
Desc5: off of.

Name: songsheet of battle
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical song of battle.

Name: behemoth hellhound hide
Desc1: This is the thick, heavy hide of a behemoth hellhound. Its
Desc2: black fur is dry and straight, and reeks of brimstone.

Name: scroll of nature tap
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: battered wooden chest
Desc1: This large wooden chest has seen better days. Large iron
Desc2: bands scratched and bent in places from fruitless attempts
Desc3: to remove them, hold the container securely on the floor. No
Desc4: locks secure the lid and there is a loose latch on the lid
Desc5: that looks like it would be easy to lift.

Name: boomstick
Desc1: This looks to be a twelve gauge double barreled Remington.
Desc2: Very rare, it can be found in the sporting goods department.
Desc3: Fashioned in Grand Rapids Michigan. It is known to be quiet
Desc4: costly. The stock has been made of walnut, and the barrels
Desc5: made of cobalt blue steel. The trigger looks to have a very
Desc6: easy pull to it. Written up on it: "Shop Smart. Shop S-mart"

Name: hero's tabard
Desc1: This deep brown cloak would weigh less if it were lined with
Desc2: lead. Sewn from the cocoons of the temprite moth they
Desc3: provide one of the sturdiest protections possible in cloth.
Desc4: Though not the easiest cloak to wear its sturdiness has
Desc5: saved more then a few warriors of lore.

Name: inquisitor's cloak
Desc1: Small scales of metal hammered thinner then paper look like
Desc2: a shimmering dragon hide on the outside of this soft deep
Desc3: grey cloak. The witchunters of old were rumored to wear such
Desc4: cloaks during their first attempt to purge magic from the
Desc5: realm.

Name: firebrand cape
Desc1: Worn by paladins of all faiths during the Great Wars,
Desc2: these bright red cloaks acted as beacons signifying a person
Desc3: looking for a honorable duel to the death. Tales of clashes
Desc4: between armoured juggernatus wearing these cloaks abound
Desc5: through the songs and tales told by bards.

Name: cloak of faith
Desc1: Devised by the first battle clerics, words of strength and
Desc2: power are woven into the underside of this cape to charge a
Desc3: cleric physically and spiritually in battle. Many an enemy
Desc4: group has fallen to a cleric wrapped in this cloaks embrace.

Name: folds of worship
Desc1: Cloth lighter then the sheerist silk, these cloaks are
Desc2: rumored to be from the robes of the gods themselves wore
Desc3: when they walked the lands. Merely wearing these poweful
Desc4: artifacts is said to bring you much closer to the greater
Desc5: powers.

Name: faith keeper
Desc1: A cape reserved for the most zealous missionaries. It is
Desc2: told to bring help to those troubled by the beasts and
Desc3: hardships of the road, in times of need it can bring the
Desc4: wearer into a zealous frenzy to keep faith in the wayward
Desc5: heathens. It is a pure white cloth, with a sun emblazoned
Desc6: brightly on the back, and a platinum star for the clasp.

Name: death's shadow
Desc1: Rumored to be magically made from the shadows of the undead,
Desc2: no item in existence is darker. It is said that a ninja who
Desc3: owns this cloak will never go unarmed for the cloak is
Desc4: hungrier for death then any owner.

Name: blacknight
Desc1: Made of the darkest black cloth these cloaks were
Desc2: commissioned by Skeller himself for the most poweful of his
Desc3: guild. Enchanted by an evil drow mage and riddled with
Desc4: hidden pockets and tools it became the gifted thieves best
Desc5: friend.

Name: lyrist's companion
Desc1: An indescript off-white, the magics within these cloaks
Desc2: could turn an unruly audience into a peaceful mob or move
Desc3: a quiet group of commoners into a dancing frenzy. Many of
Desc4: the secrets of these cloaks left with the original sages.

Name: shawl of fortune
Desc1: A light wrap that borders between blue and gray these cloaks
Desc2: had been within the gypsy families for years, lost during
Desc3: the tragedy of the wars. Many great gypsy princes and wise
Desc4: fortune tellers have warn these robes and more than a little
Desc5: of their spirit remains bound to them.

Name: tails of battle
Desc1: Not so much a cloak but a collection of cloth strips, black
Desc2: on the outer side and bright yellow on the underside.
Desc3: Commissioned by the king these cloaks struck terror into the
Desc4: foes while the warlocks spun and cleaved their way into
Desc5: enemy ranks.

Name: runed cape
Desc1: Flawless white with runes of various colors creating a
Desc2: tangle of magic upon it these robes have been donned by the
Desc3: most powerful of magi since the beginning of time. A slight
Desc4: hum of magical power can be felt by anyone near it.

Name: leafwoven cloak
Desc1: Tiny vines still producing small green leaves make up this
Desc2: cloak. Created by the first druid to give disciples
Desc3: knowledge of how the earth mother supports her children this
Desc4: magical clothing brings a druid closer to one with nature.

Name: mantle of the woodsman
Desc1: The rangers that first scouted these lands were proud owners
Desc2: of these deep green cloaks. Imbued with protection from
Desc3: various elements these cloaks allowed them to withstand the
Desc4: harsh wilderness for months at a time.

Name: peasant cloak
Desc1: The humble look of this ratty cloak hides it's true power.
Desc2: Owned by generations of quiet monks who spent life times
Desc3: training in the arts, these cloaks provide the insight and
Desc4: fighting knowledge of generations past.

Name: scroll of divine courage
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: emerald-studded bracelet
Desc1: Crafted of adamantite, and studded with large emeralds, this
Desc2: bracelet was crafted by someone of great skill. Each emerald
Desc3: seems to glow with an inner light, giving the bracelet a
Desc4: life of its own.

Name: shimmering portal
Desc1: A large oblong portal that shimmers with white light. If you
Desc2: listen quietly, you can hear the energies surging and fading
Desc3: in rhythm with your heart beating. It looks large enough for
Desc4: a man to walk through on horseback.

Name: blackened dirk
Desc1: This short thick blade is flat black color with intricate
Desc2: etchings circling the hilt. Light disappears into the
Desc3: surface of the blade instead of reflecting back. Blending
Desc4: easily into the shadows, it makes an excellent knife for
Desc5: those who prey on the unwary.

Name: sai
Desc1: A pair of thin blades about a foot long. Each blade has a
Desc2: curving hilt, giving them the appearance of small hand held
Desc3: pitchforks. The sai are ideal tools for an opportunistic
Desc4: ninja to surprise his prey with.

Name: blackened wrist guard
Desc1: Made from a flat black metal, this guard is a small disk
Desc2: that straps cleverly across the palm of your hand and the
Desc3: back of your wrist. The disk is designed to protect the back
Desc4: of the hand and wrist while still allowing freedom of
Desc5: movement to climb, wield a weapon, or cast a spell.

Name: lifestealer
Desc1: The lifestealer blade is nearly four feet long but
Desc2: unbelievably thin for its size. Made of an orcish metal it
Desc3: reflects no light and mysteriously makes no sound as it
Desc4: moves through the air.

Name: black embroidered robes
Desc1: A large black robe of a velvet material that completely
Desc2: covers you from head to toe. A gold pattern is embroidered
Desc3: around the hem of the robe, and around each sleeve. The
Desc4: material is thick and provides excellent protection.

Name: black diamond
Desc1: These oval shaped black diamonds appear to be worn
Desc2: ornamentally on the forehead. Holding one in your hand, you
Desc3: realize they are actually a living organism that embeds in
Desc4: their flesh. Only the death of a nanati host releases the
Desc5: stone. It hums with life in your hand.

Name: crystal
Desc1: This piece of crystal looks newly polished and has an odd
Desc2: cyan glow to it. You notice as you move closer to it, that
Desc3: the glow seems to almost pulse, as if it were in time with
Desc4: some heartbeat.

Name: Draka's Blade
Desc1: This broadsword is crafted from rare black metal.  The blade
Desc2: itself appears to have lost its luster but its edge gleams
Desc3: due to the sharpness of it. Etched into its simple handle
Desc4: is the name "Draka", obviously it's original owner.
Desc5: Thoughts of great and mighty deeds flash in your mind as you
Desc6: heft the weapon.

Name: head of the orc warlord
Desc1: This beaten and bloody head once belonged to a dreaded black
Desc2: orcish warlord. Now blank eyes stare dully in silence, as
Desc3: foul bloody ichor leak from its fanged mouth and severed
Desc4: neck.

Name: crimson scale gauntlets
Desc1: This pair of hard leather gloves are made of some type of
Desc2: black animal skin, the back of each hand has several
Desc3: diamond-shaped crimson pieces of some alien metal sown into
Desc4: the leather. On each piece of metal is stamped a small
Desc5: flame.

Name: sacrificial dagger
Desc1: This light weight blade appears to be crafted of some black
Desc2: metal. The blade is very serrated, with skulls engraved all
Desc3: along its length. A single bloodstone is set in the pommel
Desc4: and it seems to have a faint glow to it.

Name: curved bone dagger
Desc1: This trully gruesome weapon, made entirely out of yellowed
Desc2: bone carries a taint of pure evil. The jagged blade is very
Desc3: cold to touch, and is only adorned with a single piece of
Desc4: polished jet which hums faintly. Faded red stains on the
Desc5: edge tell you it has been used many times to prey on
Desc6: unknowing victims.

Name: scroll of ethereal shield
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: icy scroll
Desc1: This scroll is freezing to touch and gives off wisps of
Desc2: steam as if it were made entirely of ice, oddly enough you
Desc3: can unroll it to reveal swirling runes in the language of
Desc4: druids.

Name: bloody meat cleaver
Desc1: This massive piece of cutlery has dried bloodstains covering
Desc2: the thick metal blade. You can tell from the smell it hasn't
Desc3: been cleaned for quiet awhile, and yet the black wood handle
Desc4: appears to be freshly carved.

Name: ice chest
Desc1: This massive chest was once made of some fine metal, except
Desc2: ages of being locked in solid ice have made the metal
Desc3: brittle. Years of being put away in some icy, dark cavern
Desc4: have made this chest weight ten times what it seems. Your
Desc5: skin almost sticks to the surface as you brush your hand
Desc6: across the lock.

Name: withered tree
Desc1: This once great tree, now twists and bends like a tired old
Desc2: man. Diseased and near death something seems to keep it
Desc3: clinging to life. Its dried branches stick out like ancient
Desc4: fingers reaching to the sky. One large hole sticks out of
Desc5: the bark where branches once were.

Name: wedding gown
Desc1: This elaborate wedding gown is made from the finest silk.
Desc2: The bodice is decorated with small pearls, arranged in
Desc3: intricate patterns. The ten foot train that trails behind
Desc4: the gown is made from layers of soft lace.

Name: wedding band
Desc1: This elegantly-crafted band is made of the finest gold. It
Desc2: is about a quarter inch in diameter, and polished to a high
Desc3: sheen. A small diamond set in the center glitters softly,
Desc4: and engraved in small letters inside the band are the words,
Desc5: "For My Beloved."

Name: gavel of justice
Desc1: This weapon is surrounded by a faint holy aura. Made
Desc2: entirely of platinum from handle to hammer-heads, it has
Desc3: been fashioned to appear like that of a massive gavel.
Desc4: Symbols of justice are etched on each head.

Name: daikatana
Desc1: This is a large two-handed sword, five feet in length.
Desc2: Though longer then a greatsword, the blade feels light and
Desc3: is slightly curved. The edge glitters in the light, and the
Desc4: hilt, shaped like that of a dragon's maw, tells you it was
Desc5: crafted by the hands of a master.

Name: ice crystal falchion
Desc1: This sword has a bluish white hilt which attaches to a
Desc2: crystal blue blade of what looks like pure ice. The blade
Desc3: has a heavy end with a slight curve forward. It feels large
Desc4: and heavy but seems to be easy to weild.

Name: magical rune
Desc1: A magical rune crafted by a mage of great power, it
Desc2: symbolizes the person has done a great service for the
Desc3: crafter and can return it for reimbursement for that deed.

Name: smoking blackwood chest
Desc1: This massive blackwood chest smells faintly of brimstone and
Desc2: tinder. Smoke comes from every crack and crevice and you
Desc3: are left to wonder if opening it will release some hell bent
Desc4: force or unholy treasure of utter damnation.

Name: black runed shovel
Desc1: Looking at this shovel makes you queasy. The handle is made
Desc2: of polished blackwood, with glowing red runes running along
Desc3: it's shaft and the shovel blade. As you examine the blade
Desc4: further you realize it has been honed to a sharp edge and
Desc5: it looks more like an enlarged spearhead then anything else.
Desc6: Whoever fashioned this shovel no longer intend it to dig.

Name: stone chest
Desc1: This chest is actually a large piece of granite that has
Desc2: been meticulously hollowed out. A large stone slab forms the
Desc3: door. It looks immensely heavy and you already feel your
Desc4: muscles ache from the strain they are about to take.

Name: blizzardfang
Desc1: This serrated dagger could easily be a sword in the hands
Desc2: of a weaker person. It looks to be made of some magical ice
Desc3: so cold that it would give goosebumps to anyone that wields
Desc4: it.

Name: severed arm
Desc1: This long arm once belonged to some well muscled humanoid.
Desc2: It is black and purplish from the severed shoulder down to
Desc3: the stiff, jagged nails. It smells faintly of rotting but
Desc4: your sure it would do as a weapon in a pinch.

Name: severed leg
Desc1: This blackened severed leg has belonged to some humanoid of
Desc2: great strength. Even disattached the muscles are still bulky
Desc3: and toned. Despite the fact you can hardly stand the rancid
Desc4: smell you know this would make a crude though morbid weapon.

Name: spiked black tentacle
Desc1: This is is the severed black greenish arm of a tentacled
Desc2: abomination. Several spikes protrude from the end making it
Desc3: a very clumsy but cruelly effective weapon.

Name: minotaur horn
Desc1: This curved black horn is three and a half feet in length.
Desc2: As you examine the tip and see the dark stains of dried
Desc3: blood it is evident that it once belonged to a very mighty
Desc4: minotaur of great brute strength. According to ancient myth
Desc5: the horn of a minotaur can be used for magical components or
Desc6: as a musical instrument.

Name: platinum greatsword
Desc1: This is a massive platinum blade four feet in length. It
Desc2: appears incredibly sharp and you wonder if it could cleave
Desc3: a man in two. Requiring two hands to wield, and massive
Desc4: strength to even use, this sword would cause huge amounts
Desc5: of damage in battle and you can only hope you will never
Desc6: face such a weapon in combat.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Dougan, Paladin of the House Of Lords, he
Desc2: proclaimed himself the flaming cow god of doom, until he
Desc3: met the minotaurs.

Name: jail cell
Desc1: This is a small, cold, stone cell. It has a crude wooden
Desc2: bench to lay on, and a glory-hole in the corner, but
Desc3: other wise the room is bare.

Name: midnight sash
Desc1: This sash is made of some type of material which feels as
Desc2: fine as silk, but it seems to absorb any light around it.
Desc3: Holding it in your hands it seems to tingle your fingers,
Desc4: and you can see tiny runes stitched into the thread in some
Desc5: alien language.

Name: dented soup can
Desc1: This can has been crafted by some mechanical technique not
Desc2: known to you. It has a large dent on one side, which
Desc3: although brusies the can itself the can still holds a full
Desc4: eight ounces of soup, just as it did before the dent.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: In memory of Miss Teri, who vanished mysteriously into
Desc2: the mist, and is missed.. rarely has the realm seen such a
Desc3: perfect example of charm and beauty.  We are sure wherever
Desc4: she found harbor is made better by her presence, and hope
Desc5: that the Angel watching over her fares well.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies JenGhis, Paladin Leader of the House of Lords.
Desc2: He served truth and justice until betrayal overcame him from
Desc3: an unholy idol.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Fleet the Wise, Mage extraordinare, he was wolfbait for many
Desc2: moons until he discovered the secret of serpentkin, but the
Desc3: secret waned on his soul and he faded away.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Cougar Darkblade, Lord Paladin, rescuer of countless who
Desc2: were lost in the infinite twisting passages of the labrynth.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Rab, the rabid Ranger, twisted and demented he
Desc2: always had a true sense of loyalty.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: KiLee the Ranger, she had more fun romping through the
Desc2: forest then is healthy for any one person.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Og Skullsplitter, his favorite food was horseapples.
Desc2: His last words, told in a mumbled delirum, only mentioned
Desc3: the taste of the last horse.

Name: a statue of warrior
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCWAR.STA

Name: songsheet of destruction
Desc1: This is a bardic songsheet of destruction.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Tiberius the Ninja, graceful and deadly, sleek and silent.
Desc2: It didn't help much against the dragonfire.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Lying here be Kasdon, the goblin thief that stole many
Desc2: hearts as well as wallets. He was well loved by all and
Desc3: sorely missed.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Akmad, wild warrior always on the edge. He swore
Desc2: to everyone he was endowed like a camel, he only showed
Desc3: the wrong kind of woman.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: The final resting place of Brother Luke, with patient and
Desc2: even hand he guided many novices through the harsher parts
Desc3: of the realm, he moved on in life and rests easy now.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Lute SilverSong, Who was as tall as he is long,
Desc2: We will miss that halfling bard, How he made us laugh hard,
Desc3: But the last joke he had done, He picked the wrong someone,
Desc4: For it you accuse someone of the fart, It better not be
Desc5: Sheriff LionHeart. We Sa-Lute you Silversong!

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Raise a glass, raise a toast,
Desc2: Here lies Itoshu, he was made to roast,
Desc3: On his last visit to the black dragon.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Jehan JDC
Desc2: He could always put a smile on someone's face
Desc3: He knew the right things to say and stood up for them
Desc4: He loved his family and loved his mmud
Desc5: Our prayers and thoughts go out to you John
Desc6: Rest in Peace Jehan. You will be missed.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Conan. Many people were heard to exclaim
Desc2: what a mighty warrior he would be, if only he like the
Desc3: sword better than his ale.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Damien Xcelcier a friend, a foe, To whom honor ment the most
Desc2: He stood with pride, but alas, he died.
Desc3: He warned us about fear, he should have been more
Desc4: sincere. He warned of the wrath, but it was Dark Phoenix;
Desc5: who got the last laugh. He will be remembered over many beer
Desc6: it is to him, that we say 'Cheers'

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Satire Shilligan, the warrior punk. They stabbed
Desc2: him forty six times before burning the corpse.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: BlueSky the mage, we miss him so,
Desc2: It's really too bad, that he had to go,
Desc3: But an  overconfident mystic, convinced him to try,
Desc4: To get his death pile back, and now we cry,
Desc5: Into the dying grove they journeyed, never to return,
Desc6: But got ambushed by killer bees, their poison did burn,

Name: gravestone
Desc1: The resting place of Tomster FistsOfFury, he shaped the
Desc2: dark caves into his own private lair. The smell finally got
Desc3: to him.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Pandabear, Paladin of the Dark Blades, always lended a hand
Desc2: to any in need. Tolerant and patient with those who did not
Desc3: heed. Done away in dead of night, by most foul and dastardly
Desc4: deed. Unavenged goes her death, and she will be missed.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Rugal BlackNoah, a Kang Mageslayer that vowed to dominate
Desc2: the world and purify it of all that is magical. His ashes
Desc3: were found in the obsidian tunnels.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Lagerhowen, Forest King of Genocide, for the women
Desc2: and the wine did he live, but in the end one of them did him
Desc3: in, nobody knows for sure which it was

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Jyhad, he always tried to start one, and ended
Desc2: up starting too many.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Ares, he brought war and plunder to the innocent,
Desc2: ninety bounties later and his Nigrescence is no more.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: Here lies Delirium, doer of many dastardly deeds, it is said
Desc2: his spirit is that devilish voice whisipering in your ear.

Name: gravestone
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1393.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1394.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1395.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1396.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1397.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1398.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCC1399.STO

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION

Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION

Name: a statue of mage
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION

Name: a statue of druid
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
