Name: a statue of ranger
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCRAN.STA

Name: a statue of mystic
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCMYS.STA

Name: shovel
Desc1: This is a simple shovel that has hardly been used. It is
Desc2: made with an oaken handle, that seems somewhat rotten, and
Desc3: a rusty iron blade. It could be used to dig up a few graves
Desc4: but anything more stressful and it could easily break.

Name: jail key
Desc1: This rusted iron key has seen many years of age, but little
Desc2: use. It appears by the emblem on it that its some type of
Desc3: offical Silvermere key for city use. On the opposite side of
Desc4: the emblem is the letter J which you assume would mean Jail.

Name: young tree
Desc1: This young tree has been planted decades ago and is in full
Desc2: bloom of its leaves. It sways lightly through the wind, the
Desc3: branches creaking like old bones and the whisper of leaves
Desc4: is quiet and relaxing.

Name: nightblack portal
Desc1: This oval rift in space pulsates with an evil, chaotic
Desc2: power. Negative energy leaks out and surrounds you, leaving
Desc3: you numb and trembling. Whatever lies beyond would be sure
Desc4: death for the weak, and difficult at best even for mighty
Desc5: heroes.

Name: gambling sign
Desc1: Play Dragon's Dice or Crowns and Skulls for lower wages,
Desc2: or ask for a fortune by the gypsy girl here!

Name: mouthpiece
Desc1: You see a mouthpiece used for a musical instrument made of
Desc2: platinum. A single rune that of an O with a swirl in the
Desc3: center is the only marking on it.

Name: battlehorn
Desc1: This is a simple horn of some large beast, hollowed out
Desc2: entirely with a mouthpiece of platinum at the tip. You see
Desc3: on the mouthpiece is a large O with a swirl inside the ring,
Desc4: a rune of perhaps but your not sure what it does.

Name: red dragon tail
Desc1: This long slender tail is aproximately 12 feet in length.
Desc2: Long black  spines cover it from base to tip. It  is
Desc3: relativly light in weight and is quite durable In the
Desc4: hands of a master, this tail could be crafted into a fine
Desc5: weapon.

Name: dragon fang
Desc1: This razor-sharp fang is about 12 inches in length.
Desc2: It glistens brightly in the light.  With enough
Desc3: strength it could tear through flesh and metal alike.

Name: red dragonscale whip
Desc1: This long slender whip is aproximately twelve feet in
Desc2: length. The handle is made of soft black leather which gives
Desc3: you excellent control. A large dragon fang is mounted at the
Desc4: tip of this fine whip.

Name: tent
Desc1: The blue fabric of the tent sparkles lightly in the darkness
Desc2: As you feel the wonderous cloth, a cool breeze flows over
Desc3: your body and caresses your mind.

Name: tainted ruby
Desc1: A massive ruby inset on the floor before the altar, it
Desc2: has a tainted, dirty, red colour to it. With horror you
Desc3: realize the blood from the altar is draining to tarnish the
Desc4: ruby. An inner flame seems to burn inside it, swaying with
Desc5: an odd seduction, yearning for your touch.

Name: ornate dragon carving
Desc1: Made from some ornate blackened wood, it depicts a dragon
Desc2: claws outstretched and flame ablaze in full splendor. A
Desc3: magnificent depiction it seems lifelike from the tiny eyes
Desc4: to the sharp fangs of the tiny maw. The carver was immensely
Desc5: skilled in the ways of working wood.

Name: red dragon hide
Desc1: You can tell this piece of hide came from a young dragon.
Desc2: Red as blood it is somewhat heavy, with small spikes jutting
Desc3: out in some spots. It seems to carry a warmth of its own,
Desc4: and you wonder if it could be used for some kind of armour.

Name: red dragon gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of masterly crafted gauntlets, made from the
Desc2: hide of a dragon. Very supple, they are soft and warm to the
Desc3: touch, yet give excellent protection against almost any
Desc4: attack.

Name: red dragon leggings
Desc1: Blood red dragonhide make up this pair of leathery leggings.
Desc2: Crafted by a supreme leatherworker, these leggings offer
Desc3: powerful protection for the lower body, and yet are very
Desc4: flexible.

Name: red dragon tunic
Desc1: Amazing to gaze at, this suit of red dragonhide was
Desc2: obviously made by the hands of a master. Spiked ridges along
Desc3: the back and shoulders give it an almost hellish look,
Desc4: making its wearer look fearsome indeed.

Name: red dragon helm
Desc1: This is a sturdy helm of red dragonhide, fashioned with
Desc2: superb skill. You see it has extra padding so it may protect
Desc3: the crown from blows with more protection then normal.

Name: red dragon boots
Desc1: This is a pair of skillfully crafted boots, made from the
Desc2: red hide of a dragon. They come up almost to the knee and
Desc3: are warm to the touch. Built for protection they are also
Desc4: form-fitting and very comfortable.

Name: soulblighter
Desc1: A long, slightly curved blade of red meets a hilt fashioned
Desc2: from the yellowed bone of some dead animal. The blade gives
Desc3: off a glow giving everything a macabre shine of blood. An
Desc4: inscription on the blade reads "Soulblighter". As you read
Desc5: it a foul raspy voice seems to whisper in your ear words
Desc6: of great power and damnation.

Name: cruel bone greatsword
Desc1: The bone of some massive animal, this sword is immensely
Desc2: heavy and hard to wield. Jagged ridges climb up either side
Desc3: of the bone's sharpened edges, which could cause immense
Desc4: wounds. The hilt is made of some strange, blackened metal
Desc5: with the skull of some animal on the pommel.

Name: blackened unicorn horn
Desc1: Wretched and evil, this three-foot-long horn emanates an
Desc2: aura of damnation. As black as night it twists and turns
Desc3: before coming to a blood tinged tip that is needle sharp and
Desc4: just as deadly. Because it is so twisted it is somewhat
Desc5: unwieldy, however it would still make an excellently vile
Desc6: weapon.

Name: farming hoe
Desc1: A six foot long wooden pole attaches to a flat metal blade
Desc2: to form this implement of soil destruction. A simple
Desc3: farming tool, it can be used for a weapon in a pinch.

Name: runed farming hoe
Desc1: Six feet of blackwood attach to a black glittering metal
Desc2: blade. Fiery runes are etched all along the farming tool and
Desc3: glow with a rhythm of its own. You can only assume some mage
Desc4: was a farmer in a previous job and created this for some
Desc5: purpose. You at least hope it was a sane mind.

Name: rusty scythe
Desc1: This long curved blade is wicked in appearance for such a
Desc2: benign tool. Stretched out from a curved handle like a
Desc3: ragged, bloody claw, this farming instrument has seen better
Desc4: days and those days were many ages ago. While immensely slow
Desc5: it could cut many a limb off with dreadful precision.

Name: deck of cards
Desc1: A simple deck of traveling cards, they have the stiffness
Desc2: of cards never used before. Simple patterns adorn the backs,
Desc3: while individual hand-painted pictures have been placed
Desc4: with expert care on the face of each card. According to myth
Desc5: card decks have been used to turn the tides of fortunes by
Desc6: gypsies while traveling abroad.

Name: faded shawl
Desc1: This is an ancient piece of cloth with holes almost showing
Desc2: in spots. Once brightly colored with checkers of green and
Desc3: brown it has seen decades of use and wear. It gives very
Desc4: little protection and you wonder if it could be of any use
Desc5: at all.

Name: withered walking stick
Desc1: A small stick, once the branch of some tree, is now almost
Desc2: petrified from the many ages it has seen. Dirt covers it
Desc3: from tip to handle and you can tell from the scratches and
Desc4: cuts that the many miles it has seen have not been kind.
Desc5: Something about this stick gives you a tingle.

Name: bloodwood chest
Desc1: A chest that sends shivers down your spine it is a chest
Desc2: made of some ancient wood that appears to be stained with
Desc3: fresh blood. Foul runes are etched all along the sides
Desc4: and even more archaic symbols adorn the handles and lock.

Name: vorpal hatchet
Desc1: This is a strange axe made of a metal which glitters as if
Desc2: it were silver, but is blacker then the heart of a fiend.
Desc3: Designed for quick and deadly cuts, it appears that with the
Desc4: slightest swing it could dismember an opponent very easily.

Name: sunburst necklace
Desc1: Inlaid with bright gold that almost shines with its own
Desc2: light this necklace one of the finest works youve ever seen.
Desc3: In the image of a glorious sunburst that has risen with the
Desc4: new day to destroy the night with the light of purification.
Desc5: On each chain link of the necklace is a symbol from some
Desc6: sacred archaic tongue.

Name: platinum plate leggings
Desc1: This is pair of heavy plate greaves, made using the purest
Desc2: platinum you have ever seen. They are extremely thick and
Desc3: provide excellent leg protection. They almost shine with an
Desc4: inner glow of magic.

Name: jewel-encrusted warhammer
Desc1: More a treasure then an actual weapon, jewels of all shapes
Desc2: adorn this weapon. Sapphires, emeralds, rubies and diamonds
Desc3: glitter all around this massive hammer of war. Jewels are
Desc4: inlaid so thick that it is not possible to tell what it is
Desc5: made of underneath.

Name: Darkbane
Desc1: A long slender blade crafted in a fashion long lost to
Desc2: modern day. The name Darkbane is written in gold, and the
Desc3: entire sword seems to glow with its own sublime divinity.
Desc4: A platinum dragon, with wings outstretched, has been crafted
Desc5: to be the hilt of this shining blade. It moves through the
Desc6: air with a great flash of white, singing a hymn of prayer.

Name: fur cloak
Desc1: This large cloak is made from a thick white pelt that feels
Desc2: like velvet. It is thick and durable, but also heavy. The
Desc3: cloak was hand crafted by villagers living near a snow
Desc4: topped mountain range and designed to provide extra
Desc5: protection from the elements in winter.

Name: fur gloves
Desc1: The insides of these gloves are tanned to a soft and
Desc2: supple consistency, to allow freedom of movement for
Desc3: your fingers. The velvety white hair on the outside
Desc4: has been cut short enough to allow more dexterous
Desc5: movements, while still being thick enough to provide
Desc6: protection from the climate.

Name: silvery spiked corselet
Desc1: This finely crafted platemail is fashioned from a silver
Desc2: that has a white and pure innocence to it. You can find
Desc3: no dents or scratches on the metal, as if it had
Desc4: never been fashioned by mortal hand. The only markings
Desc5: found is a simple holy symbol inscribed on each individual
Desc6: plate and many large spikes that protrude from the shoulder.

Name: longsword
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: ethereal dagger
Desc1: Made of some smoking, glass-like, material this dagger is
Desc2: almost weightless to hold. Cold to touch it almost leaves a
Desc3: misty trail through the air. Glittering with a deadly gleam
Desc4: this supernatural weapon could become useful.

Name: brimstone hammer
Desc1: This great sledge reeks of sulphur and ash. A massive rock,
Desc2: black as night sits atop a long metal handle to make a crude
Desc3: but effective cudgel. Black writing is scripted on the head
Desc4: that seems to writhe and dance. The hammerhead litters ash
Desc5: around your feet. You know not where this hammer came from,
Desc6: but you can tell it is for immense destruction and evil.

Name: bloodstone ring
Desc1: This ring is made of four black iron bands, intertwined to
Desc2: appear as if it were actually a small claw. Cradled inside
Desc3: the claw is a stone the color of blood, with small flecks
Desc4: of blackness that seems to swirl in its depths. For some
Desc5: reason watching the swirling makes your stomach twinge and
Desc6: you almost have to look away before you become dizzy.

Name: dark onyx ring
Desc1: A ring of pure blackness grasps an even darker onyx stone.
Desc2: The ring is cold to touch, and seems to turn the air around
Desc3: you colder still. You find putting this ring on dims your
Desc4: vision, as if you were closing your eyes to sneeze and had
Desc5: not yet opened them.

Name: scarlet doublet
Desc1: No finer doublet have you ever seen then this piece of
Desc2: superb sewmanship. Normally worn by noblemen, you pinch the
Desc3: fabric and realize it is several thousand miniscule chains
Desc4: interlinked together. An excellent a deception as any, this
Desc5: could be worn to look like normal clothes but in truth
Desc6: protect as well as any hauberk.

Name: executioner's hood
Desc1: A massive black hood, wrought of black cloth. It is used
Desc2: fully hide the face of anyone wearing it so they made commit
Desc3: murderous deeds with their identity secret. Two narrow slits
Desc4: are the only openings and a vile rune, stitched with some
Desc5: glittering black thread, sits atop the crown of the death
Desc6: mask. Only one of evil intentions would consider this hood.

Name: black stained tunic
Desc1: A tunic made of cotton, dyed a deep, unending black. It is
Desc2: entirely unremarkable except for the dark stains that mark
Desc3: the shirt. Splotched all over there is no pattern to them
Desc4: other then they appear to have been splashed on the tunic.
Desc5: Upon closer inspection you realize the stains are blood,
Desc6: giving you a slight chill up your back.

Name: heavy black boots
Desc1: Thick black leather make up this large pair of boots. The
Desc2: skin is so rigid you would think it were iron but for the
Desc3: supple feel of tanned skin. Covering from toe to shin
Desc4: it seems to have a menacing look to them, an unending well
Desc5: of blackness as if it were going to stomp mountains into
Desc6: the ground. Small spikes jut from around the sole.

Name: red rose
Desc1: An illustrious shade of red paints this rose a magnificent
Desc2: color in any light. Freshly cut it is still full of life,
Desc3: as if it inhales the air around it with a new breath each
Desc4: time. In full bloom the petals seem a delicate piece of
Desc5: glass, together making a masterpiece only nature can create.

Name: black rose
Desc1: Midnight petals hug the stem of this freshly cut rose. Soft
Desc2: to the touch that it almost feels like down, it is so pretty
Desc3: in its dark richness it almost brings a tear to your eye.
Desc4: Legend holds that black roses are the most rare and are
Desc5: desired for magic if not true beauty.

Name: burning black feather
Desc1: This feather burns darkly from a great fire. You fear as
Desc2: if your skin will blister the moment your hand touches it.

Name: vibrant scroll
Desc1: This parchment is a radiant sight to see. In strange
Desc2: patterns, every colour of the rainbow reflects from it,
Desc3: while the blackened magi letters seem to stay bold and
Desc4: unwavering.

Name: rolled parchment
Desc1: Thorand, dire times have caused the writing of this letter.
Desc2: The fortress is weakening, and Xarthick has fallen to
Desc3: temptation, the she-devil has gotten to him. If you have any
Desc4: one that can aid us, send them now. I do not think we can
Desc5: last another fortnight. Give them this parchment so my
Desc6: men know not to fight them, they do not trust anyone else.

Name: throwing hammers
Desc1: This well-balanced, sturdy pair of light hammers make a
Desc2: poweful weapon at close range. Crafted by dwarven smiths,
Desc3: it has been told that hammers like these were used in combat
Desc4: to support skirmishing troops.

Name: diamond-encrusted bracelet
Desc1: Beautiful diamonds surround a metal band to create a
Desc2: gorgeous bracelet of incredible splendor. It glitters
Desc3: brightly, almost blinding you. No inscription or insignia
Desc4: can be found anywhere on the arm-wear.

Name: elven harp
Desc1: This exquisite golden harp is crafted with intricate
Desc2: swirling patterns. Its strings are fine and well-strung,
Desc3: and the melody that it plays when its strings are plucked
Desc4: is heavenly.

Name: blackened bracelet
Desc1: A circlet of some type of burnt metal it is impossible to
Desc2: tell what it was before being made so crudely. Bizzarre
Desc3: carvings dance around the large metal ring.

Name: nightblack scythe
Desc1: This huge, heavy scythe is as black as eternal night, and
Desc2: radiates a strange aura of death. Its shaft is set with
Desc3: ivory skulls, its blade is long, curved, and sharp as a
Desc4: razor. A sense of evil invades your senses, and you feel as
Desc5: if gazing at this grisly weapon taints your soul.

Name: bone ring
Desc1: This is a simple ring made of many small bones tied together
Desc2: to form a circle. Easily fitting most fingers, an ebony
Desc3: skull is imprinted upon the largest bone.

Name: bone club
Desc1: This large club has been fashioned from the rib-bone of some
Desc2: mammoth beast, dead long ago. The head of the club is
Desc3: covered with jagged spikes, and large protrusions that could
Desc4: do a great deal of damage to its victim.

Name: blackwood cudgel
Desc1: A crude weapon, it has been fashioned somewhat from the
Desc2: root of some great blackwood tree. It is very thick, with
Desc3: twine tide around it's narrow end to form a simple handle.
Desc4: The base of the cudgel is very thick with knots causing its
Desc5: target to bruise heavily if not break.

Name: rod of might
Desc1: A rod made from simple iron, it seems almost weightless to
Desc2: hold. A single marking is the only thing remarkable about
Desc3: this tool of a ruler. It radiates a certain serenity about
Desc4: you and piece of mind. This must be the symbol of some great
Desc5: and powerful lord from long ago, the last remnant of an
Desc6: extinct dynasty of order that fell to the chaos.

Name: blackwood longbow
Desc1: A cruelly fashioned longbow, it looks to be made from
Desc2: blackwood. The wood has been stained with some dark red
Desc3: fluid, and the bowstring seems to draw with great speed. A
Desc4: quiver does not accompany the bow and a practice draw forms
Desc5: an arrow of darkness. Vile runes are carved on the front of
Desc6: the bowshaft, that writhe in a twisted dance.

Name: reading glasses
Desc1: This is a pair of simple reading glasses, known to be worn
Desc2: by scholars and librarians of old. You note that there is
Desc3: a second lens inlaid within each frame.

Name: blackwood war-spear
Desc1: This menacing black spear has a three-foot long shaft made
Desc2: of blackwood. It feels as hard as any metal and you suspect
Desc3: some type of red resin has been used to harden its edge, as
Desc4: the wood seems to have a reddish tinge. The jagged head
Desc5: looks to be the fang of some savage beast, long, curved and
Desc6: sharp enough to slice a finger with a wrong move.

Name: scarab necklace
Desc1: A necklace of elaborate design, it is made up of twelve
Desc2: golden scarabs. Each one looks as if it had been alive, and
Desc3: dipped into the liquid metal. A single sygil is marked on
Desc4: each insect. Ancient myth tells of a necklace such as this
Desc5: protecting the wearer from most things terrifying.

Name: templar greatsword
Desc1: This is a long, heavy blade, made from some pristine metal.
Desc2: Sharp and deadly, it is bladed on both sides. A golden
Desc3: cross is imprinted on the hilt, and you see holy symbols
Desc4: written around the cross. On the blade itself it also has
Desc5: written "For Honour".

Name: beastly claws
Desc1: Formerly belonging to some dreadful beast, these claws look
Desc2: as though they could slash through skin with chilling ease.
Desc3: The claws themselves are attached to a pair of large,
Desc4: severed hands that have been hollowed out somehow by
Desc5: unnatural means. The sickening thought enters your mind that
Desc6: you could use these claws as a weapon by wearing the skin.

Name: feather-tipped hat
Desc1: A hat made from some rich, fine leather, it is the color
Desc2: of royal purple. A smooth silk band encricles the hat,
Desc3: keeping a bright, flamboyant, feather in place. Trying to
Desc4: identify the color of the feather only makes your head hurt
Desc5: as it seems to be constantly changing colors through the
Desc6: entire spectrum.

Name: displacer fur cloak
Desc1: The skin of a displacer beast, fashioned into a warm cloak.
Desc2: Magic of the creature has not left since it's death so the
Desc3: wearer will appear like a fleeting cat, always one step away
Desc4: from harm. A very powerful piece of magic.

Name: mithril executioner's axe
Desc1: This huge axe has a gigantic, single-edged blade crafted
Desc2: from pure mithril. Its fine edge could cut stone as easily
Desc3: as flesh, due to such cruelty in combat it is only useable
Desc4: by those soley dedicated to evil. While it is large and
Desc5: heavy, the blade moves marvelously quick.

Name: burnt iron chest
Desc1: This large, heavy chest is made of black iron, which has
Desc2: been polished so that the container gleams like a beetle's
Desc3: carapace. A hideous demonic face has been carved into its
Desc4: lid, and it is obvious that the chest is full of valuables.

Name: elven longbow
Desc1: This beautifully-made longbow appears to be made of
Desc2: glowing Bronzewood, a sure sign of Elven origin. Graceful
Desc3: runes have been carved along its length, and it's string
Desc4: hums vibrantly as you pull it with ease. A quiver of green
Desc5: accompanies the bow, full of silver-feathered arrows, eager
Desc6: for use.

Name: crimson scalemail tunic
Desc1: Hundreds of crimson discs have been sewn into this suit of
Desc2: armor. Each disc is of some strange metal and has been
Desc3: stamped with a crimson flame. It feels lightweight but the
Desc4: metal looks very strong for protection.

Name: crimson scalemail leggings
Desc1: This pair of leather pants are made of some type of
Desc2: black animal skin, with diamond-shaped crimson pieces sown
Desc3: around the front and back of the leather. The discs appear
Desc4: to be of some type of alien metal, and each piece has a
Desc5: flame stamped upon them.

Name: crimson helm
Desc1: Fashioned from some crimson metal, this helm looks durable
Desc2: enough to take on the worst punishment. It has a noseguard
Desc3: fashioned from obsidian yet it does not seem to hinder
Desc4: vision in the slightest. The symbol of an open flame is
Desc5: stamped on the brow of the helm, the mark of its maker.

Name: large sign
Desc1: This is a large wooden pole with three ancient slabs nailed
Desc2: to it. Through the faded writing you can see a black arrow
Desc3: pointing east with the words "Arlysia". Another faded arrow
Desc4: points north, with "Lake" inscripted on it. The last arrow
Desc5: is more ominous, written in fresh red ink, scraggled on it
Desc6: displays the words "Gravyard, Dange".

Name: dragonfang ninjato
Desc1: A magnificent one-handed sword. It is slightly curved with
Desc2: a dangerous edge. The blade radiates a spectrum. It is
Desc3: colored oddly, red, blue, green and black, all blending to
Desc4: form an intricate design. The hilt is fashioned to make it
Desc5: appear as if the ninjato was the breath of a dragon, mouth
Desc6: agape.

Name: great blackwood chest
Desc1: A large chest of unremarkable creation. Thick blackwood
Desc2: surrounds the contents of this chest, and a simple iron
Desc3: lock. The weight of the blackwood makes it immensely heavy.

Name: anointed morningstar
Desc1: A platinum rod connects a chain of finest silver to a large
Desc2: barbed diamond ball. Incantations of divine power encircle
Desc3: the diamond, protecting it from shattering, while dealing
Desc4: swift and brutal justice to any and all villiany. The weapon
Desc5: moves swiftly and with ease, as if it were an extension of
Desc6: your arm. Its spikes are like the fangs of a coiled viper.

Name: diamond longsword
Desc1: A long blade of a single cut diamond shines brightly with
Desc2: an inner light. You are basked with a holy glow as you gaze
Desc3: along the holy prayers inscripted along the three foot long
Desc4: blade. platinum has been forged to form the hilt of this
Desc5: sword. A sunburst of gold is drawn masterfully on the
Desc6: pommel.

Name: Holy Wrath and Righteous Fury
Desc1: Two longswords, twin in every fashion, meant only for use in
Desc2: combination with the other. Ivory hilts embossed with gold
Desc3: meet glowing white blades made of almost pure and holy
Desc4: might. Sacred symbols are written like flowing grace and
Desc5: beauty. On one blade it is written "Holy Wrath" and on the
Desc6: twin it is written "Righteous Fury".

Name: spiritual warhammer
Desc1: Myths have told of great and powerful priests creating the
Desc2: embodiment of a weapon to fight all that is wretched. This
Desc3: is such a weapon. Created from some holy power, it seems
Desc4: metallic, yet weighs nothing. The heavens seem instilled in
Desc5: its handle and head, and you can faintly hear the chant of
Desc6: holy prayer, tickling your senses with a divine presence.

Name: white gold flail
Desc1: This great flail is made of the purest white metal. Silver
Desc2: and gold symbols of holy power are etched into the four
Desc3: spiked heads, each one bearing righteous wrath and fury upon
Desc4: the unfaithful. Many a good soul must test their virtue each
Desc5: day to use such a weapon.

Name: great mithril battle-hammer
Desc1: This large, two-handed sledgehammer is made from the purest
Desc2: ore of mithril you have yet seen. It looks somewhat unwieldy
Desc3: and slow, yet it seems to move with ease. Runes are stamped
Desc4: along the handle, written in flowing platinum. A massive
Desc5: holy symbol is stamped on the head, showing the crafter made
Desc6: it for fighting against evil and only for the just to wield.

Name: iron wand
Desc1: This foot-long wand is fashioned from thick black iron.
Desc2: It is entirely unremarkable except for the clear, silvery
Desc3: blue rune that has been carved on the head of the wand.

Name: platinum greathelm
Desc1: This is a massive helm of platinum that once belonged to a
Desc2: knight or noble lord. It still shines brightly and it seems
Desc3: to tell a story of chivalry and deeds of valour.

Name: diamond scimitar
Desc1: You see a magnificent weapon of platinum and diamond. The
Desc2: single cut of diamond is three and a half feet long, and
Desc3: slightly curved. The blade is razor-sharp with silver runes
Desc4: scripted by some priest or saint to show this blade as holy.
Desc5: The hilt is platinum with a sunburst of gold as the pommel.

Name: Solarblade
Desc1: This swift golden blade shines as if it holds the power of
Desc2: the sun. Three feet in length, it moves with blinding speed,
Desc3: a golden wave of death. The hilt is made from pure white
Desc4: pearl with silver lettering of divine power inscribed on the
Desc5: crosspiece. Weaving it through the air it makes a loud hum,
Desc6: seething with righteous power.

Name: moonstone rod
Desc1: This rod of moonstone glows a spectrum of pale blue, white
Desc2: and gold. Three feet in length, it is engraved with silver
Desc3: markings that run along the rod. At one end of the rod you
Desc4: see it is wrapped in some type of silver metal to use as a
Desc5: grip for this crushing weapon.

Name: Angel's talon
Desc1: This dagger is over two feet in length. Large for its size,
Desc2: it is somewhat quick to wield. It looks to be made of ivory
Desc3: but it has an almost hidden beauty not found in earthen
Desc4: stones. The blade is somewhat curved to appear like that
Desc5: of a talon. A golden sunburst is engraved on the pommel of
Desc6: the silver hilt.

Name: white oaken staff
Desc1: This is a six-foot-long staff fashioned from some white oak
Desc2: tree. It is carved to appear like a ring of angels dances up
Desc3: around the staff until at the top sits a sunburst of gold.

Name: obsidian trident
Desc1: Three prongs of obsidian stick froth from a shaft of burnt
Desc2: silverwood. Two-handed it is somewhat heavy to wield, yet
Desc3: the prongs look to be crafted to dole out the most pain of
Desc4: traditional weapons. A single crimson flame is stamped on
Desc5: each spearhead, showing the markings of some lost order.

Name: Demonslayer
Desc1: This is similar to the longsword, but is double-edged and
Desc2: is heavier. The blade is made of some strange crimson metal,
Desc3: that almost seems to dull your sense to touch. The hilt is
Desc4: fashioned from silver, with a single crimson flame stamped
Desc5: on the pommel.

Name: Judicator
Desc1: This heavy-looking hammer appears painful in the capable
Desc2: hands. Fashioned of some crimson metal, it dulls your
Desc3: senses as you touch it. Created by a master it is flawless
Desc4: in weight and speed. A single crimson flame is stamped on
Desc5: the head, and under it, in ancient tongue are the words
Desc6: "Judicator".

Name: ruby staff
Desc1: Carved from a maple, this six-foot staff shines as if
Desc2: freshly polished. A large blood red ruby sits atop the head
Desc3: of the staff, a faint humming sound can be heard from it.
Desc4: Strange red runes encircle the staff from the foot to the
Desc5: head, each glowing of their own accord.

Name: ivory crozier
Desc1: This staff of ivory radiates holy power. Bronze runes run
Desc2: along its length, radiating a bright glow. An angel crafted
Desc3: from gold shines from atop the crozier, wings outspread it
Desc4: points to the heavens. Under the angel are holy words of
Desc5: prayer.

Name: amber pearl earrings
Desc1: This pair of small amber earrings have been crafted to
Desc2: cradle a pearl, looking as though they were a pair of rain
Desc3: drops. The pearls seem to waver in front of you, but it
Desc4: could be a trick on your vision.

Name: fur boots
Desc1: These boots are made from a thick white pelt, that feels
Desc2: almost like velvet. Thick and very durable, they reach to
Desc3: the knee. Warm and snug they would allow one to traverse
Desc4: wintery conditions.

Name: brown leather boots
Desc1: This is a pair of brown leather boots. They come up to the
Desc2: middle of the shin, and look durable enough for long walks.
Desc3: On the toe of each boots a lightning bolt has been branded.

Name: winged boots
Desc1: This pair of boots have been masterfully fashioned from
Desc2: white leather. Soft to the touch, they look incredibly
Desc3: durable, and a pair of golden wings have been imprinted
Desc4: on the side of each boot, next to the heel.

Name: bleeding main-gauche
Desc1: This long parrying knife appears to have come from some
Desc2: crazed dream. Blood constantly drips from the blade and hand
Desc3: guard and is a horrid sight to behold. You wonder what awful
Desc4: magics are at work with this guard, and can think only one
Desc5: of vile mind would think to grasp it.

Name: onyx earrings
Desc1: Dark onyx set against an ebony backing make up this pair of
Desc2: earrings. Crafted with great percision and expertise, these
Desc3: show no sign of tarnish or age. Obviously of great value,
Desc4: these earrings may be of vast worth at a jeweler.

Name: battered chainmail hauberk
Desc1: It is evident from initial inspection that the wearer of
Desc2: this tunic met with a grisly end. Missing links, large holes
Desc3: and countless nicks and scratches show this tunic has gone
Desc4: through several untold battles. Despite this, it looks
Desc5: protective for someone desperate enough in battle.

Name: serrated spiked shield
Desc1: This medium shield was crafted with pain in mind. A large
Desc2: spike protrudes from the center, and several serrated barbs
Desc3: stick out from the front and sides of the shield, giving
Desc4: the holder a fearsome look in combat.

Name: black velvet gloves
Desc1: This is a pair of simple gloves made of a black velvet. Soft
Desc2: and warm, they have a tingling feeling when touched. On
Desc3: the palm of each glove is the image of a red eye.

Name: crimson earrings
Desc1: Small crimson discs entwine around two thick adamantite
Desc2: hoops.  On each disc a tiny flame insignia has been stamped.

Name: star helm
Desc1: Made of pure starsteel, or adamant as it was called by the
Desc2: ancients, this huge helm is a very strange sight indeed. A
Desc3: small oval covers the entire face of the bearer, shielding
Desc4: the front of the skull, as well as protecting the eyes, it
Desc5: is said the bearer sees only by the holy light of his faith.
Desc6: Twelve golden tendrils jut out of the top and rear.

Name: turquoise ring
Desc1: This elaborately-carved platinum ring is set with a small
Desc2: turquoise stone. The band is made to ressemble intertwined
Desc3: vines, with small leaves forming the clasps which hold the
Desc4: stone.

Name: silverwood helm
Desc1: This leather helm has been fastened with a covering of deep
Desc2: silverwood bark. While heavier then regular helms it also
Desc3: vastly increases protection against blows to the head.
Desc4: A single blue sigil has been carved into the bark, above
Desc5: the crown of the helm.

Name: cobra earrings
Desc1: This is a strange pair of earrings, designed to resemble the
Desc2: head of a cobra. The eyes of the snakes are made by polished
Desc3: areas on the fine mithril earrings, and the fangs are made
Desc4: by sharpened rubies. They attach to the ears with loops of
Desc5: thin mithril wire.

Name: Caladbolg
Desc1: This sword property of the ElfGod.

Name: shadowy portal
Desc1: This rift appears as though it were a vertical pool of
Desc2: shadowy black ink. A chill seems to flow from its edges,
Desc3: consuming all light, and making your entire body ache with
Desc4: its warmth-sucking embrace. There is no telling where this
Desc5: may take you, but it appears to be your only exit.

Name: iron key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted to form a
Desc2: circle, allowing easy storage.

Name: ancient blackwood heart
Desc1: An ancient wooden heart, so black it is almost cancerous.
Desc2: Dirt still clings to it like a second skin and a stench
Desc3: seems to arise from it intermittently. It still feels very
Desc4: warm to your touch as if it still held life inside of it.

Name: white oak forest
Desc1: You gaze at one of the many trees standing before you. As
Desc2: you look closer you see the leaves are a mix of gold and
Desc3: silver, giving the ancient oak a strange glow. Its branches
Desc4: reaching to the sky it looks like a great victorious king,
Desc5: returned from a battle of vanquished evil.

Name: white oak forest
Desc1: You gaze at one of the many trees standing before you. As
Desc2: you look closer you see the leaves are a mix of gold and
Desc3: silver, giving the ancient oak a strange glow. Its branches
Desc4: reaching to the sky it looks like a great victorious king,
Desc5: returned from a battle of vanquished evil.

Name: jagged bone key
Desc1: This key looks to be the chipped fingerbone of something
Desc2: long dead. It is extremely yellowed and almost seems
Desc3: petrified. The sharp edges look as if they could easily
Desc4: pierce the flesh of anyone using it.

Name: rotted book
Desc1: Age has not treated this book well, you can barely read
Desc2: the title:
Desc3: "Great.....Volume XXVIX"
Desc4: You open it and find a single coherent passage...

Name: black leather book
Desc1: A tightly bound black leather volume, no writing can be
Desc2: seen on the outside, as if something had burnt off any
Desc3: lettering. You open the book and find a passage.

Name: molding parchment
Desc1: Parchment written on paper now molding with age, you can
Desc2: only interpret the following before the scroll becomes
Desc3: unreadable...

Name: plain scroll
Desc1: A plain scroll made of simple paper, it appears to be
Desc2: some sort of official document from years ago...

Name: tattered manual
Desc1: A training manual from long ago, it is written in old tongue
Desc2: you open it and decipher the following...

Name: ebony scroll
Desc1: Bound in bright crimson string this parchment of night
Desc2: seems dull and unremarkable, letting loose the string you
Desc3: read..

Name: yellowed parchment
Desc1: A bright yellow parchment, written with black ink, it
Desc2: unrolls easily and you read the following...

Name: ancient book
Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and
Desc2: massive tome, the front reads "Epic of Ages Volume XXIX"
Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Name: ancient book
Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and
Desc2: massive tome, the front reads "Epic of Ages Volume XXX"
Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Name: ancient book
Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and
Desc2: massive tome, the front reads "Epic of Ages Volume XXXI"
Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Name: ancient book
Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and
Desc2: massive tome, the front reads "Epic of Ages Volume XXXII"
Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Name: ancient book
Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and
Desc2: massive tome, the front reads "Epic of Ages Volume XXXIII"
Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Name: massive black gem
Desc1: This gem is finest cut diamond you have seen in your life
Desc2: of adventure. It seems to pulse with a deep, seductive
Desc3: blackness, each one throbbing your temple, pounding
Desc4: against the back of your skull. You find it hard to resist
Desc5: the urge to grasp the gem and claim it as your own.

Name: long golden chain
Desc1: This is a long, extremely thin chain of bright gold. It has
Desc2: been threaded with some strange red material that almost
Desc3: makes it look like blood has stained this chain. A clasp at
Desc4: one end has been broken off, but it looks like it could be
Desc5: repaired by skilled hands.

Name: silver key
Desc1: This simple silver key still gleams brightly despite it's
Desc2: obvious age. Made with the curves, and teeth of ages long
Desc3: past, you assume it belongs to someone with a long heritage
Desc4: to have such an old item.

Name: pew
Desc1: A plain church pew, with a simple cushion spanning its
Desc2: length. It looks to be made of oak, and still smells faintly
Desc3: of it. There is nothing remarkable about this seat of faith.

Name: ship's wheel
Desc1: Aged beyond recognition this wheel that steers the ship has
Desc2: degenerated into a skeletal circle of large splinters.
Desc3: The ghostly magic that charges the ship keeps it together
Desc4: however and it seems to be steering itself by some unknown
Desc5: command or by the will of the ship itself.

Name: chipped obsidian key
Desc1: A large key fashioned from obsidian shows signs of use in
Desc2: the jagged marks and scars along its edge. The teeth have
Desc3: been chipped someone, and you are sure this key is totally
Desc4: worthless.

Name: platinum key
Desc1: A small key made of platinum it seems to weigh as much as
Desc2: a feather. Something is enscripted on the key, but it is not
Desc3: in a language you recognize.
Desc4: worthless.

Name: angelic statue
Desc1: A large marble statue stands before you, a sculpture of
Desc2: some angelic figure clutching a book as if it were more
Desc3: important then life itself. A silver plaque has been clawed
Desc4: and scratched as if blotting out any mention to which the
Desc5: statue was ment to honor.

Name: scholarly statue
Desc1: An ancient stone statue, fashioned many centuries ago stands
Desc2: here. You presume the statue is meant to honor a specific
Desc3: scholar that belonged to the library long ago, but time has
Desc4: not been merciful and the statue is almost beyond
Desc5: recognition of any sort. A large stone book is grasped by
Desc6: the statue, a title was once chiseled onto the cover.

Name: mage statue
Desc1: Enduring granite has somehow kept this statue from
Desc2: disrepair, though the age of centuries can still be seen
Desc3: in the layer of dust upon it. Carved into that of some great
Desc4: and powerful mage, he points his finger northward, as if
Desc5: releasing powerful magic to the oncoming darkness.

Name: blue book
Desc1: The cover of this book has a strange feel to it, as if it
Desc2: were made of feathers. The wooden cover tingles at your
Desc3: fingertips, and you hastily open it to the first page...

Name: ancient parchment
Desc1: An ancient scroll, written many ages ago, it crinkles as
Desc2: you grasp it, the dry page beginning to flake away from
Desc3: your touch.

Name: ruined book
Desc1: This book may once have held the secret to life, the secrets
Desc2: of the realm, and everything thereafter, but it is now a
Desc3: novel of dust, with pages flaking into nothingness
Desc4: as soon as you grab it.

Name: ancient scroll
Desc1: Time has finally gotten the best of this scripture to
Desc2: knowledge. As soon as you unravel the scroll you see the ink
Desc3: has faded beyond recognition and the scroll itself is about
Desc4: to crumble.

Name: crimson tome
Desc1: Crimson wood surrounds the pages of this scripture. A symbol
Desc2: of a large flame adorns the cover, and it faintly smells
Desc3: of incense. You open it to the first pages.

Name: black book
Desc1: It is hard to tell if this book has ever been opened.
Desc2: Not a spot of dust covers the entire manual and the pages
Desc3: look crisp and fresh. Spidery runes decorate the front and
Desc4: sides of the manual, you open it to the first page and read:

Name: blackened scripture
Desc1: This book looks immensely burnt and clawed in several places
Desc2: you are unsure if the contents can even be deciphered.
Desc3: You open it anyway and find a single legible page...

Name: black leather book
Desc1: A tightly bound black leather volume, no writing can be
Desc2: seen on the outside, as if something had burnt off any
Desc3: lettering. You open the book and find a passage...

Name: red book
Desc1: A red book with odd lettering on the wooden cover, you open
Desc2: it and read the following...

Name: blue book
Desc1: A blue book with odd lettering on the wooden cover, you open
Desc2: it and read the following...

Name: red leather book
Desc1: A large leather book dyed red, it bears a large yellow flame
Desc2: on the cover, encircled by birds flying in a clockwise
Desc3: pattern. On the spine of the book are the letters "A.I."
Desc4: You open it and turn to the following...

Name: ruined book
Desc1: This book may once have held the secret to life, the secrets
Desc2: of the realm, and everything thereafter, but it is now a
Desc3: novel of dust, with pages flaking into nothingness
Desc4: as soon as you grab it.

Name: death shroud
Desc1: This weightless death shroud barely appears to exist in this
Desc2: world, fading in and out of view. The very fabric carries
Desc3: the smell of death upon it, as well as a taint of supereme
Desc4: evil.

Name: sign
Desc1: This is a strange sign showing runes written in a dark ink.
Desc2: Though you can not decipher what is said you can tell that
Desc3: it seems to be a sign of warding, specifically banishing
Desc4: something or someone from entrance into this encampment.

Name: cot
Desc1: Mold has ravaged this cot giving it a look of a sickly
Desc2: green shade. You can tell it hasn't been used for many years
Desc3: but you are unsure who would have found it comfortable at
Desc4: all.

Name: bulletin board
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCRULES.BUL

Name: coffin
Desc1: A plain coffin, made of thick granite. Dust is caked on
Desc2: top of the coffin in a thick layer. Until now no one has
Desc3: disturbed this final resting place, and as the hair on your
Desc4: neck stabs you like needles, you begin to consider leaving
Desc5: it be.

Name: Flamemasher
Desc1: A large hammer, magically fashioned from hot magma with a
Desc2: black steel handle. The magma is shaped like the head of
Desc3: a massive warhammer, waves of blistering heat flow from the
Desc4: hammer. A set of black and white scales are the only
Desc5: markings on this weapon.

Name: paired dragonblades
Desc1: Twin blades, masterfully crafted, they have been honed to a
Desc2: razor-sharp edge. One is pure white, with glowing blue
Desc3: scales that make it look like a serpentine tail. The other
Desc4: is black with a dark red pall to it, glowing in counter
Desc5: with its white twin. A small dragons claw make up the hilt
Desc6: of each blade. The white holds a jet, the black a diamond.

Name: sapphire chakram
Desc1: A razor-sharp circle that shines with immense power. It has
Desc2: been crafted to appear as if a large white serpent and large
Desc3: black serpent were fighting over two sapphires, crafted
Desc4: opposite of each other. Suddenly a wave of electricity runs
Desc5: through the circle from one sapphire to the next. Etched
Desc6: on each gem is a scale of balance.

Name: Frosthand
Desc1: Your bones chill merely gazing at this instrument of
Desc2: destruction. Almost clear it is a large mace fashioned from
Desc3: ice. Gold runes are chipped into the ice, deep under the
Desc4: surface of the galacial globe. Fashioned around the rod of
Desc5: cold is a piece of leather wrapped around it so that one
Desc6: may hold the weapon without immediate frostbite.

Name: stone warhammer
Desc1: Black and white runes are inscripted on this massive sledge
Desc2: of stone. Made from some type of granite, its color is so
Desc3: dull it seems to flow out and shade everything around it.
Desc4: A pair of scales have been written on the head of this
Desc5: weapon of stone, making it the only markings that you see.

Name: hammers of balance
Desc1: Two hammers of adamantite, a matching pair of power and
Desc2: strength. The head of one hammer is crafted of diamond, a
Desc3: sunburst of gold imprinted upon it. A piece of jet sits atop
Desc4: the other hammer, a crimson skull imprinted as well. They
Desc5: appear as if crafted in pure unison, never to be used apart.

Name: Windblade
Desc1: Lightning erupts from this weapon as if it had struck down
Desc2: from the clouds and stuck itself to the steel hilt. Furious
Desc3: power streaks around the sword, as if in a constant struggle
Desc4: over the blade, weaving around like a coiled serpent.
Desc5: Untouched by this struggle is a large sapphire on its pommel
Desc6: a grey stamp of scales the only markings upon it.

Name: petrified mace
Desc1: A mace fashioned from wood has now been aged into stone,
Desc2: it has been fashioned to appear as if two snakes were
Desc3: intertwining to grasp the head of the mace in either maw.
Desc4: Despite the heavy look it is very light to wield.

Name: acid slasher
Desc1: A blade of magical acid is grafted to a silver hilt. The
Desc2: blade drips large goblets of flesh-eating acid on the ground
Desc3: causing a hissing to sound. On the pommel of the hilt is
Desc4: the symbol of a black and white snake intertwining,
Desc5: devouring each other in an eternal struggle.

Name: staff of scales
Desc1: A long staff fashioned from an alien material, it has been
Desc2: carved to appear as if two long snakes were intwined with
Desc3: each other, pointing opposite of the other.

Name: jeweled dirk
Desc1: Onyx and diamonds of all sizes decorate the hilt of this
Desc2: dirk. The short thick black is crafted of silver, with
Desc3: many runes adorning the blade. The edge is razor sharp that
Desc4: could easily cut through flesh or armor, at the base of
Desc5: the blade is a black and white serpent intwined.

Name: MagiRavager
Desc1: This massive greatsword shows the hands of a master smith in
Desc2: its creation. Made from some strange crimson metal, it moves
Desc3: with incredible quickness for a blade its size. Touching
Desc4: the sword dulls your sense and you see the stamp of a flame
Desc5: upon the base of the blade. You can also see written
Desc6: "ManaRavager" in ancient tongue.

Name: vorpal cutlass
Desc1: A three foot blade crafted from an unknown metal, glittering
Desc2: as if silver, yet black as nightfall. The blade is slightly
Desc3: curved to allow for quick, precise strikes that would leave
Desc4: a foe in pieces. A crimson flame has been stamped on the
Desc5: blade.

Name: jeweled maul
Desc1: A large crimson metal rod of eight foot length attaches to
Desc2: a massive round ball encrusted with onyx and diamonds.
Desc3: It looks impossible to lift, but somehow it is manageable,
Desc4: you find nothing significant about the gems, other then they
Desc5: seem to have been treated by some chemical to be solid and
Desc6: unbreakable. Defintely a weapon that could splat most foes.

Name: medal of flame
Desc1: This medal has been formed into the a flame from some type
Desc2: of alien, white metal. Crimson paint has been used to colour
Desc3: it in spots, and inscribed upon it are the words:
Desc4: "Order of the Crimson Flame"

Name: sacrificed body
Desc1: This is the body of a creature of unknown race, its skin
Desc2: melted away, a milky fluid covering it. Its flesh is
Desc3: embedded with pale, oval-shaped eggs the colour of maggots,
Desc4: though they have all been broken and ooze liquid. It is
Desc5: impossible to determine who, or what, the body once was.

Name: levers
Desc1: Two iron levers, side by side clearly show the abuse they've
Desc2: taken from the many scars and scratches upon their shaft.
Desc3: Left and right, they both look protrude here in an upper
Desc4: position, but they look easy enough to manipulate downard.

Name: red leather book
Desc1: A large leather book dyed red, it bears a large yellow flame
Desc2: on the cover, encircled by birds flying in a clockwise
Desc3: pattern. On the spine of the book are the letters "A.I."
Desc4: You open it and turn to the following...

Name: golden box
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: silver box
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: sealed letter
Desc1: Once pristine parchment is now stained with a mixture of
Desc2: dirt, sweat and blood. Yet the seal of the letter, that of a
Desc3: cat eye inside a rising sun, seems fresh and new.

Name: small vial
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with a shimmering green
Desc2: elixir. It is closed by a simple cork stopper.

Name: songsheet of swiftness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Swiftness.

Name: songsheet of force
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Force.

Name: songsheet of knowledge
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Knowledge.

Name: songsheet of sageness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Sageness.

Name: fingerbone key
Desc1: This small, fragile-looking key appears to be made of bone.

Name: ancient tapestry
Desc6: within the picture seems to draw you in.

Name: Deathweaver
Desc1: This long blade is made of pure black metal and is extremely
Desc2: cold to the touch. Underneath the shine of the weapon you
Desc3: think you almost see helpless faces howling in agony.
Desc4: You then notice serrations in the blade itself, almost as if
Desc5: it were to drink the blood of its victims.

Name: skull flail
Desc1: Fashioned by evil hands this weapon would strike fear in the
Desc2: weak. A long, black rod carries spikes of its own, even as
Desc3: its spiked chains are attached to three humanoid skulls,
Desc4: each one polished to a sickly shine. A single crimson rune
Desc5: has been carved into each skull, glowing with a vile light.

Name: demonic pitchfork
Desc1: This long, nightblack two-tined pitchfork radiates an aura
Desc2: of palpable evil. The shaft's metallic surface is engraved
Desc3: with all manner of twisted, hideous faces. The three teeth
Desc4: at the end are curved and sharp as demon's horns, the middle
Desc5: tooth being the longest.

Name: AngelCrusher
Desc1: Hellish runes dance along this evil weapon. Black draconian
Desc2: wings sprout from the handle to form opposing hammerheads.
Desc3: Crimson markings are seen all along the entire weapon, no
Desc4: doubt signs of the many evils that have been enclosed into
Desc5: the black iron of this crusher of angels.

Name: netherworld hammer
Desc1: This massive, heavy weapon is crafted from the essence of
Desc2: tortured souls. Their low moans continually escape from the
Desc3: grotesquely shifting surface of the hammer, and the stink
Desc4: of rot and burning flesh exudes from every pore of the
Desc5: weapon. A single crimson fang is carved into the top of
Desc6: the head.

Name: flail of oblivion
Desc1: This heavy flail sports eight whirling, spiked heads. It is
Desc2: made from a light silvery metal, which gleams with a
Desc3: brilliant shine. The vortex flail can be swung with blinding
Desc4: speed for its size, its multiple heads spinning in deadly
Desc5: arcs. Each spiked head has the marking of a crimson skull.

Name: abyssal scimitar
Desc1: This curved blade looks as if a nightless sky were used to
Desc2: craft it. Light is swallowed up by the edge and yet a deadly
Desc3: shine seems to dance along the length. Black iron has been
Desc4: used to fashion a simple hilt to this weapon of evil. A
Desc5: taint seems ever-present with this scimitar, and a low
Desc6: shriek can be heard as the weapon slides through the air.

Name: Demontongue
Desc1: This long whip is alight with unholy fire. Crafted from
Desc2: the skin of some underworld beast, spikes jut from the
Desc3: entire length of the whip, each one bearing a tiny wisp of
Desc4: a dark red flame. A massive cluster of spikes and beastly
Desc5: fangs end the dark weapon, surely causing suffering to any
Desc6: victim that it was used upon.

Name: Soulwaste
Desc1: Dark runes dance along this weapon of black iron. Slightly
Desc2: curved, the blade is very well balanced with a razor sharp
Desc3: edge. A small skull is set in the pommel, a crimson rune
Desc4: clearly marked upon it. The smell of ash invades your nose
Desc5: and grasping it seems to cause the hilt to graft to your
Desc6: skin with unnautral glee.

Name: darkbone staff
Desc1: The long dark bone of some hellish beast clutches a pulsing
Desc2: bloodstone at its top. Created from evil forces, sharp
Desc3: pieces of bone jut from all around the staff, causing
Desc4: enhanced pain for any that would be struck by its evil.
Desc5: The bloodstone swirls with each pulse, dark and crimson
Desc6: fluids moving in time, as if it were a beating heart.

Name: bloodkrys
Desc1: Nearly the size of a shortsword, this weapon is permenantly
Desc2: stained from the blood and gore of former victims. From the
Desc3: large jagged edges along the blade it looks that it could be
Desc4: easily baptised again. Under the blood you can see the black
Desc5: blade has a smooth, almost bright shine to it, a long
Desc6: serpentine letter wriggles under your scrutiny.

Name: Magus Ripper
Desc1: A long serrated talon gives this scythe a very sinister
Desc2: appearance. Crafted from a strange crimson metal, the blade
Desc3: is held by a large metal haft, ancient words scripted along
Desc4: its length. One of the words you catch "Magus Ripper."

Name: serrated bone war-spear
Desc1: A large bone, three-feet in length has been used to craft
Desc2: this weapon of cruelty. Jagged ridges surround the head of
Desc3: the spear, formed to cause great agony and bleeding to any
Desc4: foe unwise enough to challenge the wielder. The butt of
Desc5: the spear has been hollowed out to appear like that of a
Desc6: skull.

Name: crimson-hilted morningstar
Desc1: This large, heavy weapon has a brightly enameled red hilt,
Desc2: and its thick black iron chain is attached to a wickedly-
Desc3: barbed ball. Crude runes have been engraved into every
Desc4: surface, and it seems extremely cool to the touch.

Name: shreaded tapestry
Desc1: You can tell this was once a piece of fine tapestry, but
Desc2: that would have been ages ago. Now it is a pile of shreaded
Desc3: and tattered thread. Despite its poor condition you can
Desc4: still make out a picture in the tapestry. It is that of
Desc5: a person climbing into a pile of shreaded tapestry, as if
Desc6: it were some kind of portal.

Name: hangman's noose
Desc1: This is a long piece of rope, tied together into a formation
Desc2: commonly known of as a hangman's noose. The circular bottom
Desc3: is wide enough so that almost any head could fit in it.

Name: songsheet of enlightenment
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Enlightenment.

Name: enigma gloves
Desc1: Several pieces of coloured, stiff, cloth have been wrapped
Desc2: to form a pair of myriad gloves. The straps have been
Desc3: shaped in bizarre patterns that almost seem to throw you
Desc4: into a rapture. On each glove, the symbol of the Kai Lords
Desc5: glows a bright crimson.

Name: blue portal
Desc1: A large rectangle hangs in midair, a rippling pool of blue
Desc2: light. A golden aura shines about it, little can be seen of
Desc3: the other side, but there is no feeling of malevolence or
Desc4: evil from the rift.

Name: spectral shroud
Desc1: This weightless death shroud barely appears to exist in this
Desc2: world, fading in and out of view and giving off strange
Desc3: energy.

Name: amber sceptre
Desc1: Three feet in length, this sceptre has an odd glow to it, as
Desc2: if dimming and shining in its own pattern. Strange, unusual
Desc3: markings adorn it on all sides, and a shining ball stands
Desc4: atop its circular head. Great power seems to surge forth,
Desc5: and you sense a heat that emanates from the grip.

Name: silverwood staff
Desc1: This elegant staff is a living branch of the silverwood
Desc2: trees, long and slender and warm with life. Starting halfway
Desc3: up the shaft and continuing to its end, stars of all shape
Desc4: and size have been carved into the wood and have been
Desc5: coloured gold, with no apparent damage to the living wood.
Desc6: The silverwood staff radiates a palpable magical aura.

Name: crimson blood robes
Desc1: The strong scent of old blood covers these robes as if it
Desc2: were woven with the fabric. Perverse runes have been written
Desc3: into the the hem and back of the robe, with hellish visions
Desc4: and evil rites covering other parts. Wickedness radiates
Desc5: from this cloth, and only such a mind could consider wearing
Desc6: it.

Name: vortex staff
Desc1: This long staff is made of a strange metallic silver, which
Desc2: has a myraid shine to it. Strange sparkles shimmer along
Desc3: its shaft, as if it held stars inside its metal confines.
Desc4: The image of a circular wave sits at the head of the staff,
Desc5: and a crackle seems to emenate from it at odd times.

Name: barbed circlet
Desc1: This odd piece of headwear has been created from a metal
Desc2: you have not seen before. It is spindly and thin, as if
Desc3: it could be easily breakable, yet somehow feels
Desc4: indestructable. It hums slightly, and a glow pulses from it
Desc5: in a rhythm of its own. Large purple-tinged barbs stick out,
Desc6: as if to grasp the head that wears it.

Name: chaotic vortex
Desc1: Brilliant colours swirl about in midair here, as some sort
Desc2: of extra-planar rift breaks the air. Energy shoots from it
Desc3: violently, and the swirls seem to speed increasingly fast,
Desc4: and the rift seems to widen slightly, as if it were about
Desc5: to explode.

Name: greatbow
Desc1: This great, heavy bow has been carved from the trunk of some
Desc2: large tree. It is strung tightly with the sinew of some
Desc3: beast. Though quiet large it can obviously pack a large
Desc4: punch to any target. It comes with a quiver full of
Desc5: blue-feathered arrows.

Name: blackwood shield
Desc1: Carved from the bark of a blackwood tree, this shield is
Desc2: very thick. Almost as light as a feather in comparison to a
Desc3: metal shield, it still looks as though it would provide
Desc4: protection against attack. The blackwood has been polished
Desc5: making it dark enough to aid stealth-like abilities. Druidic
Desc6: runes line the shield all around its edge.

Name: scroll of serenity
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: vorpal katana
Desc1: This is a light one-handed sword. It is about three and a
Desc2: half feet long, midway in size between a broadsword and a
Desc3: greatsword. Its slightly curved blade is razor-sharp, and
Desc4: the sword is apparently made by a master craftsman. Its
Desc5: black hilt is carved in the shape of a rearing panther.

Name: blackwood forest
Desc1: The trees of this forest are tall, reaching over you like
Desc2: giant monsters from a bad dream. Red ichor drips like sap
Desc3: from the bark and the long, spindly branches stretch out,
Desc4: hanging its leaves over you like sharp claws.

Name: Crest of Silvermere
Desc1: This necklace glitters brightly with its fine, crafted links
Desc2: of silver. A graceful eagle of platinum spreads its wings
Desc3: on the large silvery disc, signifying it the crest of the
Desc4: great city town of Silvermere.

Name: blackwood harp
Desc1: This harp has been crafted from a nightmare. Jagged strings
Desc2: look as if they were made from twine, with points sticking
Desc3: out in some places. Fashioned from blackwood it has been
Desc4: created to look as if the harpist were playing on a ribcage
Desc5: of some beast, with a dark red polish shining from the wood.
Desc6: A crimson sigil glows brightly, branded into the wood.

Name: arlysian longsword
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon. The mark of
Desc4: Arlysia is etched on the hilt.

Name: arlysian mace
Desc1: This is a steel ball mounted on a two-foot wooden rod. It
Desc2: is a well-rounded weapon, providing adequate defense and
Desc3: attack. This is the weapon of choice for those of the
Desc4: priestly following. The mark of Arlysia is etched on the
Desc5: handle.

Name: arlysian dagger
Desc1: This is a small, sharp knife, used primarily for stabbing.
Desc2: It is easy to handle and to conceal, but it does minor
Desc3: damage. It is completely useless against most heavy armours.
Desc4: The mark of Arlysia is etched on the blade.

Name: ethereal sabre
Desc1: Smoking black glass make up the blade of this other-worldly
Desc2: weapon. A strange silver metal forms the hilt and a single
Desc3: grinning skull is the pommel. It weaves through the air
Desc4: leaving a trail of smoke behind, and it seems very sharp.

Name: silver signet ring
Desc1: This small silver ring has been fashioned to appear like two
Desc2: wings encircling each other. On the head is the symbol of
Desc3: a sunrise, with the letters D and B engraved upon it.

Name: morningstar ring
Desc1: A beautiful ring, crafted of platinum and gold, it has been
Desc2: fashioned to appear as if sunlight were clustered around
Desc3: your finger. Written inside the band are the words of holy
Desc4: tongue, they speak "Bless the Sun, Lifegiver."

Name: shamanic headdress
Desc1: This strange rustic headdress shows no method to its madness
Desc2: with the many pieces of leather, twigs, and animal bones
Desc3: that adorn it. It carries a strange mixed aroma that is
Desc4: impossible to identify, and it seems to tingle at your touch
Desc5: as if it carried some form of magical power.

Name: yellow potion
Desc1: This glass bottle holds a rich yellow liquid that almost
Desc2: looks like melted cheese. A simple cork stopper plugs the
Desc3: opening.

Name: crimson potion
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with a shimmering red
Desc2: elixir with large bubbles floating in every direction. A
Desc3: lead stopper covers the top, stopping its contents from
Desc4: spilling out.

Name: bubbling blue potion
Desc1: This flask rattles violently, as if the bubbling light
Desc2: blue liquid were about to explode. A large iron stopper
Desc3: covers the entire top of the flask.

Name: oily potion
Desc1: This large glass bottle is brimming with an oily fluid that
Desc2: looks to be filled with large crimson blobs, floating and
Desc3: congrealing together, sloshing the bottle around makes a
Desc4: quiet revolting appearence.

Name: grey potion
Desc1: This heavy metal flask is filled with a disgusting grey
Desc2: fluid that smells of dead earth and burnt wood. Blobs of
Desc3: matter float about in it revoltingly.

Name: sickly green potion
Desc1: This odd potion looks like some form of moldy vegtables
Desc2: liquified long ago. It has a disgusting slosh to it and your
Desc3: nostrils tingle from the smell that corrodes your nose.

Name: frothing brown potion
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with a disgusting brown
Desc2: liquid. The cork barely keeps the vile smell from your
Desc3: nostrils and you are caused to think that perhaps this
Desc4: is some stool sample instead of anything magical.

Name: rainbow potion
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with an ever changing color,
Desc2: with giant bubbles bursting and reforming inside. It looks
Desc3: somewhat violatile as if it might explode at any moment.

Name: golden sun robes
Desc1: These robes are made of white cotton and look unfaded.
Desc2: Sewn into the cuffs is the symbol of a radiant, glorious
Desc3: sun, along the hem you can see tiny words in holy script.
Desc4: A blessed calm exudes from the robes, and they feel as if
Desc5: only a person of virtue could wear them.

Name: ancient bone chest
Desc1: A chest that sends shivers down your spine it is a chest
Desc2: made of some ancient wood that appears to be stained with
Desc3: blood all over. Strange runes are etched all along the sides
Desc4: and even more archaic symbols adorn the handles and locks

Name: silvery spiked shield
Desc1: This is a silver shield of medium size. A massive spike has
Desc2: been masterfully grafted in the center, offering a warning
Desc3: to any opponents of the shield.

Name: ancient book
Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and
Desc2: massive tome, the front reads "Epic of Ages Volume XXXVII"
Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and

Desc1: Many years are stacked on the pages of this great and

Desc3: by Jiggs Longthorne. You open the book and read...

Name: black dragon robes
Desc1: A magnificent silk robe, coloured a deep black. Sewn on the
Desc2: front is a midnight blue dragon, reaching out with claw and
Desc3: fang alike to strike out. It is tied around the waist by an
Desc4: equally black silk sash that has small onyx sewn into the
Desc5: center.

Name: tissue
Desc1: This piece of carefully woven cotten looks as though it can
Desc2: hold up to many gallons of liquid.

Name: rotted worm skin
Desc1: A large, hollow piece of skin from some great worm, it reeks
Desc2: of filth and vileness. Though digusting it seems to have an
Desc3: unending durability that would make avoiding attack
Desc4: difficult, but deflect the force of the blow.

Name: platinum plate gauntlets
Desc1: These heavy plate gauntlets have been fashioned from the
Desc2: finest platinum you have seen. They look very sturdy and
Desc3: able to protect hands from harm. Great care has been taken
Desc4: to inscribe silver words of prayer upon each knuckle.

Name: blood portal
Desc1: A vertical pool of blood seems to hang here, floating above
Desc2: the floor with power of unknown darkness. Occasional screams
Desc3: are heard as faces, twisted in agony and pain are seen. The
Desc4: portal seems to arch its frame, as if grinning at you,
Desc5: inviting you into its warm embrace.

Name: scroll of rejuvenation
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: explaining the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: gravestones
Desc1: This grave was once dug very neatly but something from the
Desc2: inside or out has undone the work. Large clumps of dirt have
Desc3: been tossed to the side. Nothing can be guessed of what was
Desc4: buried here as the gravestone is indecipherable from the
Desc5: jagged claw marks that have torn into the rock.

Name: pile of spectral webbing
Desc1: This is a wet pile of webbing that looks to have come from
Desc2: some beast of an undead nature. It is very cold to the touch
Desc3: and almost feels as if it were sucking the life from you.
Desc4: It is most beautiful to behold and while it appears
Desc5: delicate, feels as sturdy as the thickest rope.

Name: weeping statue
Desc1: Cracked and faded, this marble statue depicts a middle-aged
Desc2: woman, weeping for the loss of life in the graveyard. Bright
Desc3: marble has now faded to grey. As you look at the statue
Desc4: more, an eerie feeling overwhelms you and every now and then
Desc5: you would swear the statue was looking up at you, grinning
Desc6: with malice, and baring fangs.

Name: ancient tome
Desc1: Opening the tome, you find a page and read...

Name: hideous face
Desc1: A face of unspeakable evil and glee juts from the wall here.
Desc2: Fashioned to appear almost as some kind of lustful gaze,
Desc3: this face looks as though it has been badly scarred. A large
Desc4: eye socket appears vacant, and its wide, demonic grin
Desc5: seems to have a gaping hole where a tongue should be.

Name: hideous face
Desc1: A face of unspeakable evil and glee juts from the wall here.
Desc2: Fashioned to appear almost as some kind of lustful gaze,
Desc3: this face looks as though it has been badly scarred, and
Desc4: its wide, demonic grin seems to have a gaping hole where
Desc5: a tongue should be.

Name: anvil
Desc1: This large black-iron anvil is propped up by a stand, giving
Desc2: it a height of four feet. Its flat hammering surface is
Desc3: battered in parts from heavy use, and other dents show its
Desc4: abuse as well. Carved into the side of the anvil is the
Desc5: letter "A", other letters follow but they have been
Desc6: scratched out.

Name: firepit
Desc1: A large circular pit of flame sits here, surrounded by
Desc2: stone. A magical blaze licks at the air above it, causing
Desc3: waves of immense heat to blast anything that would come
Desc4: near it.

Name: splotched scroll
Desc1: This long, ripped scroll bears several splotches upon its
Desc2: pages. The contents of the scroll contains the runes of
Desc3: magic, which can only be read by those who practice the
Desc4: magi talent.

Name: Kai battle-staff
Desc1: This long, slender staff is a creation of the ancient Kai
Desc2: Lords. It is extremely potent in battle, being perfectly
Desc3: balanced and imbued with incredible power.

Name: astral staff
Desc1: This staff is seemingly made specifically for fighters,
Desc2: however strong magics have been placed upon it. It is
Desc3: doubtful that any but the most strongly linked to magic
Desc4: could wield it.

Name: ancient sword
Desc1: This ancient iron scimitar was crafted very well, as it has
Desc2: survived many an age without losing its edge. Very well
Desc3: balanced and hilted with a carved oak handle this would be
Desc4: an excellent weapon for most fighters. A single rune is
Desc5: stamped on the hilt, possibly a family crest.

Name: ancient chime
Desc1: This is a bell-like golden chime, often used to ward off
Desc2: evil spirits. Dust covers it like a greatcloak, but it
Desc3: still looks useable.

Name: golden locket
Desc1: This small golden locket strung with a light silver chain.
Desc2: Inside is a tiny painting of a very beautiful woman.

Name: cracked statue head
Desc1: The marble head or bust of a great warrior lies here
Desc2: in pieces. It looks as though it had been dropped or thrown
Desc3: a great distance. Age and dust hide its guise, leaving the
Desc4: tribute a mystery.

Name: twisted tree
Desc1: This tall tree stands here, parched and broken, waiting for
Desc2: nature to end its existence. You can tell by the size it is
Desc3: easily a century in age, but scratches and cuts all over its
Desc4: trunk tell of a life not well lived.

Name: barbed key
Desc1: This key is made of some foreign metal with various barbs
Desc2: and spikes jutting from its teeth. A wicked looking key you
Desc3: shudder to think of the door that it must go to.

Name: stormmetal belt
Desc1: This is a very large belt, fashioned from hide and linked
Desc2: plates. From the blusish tinge that radiates from the belt
Desc3: it can be identified as stormmetal. It was obviously
Desc4: intended to be worn by someone much larger, but it is still
Desc5: possible to cinch it enough to wear it. An engraving of a
Desc6: lightning bolt has been stamped upon the middle plate.

Name: bone leg boney
Desc1: Upon closer inspection you see the leg bone has been jammed
Desc2: into a crevice in the floor, perhaps some sort of last
Desc3: ditch effort to escape this place of death. The bone appears
Desc4: lose enough that it could be pulled while stuck inside the
Desc5: crevice, but it has been jammed so tight that it can not
Desc6: be taken out of its resting place.

Name: bookcase
Desc1: This bookcase is covered in full layers of dust. Once made
Desc2: of maple, time has devoured it slowly, causing it to
Desc3: eventually cave in, covering the tattered books that once
Desc4: resided here in polished condition.

Name: pile of rubble
Desc1: Examining the piles of massive rock that lie here, you see a
Desc2: crack close to the wall, just big enough to walk through.

Name: black leather book
Desc1: A large leather book dyed black, bear no markings of any
Desc2: sort on the cover. You open it and find a page that draws
Desc3: your attention....

Name: shining white talisman
Desc1: This small white disk is hung upon a fine platinum chain.
Desc2: Strange runes are inscribed upon its surface, which read:
Desc3: "Use me above the pledging room."

Name: starsteel corselet
Desc1: Large, thick plates of starsteel give this corselet a look
Desc2: of indestructibility. The combination of so many shining
Desc3: starsteel plates gives the entire suit a vibrant glow.
Desc4: It's massive weight is balanced by the fact it provides
Desc5: incredible protection in combat.

Name: runed sacrificial robes
Desc1: Robes of midnight cloth are adorned with vile runes the
Desc2: color of blood. On the cuff and color the symbol of a
Desc3: crimson horned skull is plainly seen. These robes carry an
Desc4: aura of absolute damnation.

Name: mithril dwarven axe
Desc1: This razor-sharp axe has been crafted with the hands of a
Desc2: master. Form from mithril, the crescent moon blade has the
Desc3: markings of dwarven tongue inscripted in gold upon it. You
Desc4: are awed by the balance and sharpness of this weapon.

Name: serrated dwarven axe
Desc1: This heavy, one-handed axe is short-hafted and has a single
Desc2: blade shaped like a half moon. The blade has wicked
Desc3: serrations along its edge, and a thick, green substance has
Desc4: coated it as well. The workmanship of this axe is shoddy at
Desc5: best, and looks as though an amateur smith crafted it.

Name: black dragon gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of masterly crafted gauntlets, made from the
Desc2: hide of a black dragon. Very supple, they are soft and warm
Desc3: to the touch, yet give excellent protection against almost
Desc4: any attack.

Name: black dragon leggings
Desc1: Black dragonhide make up this pair of leathery leggings.
Desc2: Crafted by a supreme leatherworker, these leggings offer
Desc3: powerful protection for the lower body, and yet are very
Desc4: flexible.

Name: black dragon tunic
Desc1: Amazing to gaze at, this suit of black dragonhide was
Desc2: obviously made by the hands of a master. Spiked ridges along
Desc3: the back and shoulders give it an almost nightmarish look,
Desc4: making its wearer look terrifying indeed.

Name: black dragon helm
Desc1: This is a sturdy helm of black dragonhide, fashioned with
Desc2: superb skill. You see it has extra padding so it may protect
Desc3: the crown from blows with more protection then normal.

Name: black dragon boots
Desc1: This is a pair of skillfully crafted boots, made from the
Desc2: black hide of a dragon. They come up almost to the knee and
Desc3: are warm to the touch. Built for protection they are also
Desc4: form-fitting and very comfortable.

Name: white dragon gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of masterly crafted gauntlets, made from the
Desc2: hide of a white dragon. Very supple, they are soft and warm
Desc3: to the touch, yet they give excellent protection against
Desc4: almost any attack.

Name: white dragon leggings
Desc1: White icy dragonhide make up this pair of leathery leggings.
Desc2: Crafted by a supreme leatherworker, these leggings offer
Desc3: powerful protection for the lower body, and yet are very
Desc4: flexible.

Name: white dragon tunic
Desc1: Amazing to gaze at, this suit of white dragonhide was
Desc2: obviously by the hands of a master. Spiked ridges run along
Desc3: the back and shoulders, and give off a shimmering glow.

Name: white dragon helm
Desc1: This is a sturdy helm of white dragonhide, fashioned with
Desc2: superb skill. You see it has extra padding so it may protect
Desc3: the crown from blows with more protection then normal.

Name: white dragon boots
