Desc2: white hide of a dragon. They come up almost to the knee and
Desc3: are warm to the touch. Built for protection they are also
Desc4: form-fitting and very comfortable.

Name: blue dragon gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of masterly crafted gauntlets, made from the
Desc2: hide of a blue dragon. Very supple, they are soft and warm
Desc3: to the touch, yet give excellent protection against almost
Desc4: any attack.

Name: blue dragon leggings
Desc1: Dark blue dragonhide make up this pair of leathery leggings.
Desc2: Crafted by a supreme leatherworker, these leggings offer
Desc3: powerful protection for the lower body, and yet are very
Desc4: flexible.

Name: blue dragon tunic
Desc1: Amazing to gaze at, this suit of blue dragonhide was
Desc2: obviously made by the hands of a master. Spiked ridges along
Desc3: the back and shoulders give it almost a gleaming look.

Name: blue dragon helm
Desc1: This is a sturdy helm of blue dragonhide, fashioned with
Desc2: superb skill. You see it has extra padding so it may protect
Desc3: the crown from blows with more protection then normal.

Name: blue dragon boots
Desc1: This is a pair of skillfully crafted boots, made from the
Desc2: blue hide of a dragon. They come up almost to the knee and
Desc3: are warm to the touch. Built for protection they are also
Desc4: form-fitting and very comfortable.

Name: altar
Desc1: This large altar is made of smooth granite, with runes of
Desc2: wickedness carved into its face. Restraints for the head,
Desc3: hands and feet have been grafted to the stone, allowing
Desc4: little escape for anyone chained to its blood-bathed
Desc5: surface. An intricate spider design has been fashioned in
Desc6: the centre of the rock, its eyes glaring at you evilly.

Name: large chest
Desc1: This appears to be a large, ordinary-looking wooden chest. I
Desc2: bound with iron bands, and sits upon four short steel feet.

Name: arlysian firegut
Desc1: A strange and mysterious liquid resides in the depths of
Desc2: this stone tankard. A quick sniff immediately numbs your
Desc3: nostrils, cutting off all sense of smell and feeling.

Name: diamond willow staff
Desc1: Whoever created this staff had great crafting skill. It is
Desc2: taller than most men and is the color of old Ivory with
Desc3: veins of ebony. Where the veins swirl together in knots
Desc4: you notice the staff looking back at you. There are hidden
Desc5: in the wood the eyes of many creatures, you recognize
Desc6: owl and hawk, lion and wolf, bat rat and mouse among

Name: rotten eye
Desc1: White and pupiless, this grotesque organ was once the eye of
Desc2: some massive beast, but is now totally lifeless and smells
Desc3: of great decay. It is totally revolting to hold, and
Desc4: is very squishy.

Name: rotted tongue
Desc1: The massive, lifeless, tongue of some creation, it is
Desc2: putridly black, with some off shades of purple. You can
Desc3: hardly stop from retching at the sight of this dead member.

Name: ancient book

Name: white dragon hide
Desc1: You can tell this piece of hide came from a young dragon.
Desc2: White as snow it is somewhat heavy, with small spikes
Desc3: jutting out in some spots. It seems to carry a chill of its
Desc4: own, and you wonder if it could be used for some kind of
Desc5: armour.

Name: black dragon hide
Desc1: You can tell this piece of hide came from a young dragon.
Desc2: Black as night, it is somewhat heavy, with small spikes
Desc3: jutting out in some spots. Touching the scales show an extra
Desc4: roughness to them, and you wonder if it could be used for
Desc5: some kind of armour.

Name: blue dragon hide
Desc1: You can tell this piece of hide came from a young dragon.
Desc2: Blue as the sky it is somewhat heavy, with small spikes
Desc3: jutting out in some spots. It seems to carry an electric
Desc4: feel to it and you wonder if it could be made into some kind
Desc5: of armour.

Name: massive chest
Desc1: This huge black chest is carved from some sort of glossy sto
Desc2: surface is smooth and marbled with grey.

Name: jeweled adamantite ninjato
Desc1: This straight singled-edged blade is fashioned from pure
Desc2: adamantite. Its hilt is forged into the shape of a panthers
Desc3: head, and the letter "R" has been carved onto the base of
Desc4: the blade.

Name: adamantite longsword
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened adamantite, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its thin, heavy blade was made for thrusting
Desc3: or slashing. The feel of the sword shows it was crafted to
Desc4: be a well-balanced weapon, striking wounds with ferocious
Desc5: accuracy.

Name: blackened book
Desc1: A black silk cover overlaps the dark pages within, written
Desc2: in an odd script it is somewhat hard to decipher. On the
Desc3: cover has been drawn the picture of a mirror with a circle
Desc4: moving around it.

Name: dusty papyrus
Desc1: Through the immense layers of dust that have taken residence
Desc2: upon this paper you can barely make out the following...

Name: green dragon hide
Desc1: You can tell this piece of hide came from a young dragon.
Desc2: Green as the forest, it is somewhat heavy, with small spikes
Desc3: jutting out in some spots. You wonder if it could be used
Desc4: some kind of armor.

Name: severed head of Enigma Lord
Desc1: The bloody head of the undead mystic known as the Enigma
Desc2: Lord. Even in death his eyes are cold and unforgiving. His
Desc3: demeanor showing a will of iron, and unbendable force.

Name: blood gore
Desc1: Covering your mouth brings you little recovery as you vomit
Desc2: your last meal onto the floor. Pieces of humanoid anatomy
Desc3: can be seen all over this place, some whole, some sliced. A
Desc4: truly disgusting spectacle, fueled by insanity or pure evil.

Name: granite coffin
Desc1: A plain coffin, made of dull, grey granite. Dust is caked on
Desc2: the lid in a massive heap. On the sides you see massive
Desc3: holes as if someone had tried to nail the lid shut, but by
Desc4: the various cracks around them it would seem that failed.
Desc5: Something terrible has already broken out and is loose.

Name: yellow bone portal
Desc1: A grotesque piece of sorcery, this portal appears to be made
Desc2: of the bones of many humanoids. The vile gate pulsates
Desc3: making the bones chatter to some foul tempo. A swirlling
Desc4: crimson liquid pulsates within the portal, and the stink of
Desc5: death reeks from it.

Name: scroll of camouflage
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of barbed tentacles
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Desc1: Made of simple granite, this rock is very large and looks

Name: Crest of Arlysia
Desc1: This necklace glitters has seen better days and those days
Desc2: were long ago. Made of iron this crest once held some design
Desc3: on it to symbolize Arlysia but now it is just a chunk of
Desc4: useless metal.

Name: crimson tankard
Desc1: This iron tankard bears the stamp of a crimson flame along
Desc2: the bottom. It is almost overflowing with mulled wine.

Desc1: The scripture of the name is in very old fashion, possibly
Desc2: ages old. You notice in the center of the O appears to be a
Desc3: small indentation, a button of some sort.

Name: golden plaque
Desc1: A plaque made in fine gold, it has been etched with cryptic
Desc2: writing, the plaque reads:

Name: stone
Desc1: This large stone looks very out of place from the rest of
Desc2: the rubble. Something seems to be holding it in place, but
Desc3: it looks moveable.

Name: disfigured statue
Desc1: Once a beautiful sculpture, claws and other markings have
Desc2: mutilated this statue beyond any recognition of what it was.
Desc3: You can clearly see it once had limbs, but those have been
Desc4: severed long ago, leaving the marble to slowly crumble and
Desc5: further rot. As you seem to get closer to the statue your
Desc6: ears pick up the sound of agonized screams.

Name: warrior statue
Desc1: A large statue, carved from marble stands here. It shows no
Desc2: sign of age or degradation, as if it was carved new. The
Desc3: statue itself is sculpted after some noble, powerful
Desc4: warrior, a hard cold gaze staring into nothing. One hand is
Desc5: placed over his heart, while the other grasps a magnificent
Desc6: sword. A single word is on the statue's plaque: Ozrinom.

Name: wooden hammer
Desc1: A simple wooden hammer, it smells of fresh oak. It is a
Desc2: simple weapon of labor, a square wooden head sitting atop a
Desc3: wooden handle. Used primarly for pounding with great force,
Desc4: it could hardly be used much as a weapon against normal
Desc5: adversaries.

Name: wooden stake
Desc1: A stake of wood carved with master precision, the tip looks
Desc2: sharp enough to pierce any sort of unprotected surface.
Desc3: Made from a white oak, it smells freshly cut, but looks to
Desc4: have had some sort of hardening chemical used to make it
Desc5: almost unbreakable. It can be used by all priestly types but
Desc6: only for holy acts such as purifying a coffin.

Name: scrawling wall
Desc1: Brushing away the dust you can see that someone or something
Desc2: used a sharp, crude instrument to make the markings on the
Desc3: wall. It takes some time to read the handwriting but it says
Desc4: the following: Tis the sword, the hand and the eye, but not
Desc5: the m.... the rest is unreadable.

Name: black scroll
Desc1: With word from the Enigma Lord, I sense my minions from
Desc2: Silvermere have betrayed me. You saw them when you
Desc3: delivered the message of Nadroj. Kill them, and any agents
Desc4: of the white wench or the grey jester. --Balthazar
Desc5: --Balthazar

Name: scrawling wall
Desc1: Brushing away the dust you can see that someone or something
Desc2: used a sharp, crude instrument to make the markings on the
Desc3: wall. It takes some time to read the handwriting but it says
Desc4: the following: Sword, hand, sword, eye, then you die!

Name: stone statue
Desc1: A large stone statue stands before you. Sculpted in the
Desc2: image of a warrior, he wields a sword in one hand, and his
Desc3: other is outstretched in a grasping manner. Age has caused
Desc4: cracks to form on his sword hand, his other hand and his
Desc5: jaw.

Name: stone sword
Desc1: Upon closer inspection of the sword you see that it is not
Desc2: age that has formed the cracks but the original maker. It
Desc3: looks as though you could perhaps twist the sword while it
Desc4: is still wielded by the statue.

Name: stone hand
Desc1: This outstretched hand, palm up, appears not to have been
Desc2: cracked by age, but by design. Closer inspection shows that
Desc3: by turning the hand you can move it in a circular motion,
Desc4: perhaps even turning it upside down.

Name: stone jaw
Desc1: Though closed shut, this jaw appears as if it could be
Desc2: easily moved or lowered down to open the mouth, and possibly
Desc3: reveal the contents inside.

Name: eye socket
Desc1: At first nothing can be seen when looking into the empty
Desc2: socket, but as you gaze more into the gaping blackness, a
Desc3: small grey circle can be seen. Deep within the recesses you
Desc4: see a button.

Name: stone statue
Desc1: A large stone statue stands before you. Sculpted in the
Desc2: image of a warrior, he wields a sword in one hand, and his
Desc3: other is outstretched in a grasping manner. Age has caused
Desc4: cracks to form on his sword hand, his jaw, and a large hole
Desc5: can be seen where his eye once was.

Name: large sign
Desc1: A newly painted sign sits here in the middle of the road,
Desc2: in bright, obnoxious lettering it reads:
Desc3: Coming Soon! The most majistical marvelous myraid misfits
Desc4: in the land! The travelling comedy groupe of
Desc5: M. Alevolience and Co.

Name: pristine coffin
Desc1: The fashioning of this coffin was done with great care, even
Desc2: after the many years it has been buried. The coffin is
Desc3: fashioned of fine oak, with a crest of gold set engraved
Desc4: into the lid. On the crest the word "Darkbane" is scripted
Desc5: in graceful, flowing script.

Name: large sign
Desc1: A brand new sign sits here, pointing to a boarded up
Desc2: building to the north, the sign reads:
Desc3: Coming Soon! Phezik's Manual Labor Emporium
Desc4: Instant Work for Anyone!

Name: wooden box
Desc1: This simple pine box is about one foot long and half as
Desc2: wide and deep. Objects inside rattle about freely.

Name: Feyr
Desc1: A fearsome greatsword, it would require massive power to
Desc2: wield. Kissed with black fire, it shines as if it were made
Desc3: of darkest onyx. The hilt is fashioned from a blue metal,
Desc4: with the word "Feyr" inscripted along the handle. A horrid
Desc5: decoration is upon the pommel, that of a baleful eye, full
Desc6: of hate and evil.

Name: adamantite scimitar
Desc1: This is a curved sword, about three feet in length, and
Desc2: bladed upon one edge. It is thin and fairly light, but can
Desc3: deliver considerable slashing wounds.

Name: dark plated warchest
Desc1: This gigantic chest is made of a deep, black metal, that
Desc2: devours all light. It looks as though it could easily weigh
Desc3: more then a ton, and would be unliftable by any but a giant.
Desc4: A massive lock keeps the chest safe from intrusion, however
Desc5: the key has been left in the lock, easily allowing someone
Desc6: to turn the key and unlock the chest.

Name: yellow bone portal
Desc1: A grotesque piece of sorcery, this portal appears to be made
Desc2: of the bones of many humanoids. The vile gate pulsates
Desc3: making the bones chatter to some foul tempo. A swirlling
Desc4: crimson liquid pulsates within the portal, and the stink of
Desc5: death reeks from it.

Name: shadowy corselet
Desc1: This is a heavy platemail corselet eats the light around you
Desc2: with its blackness. Engraved on the breast is a white
Desc3: skeletal hand crushing a red skull. The armour is so bulky
Desc4: it would be hard to avoid not getting hit, but it looks so
Desc5: massive that it would take any blow with ease.

Name: oak chest
Desc1: This medium-sized chest is of simple but elegant
Desc2: construction. Long, interlocking planks of sanded oak form
Desc3: its rectangular shape, and the clattering of object can be
Desc4: heard from within when it is moved.

Name: large black gem
Desc1: This gem is finest cut diamond you have seen in your life
Desc2: of adventure. It seems to pulse with a deep, seductive
Desc3: blackness. A large O has been chiseled on top of the diamond
Desc4: in red lettering.

Name: silver box
Desc1: This smallish silver box is ornately carved with rampant
Desc2: animals. When moved, objects rattle about inside.

Name: scrawling wall
Desc1: Brushing away the dust you can see that someone or something
Desc2: used a sharp, crude instrument to make the markings on the
Desc3: wall. It takes some time to read the handwriting but it says
Desc4: the following: "Gem...storage......mouth....back...pray....
Desc5: opens....way"

Name: crowned spider skull
Desc1: A fearsome looking item, it looks to be the skull of a
Desc2: large crowned spider. Ridges around the eye holes show where
Desc3: the clusters once lay. The chitin is so sturdy it would make
Desc4: an exotic, but sturdy piece of headwear to protect in
Desc5: battle.

Name: horned spider skull
Desc1: A fearsome looking item, it looks to be the skull of a
Desc2: great horned spider. Ridges around the eye holes show where
Desc3: the clusters once lay. Two great horns jut from the helm,
Desc4: allowing one to possibly gore an opponent, causing harm and
Desc5: knocking them to the ground. Though odd looking it could
Desc6: make for a sturdy helm.

Name: scroll of natural prowess
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: explaining the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: blood inscripted scroll
Desc1: Ancient dark parchment has been inscribed with unholy runes,
Desc2: written with aged blood that has been caked heavily to
Desc3: survive the years.

Name: scroll of mass entangle
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: explaining the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: scroll of sleep
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: magma rock chest
Desc1: This large chest is made from magma rock, long since cooled
Desc2: since the day it was first made. It has trully been made
Desc3: from magical means, for the weight of it is quiet late for
Desc4: being made of such heavy stone.

Name: lunar chainmail hauberk
Desc1: This suit of chainmail shines as if the moon were captured
Desc2: in its very rings. Shining with a blue tinge, a silver wolf
Desc3: head is sewn into the chestcloth, howling at the moon.

Name: lunar chainmail leggings
Desc1: Tiny chain links have been woven with a strange blue metal
Desc2: to form an unbreakable pair of leggings. The way they glow
Desc3: it would seem as if they had fallen from the night sky.

Name: lunar chainmail coif
Desc1: Links of blue steel mesh together and form a tight fitting
Desc2: coif. The metal has a strange glow that gives it a strange
Desc3: alien quality.

Name: lunar chain gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair if elbow-length chain gauntlets has been
Desc2: fashioned in a bizarre fashion. Through intricate patterns
Desc3: it has been crafted to appear so that the hand were the head
Desc4: of a wolf, and the fingers forming the maw. It appears
Desc5: stylish without degrading the protection of the gauntlets.

Name: sadamune-
Desc1: This is a light one-handed sword. It is about three and a
Desc2: half feet long, midway in size between a broadsword and a
Desc3: greatsword. Its slightly curved blade is razor-sharp, and
Desc4: the sword is apparently made by a master craftsman. Its
Desc5: black hilt is carved in the shape of a rearing panther.

Name: poisoned shuriken
Desc1: This small steel disk has four razor-sharp blades protruding
Desc2: from its edge. A dull black substance has been smeared on
Desc3: the points.

Name: granite tablet
Desc1: This massive grey stone smells of fresh soil and rock dust,
Desc2: it weighs you down heavily but you not various runes and
Desc3: symbols of druidic tongue have been carved onto it.

Name: magma chunk
Desc1: This chunk of magma looks as though it would easily char
Desc2: the flesh off anything but surprisingly it radiates no heat.
Desc3: In glowing runes of druidic tongue phrases are written upon
Desc4: the lava rock.

Name: metallic parchment
Desc1: A thin metal sheet crackles with powerful energy, sparks
Desc2: jet from all over the page. Bright blue sygils of power
Desc3: can be seen very clearly on this metal page and they appear
Desc4: to be written in the language of druids.

Name: frozen orb
Desc1: This large orb of solid ice makes your teeth almost chatter
Desc2: with its glacial aura. Oddly you see faint crimson writing
Desc3: around it, which looks similar to druidic script.

Name: mutilated corpses
Desc1: Several bodies lie in piles along the floor here, all of
Desc2: them with various parts cut from them, sliced away as if
Desc3: they were choice cuts of meat. Some of the bodies you can
Desc4: tell have been here for some time, others look recently
Desc5: fresh.

Name: table
Desc1: This simple table has seen better days years ago. Marks and
Desc2: scratches decorate it like a polish, and it has been stained
Desc3: crimson in splotches, as if a great battle had been waged
Desc4: upon its simple surface.

Name: aged desk
Desc1: This elegant desk has been painstakingly hand-crafted from
Desc2: a variety of precious woods, and is rarely seen outside
Desc3: mansions of the rich. Thick dust coats it entirely, turning
Desc4: its polished brown to a dull, sickly grey. A drawer is
Desc5: curiously open halfway, drawing your attention.

Name: aged desk
Desc1: This elegant desk has been painstakingly hand-crafted from
Desc2: a variety of precious woods, and is rarely seen outside
Desc3: mansions of the rich. Thick dust coats it entirely, turning
Desc4: its polished brown to a dull, sickly grey.

Name: silver casket
Desc1: This squat, heavy silver casket is inlaid with many small
Desc2: etchings of capering warriors. It rests upon a small marble
Desc3: dias.

Name: stormmetal corselet
Desc1: Thick plates of a bluish metal have been crafted to form a
Desc2: massive corselet. Sparkles of white and blue dance around
Desc3: the edges and the plates seem to hum as they rub together.
Desc4: It is obvious by its size that a giant was the intended
Desc5: wearer, but with some adjustments it could fit the frame
Desc6: of a normal humanoid.

Name: silversilk gloves
Desc1: Woven from elven silversilk, these gloves weigh almost
Desc2: nothing. Stitched with runes of gold they would give any
Desc3: wearer simple protection to their hands.

Name: silversilk slippers
Desc1: This pair of simple slippers have been woven from silversilk
Desc2: that only elves possess. Embroidered with runes of gold
Desc3: they offer great comfort to the feet while traversing the
Desc4: harshest surface.

Name: demonhide sandals
Desc1: These blood red sandals are crafted out of the black-spined
Desc2: skin of a demon. They are tough and thick-soled. On the
Desc3: heel of each sandal, a glowing blue symbol of the
Desc4: Kai Lords is emblazoned.

Name: sapphire bracers
Desc1: Fashioned from a beautiful sapphire gem, and enforced with
Desc2: powerful magic, these bracers crackle with energy and might.
Desc3: A glowing warmth radiates from this magical armour, and the
Desc4: symbol of the Kai Lords can be seen within each bracer.

Name: sandstone chest
Desc1: This large, heavy chest is made of black iron, which has
Desc2: been polished so that the container gleams like a beetle's
Desc3: carapace. A hideous demonic face has been carved into its
Desc4: lid, and it is obvious that the chest is full of valuables.

Name: black plate boots
Desc1: This pair of boots is fashioned from thick black iron, and
Desc2: lined with the coarse hide of some animal. Formed with very
Desc3: poor skill, they lack any form of comfort but offer
Desc4: good defense against attack. A harsh, crimson rune has been
Desc5: stamped on the toe and heel of each boot. The iron is
Desc6: surprisingly light for its thickness.

Name: black plate gauntlets
Desc1: A collection of black iron have been fashioned to into a
Desc2: pair of heavy gauntlets. The palm of each metal glove has
Desc3: been created from coarse animal hide and each knuckle has
Desc4: been stamped with a harsh, glowing rune. The iron looks
Desc5: very heavy but feels surprisingly light.

Name: black dragon tabi
Desc1: These knee-length boots have been fashioned from a fine type
Desc2: of silk, and dyed a midnight blue. The form of a black
Desc3: dragon has been sewn on them, its tail beginning at the shin
Desc4: and its maw ending on the foot. The soles have been woven
Desc5: in such a way that movement would be muffled, enhancing
Desc6: the wearers stealth.

Name: mithril plate gauntlets
Desc1: This pair of gauntlets are made of the purest mithril,
Desc2: shining brightly in the light. They appear very heavy,
Desc3: but are surprisingly light when you pick them up. You
Desc4: can tell from the craftsmanship that they were
Desc5: fashioned by a master-smith.

Name: prismatic slippers
Desc1: This pair of fine slippers are woven out of a cloth that
Desc2: displays every colour of the rainbow. Smooth as silk,
Desc3: they are incredibly comfortable, and the warmth that
Desc4: radiates from them show they are of great magical quality.

Name: prismatic gloves
Desc1: Fashioned from a magical cloth, these gloves sparkle with
Desc2: ever changing colours. The outside feel smooth to the touch,
Desc3: but the inside of the gloves seem more sturdy, and a feeling
Desc4: of warmth flows from them.

Name: prismatic trousers
Desc1: These flamboyant pants glow in a spectrum of colour. Woven
Desc2: from a fine cloth, these leggings offer comfort and some
Desc3: durable protection from the ankles to the waist of the
Desc4: wearer.

Name: astral slippers
Desc1: Astral patterns dance along the tops of this pair of
Desc2: magically woven slippers. While more weighty then a pair of
Desc3: shoes, the power of these slippers easily offer more
Desc4: protection from the elements.

Name: astral trousers
Desc1: The bright sights of the astral plane move and quiver
Desc2: across this pair of pale golden leggings. Made of an almost
Desc3: weightless material, the feeling of immense magic radiates
Desc4: from the fabric.

Name: astral gloves
Desc1: This pair of silky smooth gloves reflect an alien greyness
Desc2: that moves about with a life of its own. At first glance
Desc3: these gloves look flimsy, but upon further inspection reveal
Desc4: a magical toughness that would offer fair protection to the
Desc5: hands.

Name: shadowy ankh
Desc1: This slim cross seems to defy description. One moment it
Desc2: glows softly, yet is insubstantial, then next becomes
Desc3: shadowy, occasionally waves of color ripple throughout.
Desc4: Only a dim red light is always visible at the center. One
Desc5: leg of the cross is a bit longer, the center of the shorter
Desc6: is ribbed, and fits your hand comfortably.

Name: wyvernhide gauntlets
Desc1: These leather gauntlets are made from the hide of a wyvern.
Desc2: The dull brown scales are extremely tough, and provide
Desc3: excellent protection for the hands. Wyvernhide is highly
Desc4: prized as wyverns are known for their ferocity in combat.

Name: wyvernhide boots
Desc1: This pair of boots have been fashioned from wyvern's hide.
Desc2: They are extremely tough, providing protection from the toe
Desc3: to the middle of the shin. The insides are lined with a soft
Desc4: material, to provide comfort as well.

Name: adamantite ninjato
Desc1: This blade of bright adamantite looks sharp enough to split
Desc2: a hair. The wooden hilt has been wrapped with fine black
Desc3: leather, and the letter R has been stamped on the base.

Name: scroll of eldritch fury
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: adamantite ring
Desc1: This ring is crafted in the image of a dragon, encircling
Desc2: itself to devour its tail. Written on the head of the
Desc3: dragon is the letter "R".

Name: adamantite chainmail leggings
Desc1: These heavy leggings gleam with a shine all their own.
Desc2: Crafted from adamantite, the chain links have been fasioned
Desc3: with an experienced hand. While heavier then normal chain,
Desc4: they also provide increased protection from attack.

Name: adamantite chain gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of elbow-length gauntlets, created from
Desc2: adamantite metal. The gloves seem to have their own gleam,
Desc3: and the links themselves show the excellence that only a
Desc4: dwarven hand could bring.

Name: adamantite chainmail coif
Desc1: Crafted expertly for snug fitting protection of the head,
Desc2: these adamantite chain links look almost invincible to
Desc3: the sharpest blade.

Name: adamantite scalemail tunic
Desc1: This suit of animal hide is covered with fist-shaped discs
Desc2: of adamantite. Each one has been sewn into the hide,
Desc3: clustered together in vital areas of the torso. On each disc
Desc4: the rune of the dwarven tongue has been stamped, indicating
Desc5: this fine suit of armour the work of "Martok"

Name: adamantite scalemail leggings
Desc1: Discs of purest adamantite have been sewn together into the
Desc2: thick hide of an animal. While the hide itself offers some
Desc3: protection, the powerful metal covering offers even
Desc4: greater protection to the legs of the wearer. On each disc
Desc5: is stamped the dwarven letter for "M" indicating the master
Desc6: craft of a dwarven smith.

Name: adamantite scale gauntlets
Desc1: Toughened animal hide is decorated with the fist sized
Desc2: shapes of pure adamantite metal. While heavier then the norm
Desc3: these gloves are clearly designed for the best protection
Desc4: in combat, without the weight of platemail. On each piece
Desc5: a dwarven rune has been stamped, showing the craftsman to
Desc6: be of great prowess among dwarves.

Name: adamantite enforced boots
Desc1: Boots of thick, heavy leather have been reinforced with
Desc2: large bands of pure adamantite. The efficiency of the work
Desc3: shows the boots to be of dwarven make, and their toughness
Desc4: in combat can be seen by the naked eye.

Name: starsteel plate boots
Desc1: You see before you, a pair of very fine boots. Thin,
Desc2: overlapping starsteel plates reinforce the already sturdy
Desc3: leather backdrop, providing amazing protection to your feet
Desc4: and lower legs. Inside the boot is layered with the finest
Desc5: doe-skin, to provide a soft padding as well as excellent

Name: starsteel plate gauntlets
Desc1: This pair of plate gauntlets is fashioned from the silver
Desc2: blue metal known as starsteel. Dwarven worksmen have pounded
Desc3: and fashioned the plates to maximize their durability and
Desc4: protection.

Name: starsteel greathelm
Desc1: This large helm is made of shining starsteel, as you hold it
Desc2: up to the light it gleams a brilliant azure. It is obviously
Desc3: work of the finest craftsmanship, but simple and efficient
Desc4: as well.

Name: starsteel plate leggings
Desc1: This is a pair of greaves made from shimmering starsteel.
Desc2: They look to provide remarkable protection for the legs,
Desc3: if the weight of the thick metal can be easily supported.

Name: starsteel bracers
Desc1: These shining steel bracers have a bluish-silver glint in
Desc2: the light. As you look more closely, you notice runes
Desc3: etched into their surface, and upon further examination
Desc4: you determine the runes to be of the dwarven language.

Name: tattered white bible
Desc1: With curled edges, and visible tear marks, this book has
Desc2: seen many days go by, and yet it somehow its pages seem to
Desc3: have a bright, enduring whiteness to its paper. Within the
Desc4: manual, written in silver, are the runes of a special, holy
Desc5: prayer.

Name: green dragon tunic
Desc1: Amazing to gaze at, this suit of green dragonhide was
Desc2: obviously made by the hands of a master. Spiked ridges
Desc3: along the back and shoulders give the wearer a powerful
Desc4: prescence.

Name: green dragon leggings
Desc1: Emerald green dragonhide make up this pair of leathery
Desc2: leggings. Crafted by a supreme leatherworker, these leggings
Desc3: offer powerful protection for the lower body, and yet are
Desc4: very flexible.

Name: green dragon helm
Desc1: This is a sturdy helm of green dragonhide, fashioned with
Desc2: superb skill. You see it has extra padding so it may protect
Desc3: the crown from blows with more protection then normal.

Name: green dragon gauntlets
Desc1: This is a pair of masterfully crafted gauntlets, made from
Desc2: the hide of a green dragon. Very supple, they are soft and
Desc3: warm to the touch, yet give excellent protection against
Desc4: almost any attack.

Name: green dragon boots
Desc1: This is a pair of skillfully crafted boots, made from the
Desc2: green hide of a dragon. They come up almost to the knee and
Desc3: are warm to the touch. Built for protection they are also
Desc4: form-fitting and very comfortable.

Name: wyvernhide helm
Desc1: This is a helm of thick, boiled, wyvern's hide. The brownish
Desc2: scales look dull, but immensely sturdy, and you can tell
Desc3: this helm was fashioned to offer decent protection for the
Desc4: head.

Name: blood-stained manual
Desc1: The dark stain of blood covers this wicked tome in every
Desc2: page corner, and crevice. Turning each page, reveals text
Desc3: more vile and grotesque then the previous. In the midst of
Desc4: wicked gloats, and stomach-turning torture, a rite of
Desc5: unholy power can be found.

Name: blessed scroll
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: pristine scroll
Desc1: This holy writ details the exact prayers and intonations
Desc2: necessary to gain the power to learn this spell.

Name: hide inscripted scroll
Desc1: Tattooed upon the hide of some ill fated humanoid are the
Desc2: words to an unholy prayer, giving power to those wicked
Desc3: enough to accept it.

Name: platinum plate boots
Desc1: This is a pair of plate boots, lined with soft leather, and
Desc2: fashion from platinum. The plates shine with a life of their
Desc3: own, and ornate carvings show great mastery was used in the
Desc4: making of these boots.

Name: lunar chainmail boots
Desc1: This is a pair of black leather boots, rising from the toe
Desc2: to just above the ankle. Sewn tightly about the boots are
Desc3: links of a strange blue metal. The chain seems to glow
Desc4: a metallic dark blue, and look strong enough to give decent
Desc5: protection in combat.

Name: belt of the crimson flame
Desc1: This is a wide leather strap with crimson metal scales
Desc2: fastened tightly together around it. Each scale has the
Desc3: mark of a flame stamped firmly upon it. The largest metal
Desc4: piece also works as the buckle. It is somewhat stiff to bend
Desc5: but flexible enough to wear around the waist.

Name: ogre-skin baldric
Desc1: The elegance of this baldric is found in its simplicity and
Desc2: its plain utility. The thick hide of an ogre has been
Desc3: tanned and studded with steel to provide excellent
Desc4: protection.

Name: crimson inquisition mask
Desc1: These masks are worn by members of the Crimson Flame to hide
Desc2: their identity and to intimidate prisoners put to the test
Desc3: of witchcraft. This mask is composed of smooth crimson metal
Desc4: and is featureless, save a pair of narrow eyeslits.

Name: turkey leg
Desc1: This giant turkey leg is easily the size of your fist!
Desc2: It smells delicious, and has been roasted in a thick, gooey
Desc3: red sauce. You can't help but get it all over yourself,
Desc4: and consider having a second helping.

Name: scroll of chaos surge
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: iron ring
Desc1: This is a plain iron ring, polished so that is gleams
Desc2: brilliantly.

Name: severed purple tentacle
Desc1: This is the deep purple tentacle of a mind flayer, brutally
Desc2: severed from it's previous owner. It is cold and damp to
Desc3: touch, and black ichor still oozes occasionally from the
Desc4: wound.

Name: icy scroll
Desc1: This scroll is tinged blue and tied by a bright blue ribbon.
Desc2: It seems to let off a vapor of some sort, and as you touch
Desc3: it, your hands began to flare with pain, as if they had
Desc4: been cut by something very sharp and cold, but no marks
Desc5: appear on them.

Name: long-spear
Desc1: This is a four foot long spear, used with both hands. It is
Desc2: fairly quick and is a good defensive weapon, but it does not
Desc3: do great damage.

Name: great hydra statue
Desc1: This massive statue is a monstrous sculpture. Fashioned from
Desc2: stone, it is carved into the form of a great draconic beast
Desc3: with two huge heads sprouting from its shoulders. Each head
Desc4: is nearly split in half by the maw it bears. The fangs of
Desc5: each head are easily the size of greatswords, and count into
Desc6: the hundreds.

Name: wall
Desc1: This wall of cavern rock seems to have been smoothed down
Desc2: through magical means. Upon closer inspection you can see a
Desc3: small letter "R" that has been chiseled in reverse on its
Desc4: dark surface.

Name: nexus portal
Desc1: This square block of energy seems to pulsate violently with
Desc2: life. Power reaches out from all sides, seeking release from
Desc3: its prison. Visions of a dark passage seem to erupt over the
Desc4: surface intermittently, and you realize this is a physical
Desc5: portal, leading to places unknown.

Name: burning key
Desc1: This key's head is shaped liked like a circled five-pointed
Desc2: star. It burns your flesh to touch it, and the taint of evil
Desc3: arises from it strongly.

Name: golden pillar
Desc1: A massive pillar of gold stands here, reaching high up into
Desc2: the sky. A myriad pattern of grooves spins around the pillar
Desc3: making it appear like a twisting screw with no beginning or
Desc4: end. In each groove you see several letters inscribed:

Name: bubbling black potion
Desc1: This small glass vial is filled with a jet black liquid,
Desc2: constantly bubbles and shakes about. Its impossible to tell
Desc3: the contents, but you think you see an eyeball floating
Desc4: around in it. The potion is stoppered with a thick seal.

Name: charred spear
Desc1: This is a four foot long spear, used with both hands. It is
Desc2: fairly quick and is a good defensive weapon, but it does not
Desc3: do great damage.

Name: ornate panther carving
Desc1: Made from a single piece of darkest blackwood, it depicts a
Desc2: panther, ready to strike. A superb representation, it seems
Desc3: lifelike from the brutal fangs of the gaping jaw to the
Desc4: razor-sharp claws on the meticulously detailed paw.
Desc5: The artist must have been quite an expert at carving.

Name: ancient key
Desc1: This key of ancient stone is shaped like an angel with its
Desc2: wings spread for flight. Most of the features have been
Desc3: marred by age, and it feels as if it were about to crumble
Desc4: in your hand.

Name: silver plaque
Desc1: Carved with a skilled hand, this plaque stands upon a
Desc2: marble pedestal for all to see. Various patterns have been
Desc3: shaped around the edges, and in big block letters you see:
Desc4: X B I E K O C D
Desc5: a few inches below the plaque reads:
Desc6: Speak the missing letter.

Name: slimey spiked key
Desc1: Covered in slime that reeks of death, this key appears to
Desc2: be tiny bits of metal somehow melded into one. Disjointed
Desc3: points rise up from the key, stabbing and poking any who
Desc4: grasp it.

Name: stone rook key
Desc1: Made of smooth, polished stone, this key has been fashioned
Desc2: to appear like that of the Rook chess piece.

Name: bronze statue
Desc1: A statue of newly polished bronze stands before you.
Desc2: Crafted in the vision of a crowned man, sitting atop a
Desc3: rearing horse. He looks to be wielding a large shovel.

Name: starsteel shortsword
Desc1: This impressive shortsword gleams with a silver-bluish tint,
Desc2: indicating it to be made from the rare metal, starsteel.
Desc3: It's razor-sharp edge looks extremely deadly, and it
Desc4: seems to glide silently through the air as you swing it.
Desc5: A well-cut diamond is set within the pommel.

Name: enigma sandals
Desc1: Several pieces of coloured, stiff, cloth have been wrapped
Desc2: to form a pair of myriad sandals. The straps have been
Desc3: shaped in bizarre patterns that almost seem to throw you
Desc4: into a rapture. On the heel of each sandal the symbol of the
Desc5: Kai Lords glows a bright crimson.

Name: tree branch
Desc1: Made from a tree you do not recognize, this branch seems
Desc2: to glow with power and youth. While it is not attached to
Desc3: any sort of tree itself, the branch does not bleed.

Name: bow of silver
Desc1: angel weapon

Name: chained pile of bones
Desc1: Immensely thick chains clasp around a pile of bones here.
Desc2: While the layers of dust speak of its untouched slumber for
Desc3: many ages, closer inspection reveals something went to great
Desc4: pains to break, and rebreak the bones. Undearneath it can
Desc5: be seen some writing, scratched into the floor:

Name: shintai sword-
Desc1: This simple sword is just under five feet long. Its three
Desc2: and a half foot blade is sharpened from both sides to the
Desc3: center. Its steel blade is a dull white colour and near its
Desc4: tip a single rune is engraved with unpolished gold. Its long
Desc5: cloth wrapped handle is stained with sweat and shows the
Desc6: swords extensive use.

Name: golden rod
Desc1: This four-foot-long rod glows brightly, casting everything
Desc2: with a golden shimmer. Words of a long dead language line
Desc3: its length, and it seems unusually light for being fashioned
Desc4: from a heavy metal. The top of the rod appears to be
Desc5: threaded, as if something should be attached upon it.

Name: black spiked ball
Desc1: The smell of burning flesh rises up from this ball of metal.
Desc2: Long, nine inch spikes protrude from the ball at every angle
Desc3: making it difficult to manipulate. A small hole can be seen
Desc4: within the ball itself, with tiny threads inside, as if the
Desc5: ball were meant to be attached to something.

Name: black spike
Desc1: Fashioned from a black metal, this spike looks as though it
Desc2: were filed to a needle sharp point. Dried blood and bits of
Desc3: gore stick to the surface, and it seems to emenate a strange
Desc4: throbbing heat.
Desc6: realize that the 'rust' is actually dried blood.

Name: dynamite longbow
Desc1: This slender, curved bow is made out of a long branch of
Desc2: supple wood. It is tightly-strung, and has a fair amount of
Desc3: stopping power. Its pull is a little heavy, but it makes for
Desc4: a good, accurate weapon. It comes with a quiver full of
Desc5: black-feathered arrows.

Name: copper cross
Desc1: A simple cross made from copper, it has been carved with
Desc2: great care and detail. It has been said that holy men hold
Desc3: it in hand, to strengthen their faith in times of crisis.

Name: massive boulder
Desc1: This massive stone is the color of dried blood and smells
Desc2: heavily of sulphur. It is hot to the touch, as if a fire
Desc3: burned deep within. It has been squarely placed in your
Desc4: path, blocking any further passage through here.

Name: multicoloured staff
Desc1: This sparkling staff is crafted out of four colored pieces
Desc2: of alien metal. Blue, red, brown, and yellow light seem to
Desc3: dance up and down its length, glowing about your fingers in
Desc4: delight. A single, silvery ball is set atop the staff,
Desc5: clutched by each of the four coloured pieces.

Name: diamond pedestal
Desc1: A breath-taking pedestal stands in the middle of the floor.
Desc2: Fashioned from some of the finest cut diamonds you have yet
Desc3: seen, it stands three feet tall, and its splendor is
Desc4: amazing to behold. Only one flaw can be found on the
Desc5: structure, a single hole gazes out, as if expecting a
Desc6: diamond of large size to close the gap.

Name: pearl pedestal
Desc1: A breath-taking pedestal stands in the middle of the floor.
Desc2: Fashioned from some of the most perfect pearls you have yet
Desc3: seen, it stands three feet tall, and its splendor is
Desc4: amazing to behold. Only one flaw can be found on the
Desc5: structure, a single hole gazes out, as if expecting a
Desc6: pearl of large size to close the gap.

Name: moonstone pedestal
Desc1: A breath-taking pedestal stands in the middle of the floor.
Desc2: Fashioned from some of the highest quality moonstones you
Desc3: have yet seen, it stands three feet tall, and its splendor
Desc4: is amazing to behold. Only one flaw can be found on the
Desc5: structure, a single hole gazes out, as if expecting a
Desc6: moonstone of large size to close the gap.

Name: marble pedestal
Desc1: A breath-taking pedestal stands in the middle of the floor.
Desc2: Fashioned from some of the most exquisite marble you have
Desc3: yet seen, it stands three feet tall, and its splendor
Desc4: is amazing to behold. Only one flaw can be found on the
Desc5: structure, a single hole gazes out, as if expecting a
Desc6: large block of marble to close the gap.

Name: diamond
Desc1: This large, transparent jewel is a brilliantly glittering
Desc2: blue-white in colour, and is highly prized for use in
Desc3: jewelry. Its beauty is only marred by the branding of the
Desc4: letter "N" that has been burnt onto its surface.

Name: moonstone
Desc1: This large, semi-precious stone is semi-opaque, and is white
Desc2: with a pale blue hue. Its beauty is marred by the letter "N"
Desc3: that has been burnt onto its surface.

Name: pearl
Desc1: This large, precious stone is pure white and seems to glow
Desc2: in the light. Its beauty is marred by the letter "N" which
Desc3: has been charred onto its surface.

Name: marble
Desc1: This large marble square is beautifully-made, and has a
Desc2: bright shine as if just polished. Its beauty is only marred
Desc3: by the letter "N" which has been carved onto it's surface.

Name: marble pedestal
Desc1: This intricately designed pedestal was most likely magically
Desc2: crafted out of raw marble. Four prongs break out from the
Desc3: top to grasp a magnificent crystal gem which sits directly
Desc4: in the center of the pedestal. You notice the crystal seems
Desc5: to glow with an inner blue light.

Name: marble statue
Desc1: This is a white marble statue of a ten foot tall knight in
Desc2: full plate armour. He stands before you, wielding a
Desc3: greatsword high in the air. It hangs just above the pedestal
Desc4: as if prepared to drop it down at any moment upon the
Desc5: crystal.

Name: crystal gem
Desc1: Cut by the most acute eye, this gem shines brilliantly in
Desc2: any light. It seems to have a bluish glow about it and
Desc3: throbs quietly in your hand.

Name: crystal gem
Desc1: Cut by the most acute eye, this gem shines brilliantly in
Desc2: any light. It seems to have a yelloish glow about it and
Desc3: throbs quietly in your hand.

Name: skull key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted in the form
Desc2: of a skull.

Name: helmet key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted in the form
Desc2: of a visored helmet.

Name: star key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted in the form
Desc2: of a multi-pointed star.

Name: ankh key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted in the form
Desc2: of an ankh.

Name: white pawn
Desc1: This appears to be a game piece of some sort. It is
Desc2: fashioned from marble, circular in size, and has a wide
Desc3: flat bottom which slowly narrows to a rounded top.

Name: black knight
Desc1: This appears to be a game piece of some sort. It is
Desc2: fashioned from marble, circular in size, and has a wide
Desc3: flat bottom which then is fashioned to become a horses
Desc4: head.

Name: white bishop
Desc1: This appears to be a game piece of some sort. It is
Desc2: fashioned from marble, circular in size, and has a wide
Desc3: flat bottom which then is fashioned to form a miter, the
Desc4: headdress of high clergy.

Name: white queen
Desc1: This appears to be a game piece of some sort. It is
Desc2: fashioned from marble, circular in size, and has a wide
Desc3: flat bottom which then is fashioned to form a tiara, the
Desc4: crown of queens.

Name: black king
Desc1: This appears to be a game piece of some sort. It is
Desc2: fashioned from marble, circular in size, and has a wide
Desc3: flat bottom which then is fashioned to form a royal crown,
Desc4: similar to that of a great king.

Name: sceptre
Desc1: This heavy glass sceptre feels as cold as ice. Its broad,
Desc2: flat head is engraved with a single, brightly glowing rune.
Desc3: The handle is wrapped in white leather, and a thong hangs
Desc4: from the pommel.

Name: black rook
Desc1: This appears to be a game piece of some sort. It is
Desc2: fashioned from marble, circular in size, and has a wide
Desc3: flat bottom which then is fashioned to become a castle
Desc4: battlement.

Name: crown key
Desc1: This iron key's head is shaped like a flat crown, with a
Desc2: cross at the very top of the head.

Name: ruby key
Desc1: This is a large shiny key carved from ruby. Its
Desc2: handle is carved in the shape of a flame.

Name: amber key
Desc1: This is a large shiny key carved from a large piece of
Desc2: amber. Its handle is carved in the shape of a lightning
Desc3: bolt.

Name: sapphire key
Desc1: This is a large shiny key carved from a large sapphire.
Desc2: Its handle is carved in the shape of a snowflake.

Name: stone key
Desc1: This is a large key fashioned from a large piece of granite.
Desc2: Its handle is unremarkable, fashioned to form a solid
Desc3: circle.

Name: iron key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handle is crafted in the form
Desc2: of a bird claw.

Name: iron pedestal
Desc1: Round and sturdy, it is a wonder this pedestal has not
Desc2: melted under the intense heat which surrounds it. Floating
Desc3: above the pedestal, out of reach is a large crimson shard,
Desc4: which appears uneffected by the blazing chamber.

Name: crimson shard
Desc1: This long shard of red crystal is almost blistering to touch
Desc2: for it seems to possess an awesome amount of heat. Inside
Desc3: the crystal you see flames dancing within, most likely
Desc4: fueling the enormous heat it emits.

Name: amber shard
Desc1: This long shard of amber is shocking to touch for it seems
Desc2: to possess an awesome amount of electricity. Inside
Desc3: the crystal you see lightning dancing within, most likely
Desc4: fueling the enormous shock it emits.

Name: sapphire shard
Desc1: This long shard of sapphire is freezing to touch for it
Desc2: seems to possess an awesome amount of cold. Inside
Desc3: the crystal you see a light blue icicle, most likely
Desc4: fueling the enormous chill it emits.

Name: quartz shard
Desc1: This long shard of quartz is painful to touch for the many
Desc2: razor sharp points that protrude from it. Pieces granite,
Desc3: quartz, limestone and other stones jut from it at every
Desc4: angle, cutting any who touch it.

Name: stone pedestal
Desc1: Jagged and rough, this pedestal of stone looks as though it
Desc2: had been ripped from under a mountain. It is a deep grey
Desc3: color and still smells heavily of earth. A large shard of
Desc4: quartz floats out of reach above it, hanging in midair above
Desc5: the chaos.

Name: throne
Desc1: Piercing spikes protrude from every angle of this throne.
Desc2: Crafted from some sort of black iron that has long since
Desc3: rusted and stained by blood, it looks as though it were a
Desc4: device for torture then used for sitting.
Desc6: power emanating from it.

Name: throne
Desc1: Crafted masterfully from solid gold, this throne would do
Desc2: for any person of royalty. Fashioned for comfort, a plush
Desc3: cushion of purple covers the seat. The faint smell of
Desc4: perfume is in the air, and you feel warm just by being near
Desc5: this symbol of power.

Name: nexus ore
Desc1: This dense metal is shocking to touch and almost seems to
Desc2: tingle your every sense. The large chunk of ore is about the
Desc3: size of someone's head, and is very heavy.

Name: skeletal remains
Desc1: A humanoid skeletan lies here, or what parts remain. From
Desc2: what you are able to discern, a large amount of force was
Desc3: applied to its structure, leaving most of it in chips or
Desc4: shattered bits. One entire hand though still cluthes a piece
Desc5: of paper.
Desc6: The paper reads...

Name: rock outcropping
Desc1: This outcropping of rocks seems to bulge from the sides of
Desc2: the cavern here. You note they do not seem very attached
Desc3: to the wall, and could possibly be wrenched from the walls
Desc4: if someone had adequate strength.

Name: void
Desc1: A large void of space stands before you, supported by
Desc2: nothing, containing nothing, you almost think it goes on for
Desc3: eternity, but that would still come up short. Suddenly a
Desc4: small tiny pin prick of light appears, and seems to move
Desc5: closer to the hole of nothingness.

Name: dusty tricorne
Desc1: Dusty, black felt has been shaped into a wide cone, its
Desc2: brims folded up and pinched at three corners. A faded,
Desc3: white plume boasts out from the rear brim, for grand
Desc4: display. Occasionally the faint, ethereal image of a
Desc5: skull and crossbones pearlizes along the face of the cap.

Name: raven claw
Desc1: This short, thick, double-edge blade is made of a shimmering
Desc2: material that has a purplish hue to it. The blade itself is
Desc3: a little over two feet long, and comes straight out of
Desc4: the hilt before coming to an abrupt, vicious curve.
Desc5: For those fighting in close quarter, or in stealth attacks,
Desc6: this weapon looks as though it would fit the job nicely.

Name: black dragon hood
Desc1: The cloth of this hood readily appears black, but shines
Desc2: midnight blue in bright light. A serpentine dragon has been
Desc3: embroidered along the bottom of the mask, looking as
Desc4: though it were about to strike. The mask enhances the abilit
Desc5: to sneak up on someone, as  it absorbs even the tiniest
Desc6: sounds of breathing.

Name: large rock
Desc1: Made of simple granite, this rock is very large and looks
Desc2: immenseley heavy.

Name: large rock
Desc1: Made of simple granite, this rock is very large and looks
Desc2: immenseley heavy.

Name: gold jeweled ring
Desc1: FILE DESCRIPTION
Desc2: WCCRING.DSC

Name: longsword1
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: longsword2
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: longsword3
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: longsword4
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: longsword5
Desc1: This is a three-foot length of sharpened cold steel, bladed
Desc2: along one edge. Its blade is thin, and designed for
Desc3: thrusting. Overall, this is a good weapon.

Name: silver gloves
Desc1: These gloves are made of some type of metallic silver cloth.
Desc2: Tingling the tips of your fingers, you notice the stitching
Desc3: along the fingers and wrists show an odd pattern, woven
Desc4: with black and crimson thread.

Name: silver hood
Desc1: This is a hood of metallic silver cloth. Woven along the
Desc2: border is a strange pattern of black and crimson.

Name: lightning whip
Desc1: A large leather handle connects to a thin, long tail of
Desc2: shocking pain. Electricity shoots from the handle to the tip
Desc3: in sparking waves of fury. The whip seems to sway around
Desc4: as if to mimic a snakes hypnotic dance.

Name: black chitin gauntlets
Desc1: These exotic-looking gauntlets seem to have been made out
Desc2: of glossy, violet-black plates of insect chitin. They have
Desc3: been bounded together with spider silk and treated with a
Desc4: secret formula which makes them extremely hard and glossy.

Name: red chitin gauntlets
Desc1: These strange gauntlets appear to have been made out of the
Desc2: shell plates from some gigantic red crustacean. They are
Desc3: tied together by some glowing vines, and it appears to have
Desc4: been treated with some mixture that gives it a fine sheen.

Name: training key
Desc1: This is a heavy iron key. Its handles has been crafted into
Desc2: three images, a visored helmet, a skull, and a five pointed
Desc3: star.

Name: stone wall letters
Desc1: It is hard to make out much of the scrawling here, as age
Desc2: has devoured most of its form. Trying to decipher the
Desc3: writing only reveals gibberish, with the letters
Desc4: "ukubakahs si rewop fo drow eht" etched repeatedly, ending
Desc5: finally with "egnellahc eht tiefrof dna drow eht esu"

Name: greater black dragon scale
Desc1: This huge black scale is larger than a tower shield and
Desc2: as solid as iron. It is incredibly light for its size,
Desc3: though, which is fortunate since otherwise it would be
Desc4: impossible to lift.

Name: greater white dragon scale
Desc1: This huge white scale is larger than a tower shield and
Desc2: as solid as iron. It is incredibly light for its size,
Desc3: though, which is fortunate since otherwise it would be
Desc4: impossible to lift.

Name: greater blue dragon scale
Desc1: This huge bluish scale is larger than a tower shield and
Desc2: as solid as iron. It is incredibly light for its size,
Desc3: though, which is fortunate since otherwise it would be
Desc4: impossible to lift.

Name: greater green dragon scale
Desc1: This huge greenish scale is larger than a tower shield and
Desc2: as solid as iron. It is incredibly light for its size,
Desc3: though, which is fortunate since otherwise it would be
Desc4: impossible to lift.

Name: iron earrings
Desc1: These are a pair of simple iron hoops, crafted well enough
Desc2: to not be called sloppy, but not magnificent either.
Desc3: Each hoop ends in a spike which can be moved for fastening.

Name: bronze statue
Desc1: This gargantuan statue of bronze stands thirty feet from
Desc2: the ground. Three distinct figures have been sculpted,
Desc3: one in full armour, another enshrouded by a cloak, and the
Desc4: last in plain robes. Nothing else can be seen of the figures
Desc5: for they have been posed with their backs facing outward.

Name: red skull
Desc1: Iron, painted red, has been used by expert hands to form a
Desc2: skull. Two gaping holes form the eye sockets, and the teeth
Desc3: have been chisled to give the skull a frightening, fanged
Desc4: leer. Ridges along the back of the skull allow for one hand
Desc5: to grasp it, as if to show any who would see it's wicked
Desc6: visage.

Name: burning scroll
Desc1: Reeking of sulphur, this scroll appears to be burning up,
Desc2: but still the strange paper remains whole. Upon it are
Desc3: written the rite of some wickedly evil prayer.

Name: sandstone tablet
Desc1: This large sandstone slab is crudely engraved with intricate
Desc2: runes of power, which you recognize as druidic magic.

Name: scroll of glacial skin
Desc1: This bark parchment has swirling runes burned onto it,
Desc2: detailing the rituals and methods of learning this spell.

Name: stained papyrus scroll
Desc1: This ancient, crumbling scroll of coarse-grained paper has
Desc2: been greatly dirtied and stained over the years. Despite
Desc3: this you are still able to read the words of an ancient,
Desc4: guttural tongue writen upon its surface. They appear to be
Desc5: words to an unholy prayer.

Name: scroll of resist lightning
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with runes of magic, but exactly
Desc2: what is written can only be learned by reading it.

Name: grey robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: grey robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: adamantite wrist guard
Desc1: This wrist guard is made from pure adamantite, glimmmering
Desc2: darkly as you turn it this way and that examining the
Desc3: exquisite work. The metal is tastefully paired with black
Desc4: leather to form a dark and dangerous looking wrist guard,
Desc5: while still providing excellent protection and flexibility
Desc6: for the off-hand.

Name: runed wrist guard
Desc1: This ornate wrist guard is crafted of fine steel, with
Desc2: glittering runes of power engraved along it's length.
Desc3: Artfully cured leather straps bind it's cool, smooth surface
Desc4: to your wrist and hand, offering superior protection as well
Desc5: as mobility.

Name: mithril chainmail boots
Desc1: This is a pair of elven leather boots, covered with
Desc2: dwarven-crafted mithril links of chain. It is exceedingly
Desc3: rare for the elves and the dwarves to combine their
Desc4: methods of craftsmanship, but the result is
Desc5: precious indeed. The boots provide excellent protection
Desc6: without hindering stealthy movement.

Name: red paisley bandanna
Desc1: A large red cloth square, stiched with a white and black
Desc2: paisley print, is folded along it's diagonal and tied around
Desc3: around the head. It looks well worn, so worn in fact, that
Desc4: the voices of the previous wearers can occasionally be heard
Desc5: whispering indiscernibly.

Name: gold-coin sash
Desc1: Hundreds of bright, rune-stamped, gold coins have been
Desc2: hammered and chained together to form a grand hip scarf.
Desc3: Triangular in shape, the coins cover all down your thigh
Desc4: on one side, raising to a tied knot on the other. It can be
Desc5: fairly noisey while walking, if attention is not paid to
Desc6: move fastidiously.

Name: brass zills
Desc1: Finger-symbols, worn on the thumb and middle finger,
Desc2: are used to distract and entice targets. Their strange
Desc3: melodies, when used my knowing hands, infuse with the
Desc4: zills' own powers to create unique effects. This particular
Desc5: pair has been engraved with orchids, painted violet.

Name: mirrored choli
Desc1: Strips of variously colored and printed fabrics have
Desc2: been stiched together to form this tight fitting,
Desc3: long-sleeved, raffish blouse. Paired swirls draw attention
Desc4: to the upper chest, while each horizontal layer of fabric
Desc5: is alternated with a row of mirror-embedded cloth.
Desc6: Silvery runes glimmer near each mirror eyelet.

Name: blue pantaloons
Desc1: Bright, nearly electric, blue silk is pleated in between
Desc2: vertical strips of shiney black leather. The pants are
Desc3: almost an eyesore, being fairly snug at the waist and ankles
Desc4: though billowing out at the legs. The silk shimmers oddly,
Desc5: however, as silvery runes and tiny black diamonds have
Desc6: been embedded into the cloth.

Name: layered sun skirt
Desc1: The top layer of this skirt has been dyed yellow, with
Desc2: blazing suns worked into its surface. It is solid around
Desc3: the upper thighs, dividing at center into long strips
Desc4: that are tipped with topaz-stone suns. The under layer,
Desc5: visible lower thigh down, is bright yellow and orange,
Desc6: cut into vertical strips as though sunfire.

Name: songsheet of beauty
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Beauty.

Name: songsheet of ugliness
Desc1: This parchment is inscribed with the musical knowledge to
Desc2: sing the magical Song of Ugliness.

Name: astral skirt
Desc1: The bright sights of the astral plane move and quiver
Desc2: across this wrap of pale golden fabric. Made of an almost
Desc3: weightless material, the feeling of immense magic radiates
Desc4: from the fabric.

Name: black silk skirt
Desc1: This fine wrap is woven out of a glossy black silk. It is
Desc2: embroidered with black thread, and is surprisingly tough.
Desc3: At second glance intricate symbols can be seen stitched all
Desc4: over their surface.

Name: prismatic skirt
Desc1: This flamboyant skirt glows in a spectrum of colour. Woven
Desc2: from a fine cloth, the wrap offers comfort and some
Desc3: durable protection from the ankles to the waist of the
Desc4: wearer.

Name: silk skirt
Desc1: This long wrap of brilliant silk is of excellent
Desc2: workmanship. It are light and loose, ties in a knot at the
Desc3: waist, and hangs down to the ankles.

Name: white scroll
Desc1: Written upon bleached white paper, in gold letters you can
Desc2: tell this scroll is a prayer of good priestly virtue.

Name: shimmering papyrus
Desc1: This coarse-grained paper seems to disappear and reappear at
Desc2: random intervals. Runes of magic are inscribed in a thick,
Desc3: black ink. The runes seem to spell out powers that can only
Desc4: be harnessed by powerful magi.

Name: crimson chest
Desc1: This large chest has been crafted from a thick pine. Stained
Desc2: a deep crimson, well-crafted designs have been carved upon
Desc3: it's surface, including a large flame upon the lid.

Name: grey robes
Desc1: This is a simple loose cloth tunic, made of soft cotton. It
Desc2: is thin and provides little protection, but is quite light.

Name: water lily
Desc1: Designed for floating freely, a large, trumpet-like flower
Desc2: rests candidly atop a broad, circular leaf. A languid, thin
Desc3: strand of roots dangles from beneath the flower, to provide
Desc4: necessary sustenance.

Name: violet orchid
Desc1: A narrow, dangly brown stem bears five, perfectly-shaped,
Desc2: violet flowers. Each flower has five petals, round and broad
Desc3: encircling feathery, red anthers. Each orchid plant will
Desc4: only bear this one stem of flowers, making them extremely
Desc5: exotic and beautiful.

Name: onion
Desc1: This globe-shaped bulb is slightly smaller than your hand,
Desc2: and is composed of many concentrically arranged layers.
Desc3: It is yellowish in color, and each layer is paper-thin.

Name: carrot
Desc1: This thick, bright orange root is capped with a crown of
Desc2: tall, feathery green leaves. Small rootlets reach out from
Desc3: around the carrot, adding to its grainy texture.

Name: potato
Desc1: This swollen root has brown dirty skin and yellow starchy
Desc2: flesh. It is oblong and round, though quite unevenly, as
Desc3: in some places it seems concaved in.

Name: pumpkin
Desc1: A massive, telltale orange globe sits at the end of a
Desc2: long prickly vine. It is naturally pleated, and is
Desc3: flattened on the side it was laying on to grow. Within
Desc4: it is a mess of stringy flesh and almond-like seeds,
Desc5: seeming kind of hollow.

Name: red keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate red keys.

Name: orange keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate orange keys.

Name: yellow keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate yellow keys.

Name: green keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate green keys.

Name: blue keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate blue keys.

Name: violet keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate violet keys.

Name: black keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate black keys.

Name: silver keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate silver keys.

Name: gold keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate gold keys.

Name: white keyring
Desc1: A steel ring, wide enough to slip around one's wrist with
Desc2: ease. It contains ten duplicate white keys.

Name: altar
Desc1: A round pillar of molten brimstone is set in the center of
Desc2: the lair, flames billowing high from its center pit. Glyphs
Desc3: and other symbols of forbidden arcanery flicker from the
Desc4: altar's smoldering surface, seeming like caged spirits held
Desc5: against their will.

Name: skirts of flame
Desc1: Red and orange silk make up the underlayers of these
Desc2: eyecatching skirts, with the topmost pieces shaped like
Desc3: petals of the sun. The pieces rise and sway as small flames
Desc4: run course along their surface. The deep red inner layer
Desc5: feels cool to the touch.

Name: ruby hairpin
Desc1: This sturdy hairpin is covered in tiny diamonds, with 5 tear
Desc2: shaped rubies making a flower at the tip.

Name: lock of fiery hair
Desc1: This lovely lock of hair still burns with energy. Each fine
Desc2: strand is a different color of flame, and is warm to the
Desc3: touch.

Name: crimson ring
Desc1: This ring covers nearly the entire length of the inner
Desc2: finger and appears to be master crafted from crimson
Desc3: metal. The underside is finely textured, helping to
Desc4: aid in the grip of a weapon. Set in the top is a
Desc5: narrow ruby within an oval engraving much resembling
Desc6: a burning flame.

Name: apple tree
Desc1: Matured well into its prime, this beautiful, healthy tree
Desc2: has greyish brown bark and soft green leaves. The
Desc3: branches and foliage are so thick it is sometimes difficult
Desc4: to spot ripened fruits within. You think you spot a ready
Desc5: fruit hanging just above your reach.

Name: apple tree
Desc1: Matured well into its prime, this beautiful, healthy tree
Desc2: has greyish brown bark and soft green leaves. The
Desc3: branches and foliage are so thick it is sometimes difficult
Desc4: to spot ripened fruits within.

Name: apple
Desc1: A semi-round fruit with bright red skin and off-white flesh.
Desc2: A dry, brown stem and small green leaf are still attached to
Desc3: its crown.

Name: bruised apple
Desc1: A semi-round fruit with spotchy red skin and slightly brown
Desc2: flesh. A dry stem and small green leaf are still attached
Desc3: to its crown.

Name: wooden ladder
Desc1: Two long, parellel planks of wood are attached together by
Desc2: evenly spaced, perpendicular steps. The wood has been sanded
Desc3: smooth, and feels fairly trustworthy not to break from under
Desc4: you.

Name: flowery apron
Desc1: A garment, fastened around the waist in the back, worn over
Desc2: the lower front of the body to protect clothing. The fabric
Desc3: is embroidered with tiny flowers around the edges, and the
Desc4: letters "W.W." boldy read from the bottom right corner.

Name: apple pie
Desc1: An apple filled pastry fills and is folded over a thin tin
Desc2: pan. The dough is cross-hatched across the top, and baked
Desc3: to golden perfection. The smell of cinnamon seeps wafts out
Desc4: from within, oozing in places where the apple goo has seeped
Desc5: out of cracks.

Name: glass jug
Desc1: A large clear container, bowled out at the center and
Desc2: funneling to a thin nozzle at the top. A small brown cork
Desc3: is stuck in the nozzle.

Name: jug of cider
Desc1: A large glass jug, bowled out at the center and funneling to
Desc2: a thin nozzle at the top. It is filled with a clear,
Desc3: honey-colored liquid, that smells quite strongly of apples
Desc4: and alcohol when uncorked.

Name: dunce cap
Desc1: this item reserved for jinx...I got your tricorne right here

Name: Pen and Paper
Desc1: "Kill Oz"

Name: wooden ladder
Desc1: Two long, parellel planks of wood are attached together by
Desc2: evenly spaced, perpendicular steps. The wood looks chipped
Desc3: and gnawed, and it is easy to tell this ladder has been used
Desc4: many times.
